rn Forward represented her country in highest levels like the Olympics and the World Cup.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-357\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alex-Morgan-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Alex Morgan (USA)\" width=\"683\" height=\"1024\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lauren Sesselmann (Canada)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Houston Dash defender won an Olympic bronze for her country. By the way, she was born in America.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-378\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Lauren-Sesselmann-1.jpg\" alt=\"Lauren Sesselmann\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Alexia Putellas (Spain)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Playing for FC Barcelona, Alexia has already won 5 titles in total. In 2013, she scored a magnificent goal that made her famous.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-358\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alexia-Putellas.jpg\" alt=\"Alexia Putellas\" width=\"500\" height=\"294\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Amanda Ilestedt (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Swedish defender is known for her tactical skills. She plays for Damallsvenskan club FC Rosengård in the domestic arena.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-359\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Amanda-Ilestedt-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Amanda Ilestedt (Sweden)\" width=\"830\" height=\"552\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Amandine Henry (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The French international plays in the defensive midfield position. She won the Bronze Ball Award in a world cup.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-386\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Amandine-Henry-France-1.jpg\" alt=\"Amandine Henry (France)\" width=\"600\" height=\"814\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Angela Christ (Netherlands)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Dutch footballer is the Netherlands’ last line of defense under the crossbar.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-361\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Angela-Christ-Netherlands.jpg\" alt=\"Angela Christ (Netherlands)\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anna Green (New Zealand)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The kiwi defender is someone to keep an eye on. She represented her country in the Beijing Olympics.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-362\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anna-Green-New-Zealand.jpg\" alt=\"Anna Green (New Zealand)\" width=\"650\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anouk Hoogendijk (Netherlands)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Anouk Hoogendijk plays for top Dutch side Ajax. Her primary position is the midfield.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-363\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anouk-Hoogendijk-Netherlands.jpg\" alt=\"Anouk Hoogendijk (Netherlands)\" width=\"650\" height=\"487\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Christen Press (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Christen was a part of the Rio Olympics team. She is famous for her athletic skills.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-364\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Christen-Press-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Christen Press (USA)\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Claire Lavogez (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>21 year old Claire plays for Olympique Lyon as a midfielder. She is considered as one of the aspirant stars in the French national side.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Daniela Cruz (Costa Rica)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Defender Daniela Cruz represents Costa Rica in the international arena.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Erika Cristiano dos Santos (Brazil)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Erika won silver medal for her country playing in the Beijing Olympics.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Erin Nayler (New Zealand)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the international level she is New Zealand’s proven goalkeeper. Besides, she also competes in Association football.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Florijana Ismaili (Switzerland)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In club level Florijana plays in Switzerland’s Nationalliga A. She plays both as a forward and midfielder.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Hope Solo (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Playing for her nation, Hope won the Olympic gold medal twice. She is a goalkeeper.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jessica Landstrom (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Jessica played for the Swedish national side both in the Olympics and the World cup.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Julia Simic (Germany)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Apart from playing good football Julia is also known for her modeling skills. She posed for the German edition of Playboy.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Julie Johnston (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Julie plays as a defender for Chicago Red Stars and the US national women’s soccer team.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kaylyn Kyle (Canada)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Born in Saskatoon, Kaylyn is an effective playmaker in the midfield position.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kosovare Asllani (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Swedish forward Kosovare plays club football in French Division 1 Féminine.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Toni Duggan (England)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The English winger plays as a winger for Manchester City, a top side in England.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tatiana Ariza (Colombia)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Colombian midfield maestro Tatiana is an integral part of the national team.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lara Dickenmann (Switzerland)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>A versatile footballer she is, Lara can cover both the midfield and defense.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Laure Boulleau (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>It is said that without Laure the French defense is unfulfilled. She plays for French club Paris Saint-Germain.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Adriana Leon (Canada)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Adriana came into spotlight when she was selected for the U-20 team. She is now a member of the regular team.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Louisa Necib (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Considered as one of the best playmakers in the French side, Louisa has all the potentials to be one of the greatest footballers the world has ever known.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Maria Coto (Costa Rica)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>19 years old Maria Coto is relatively new in the international stage. She is however maturing up quickly.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Melanie Leupolz (Germany)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Melanie made her presence known to the world during her appearance in the U-17 World Cup. She is primarily a midfielder.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Natalie Vinti (Mexico)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though she was born in in the states, Natalie plays for her parents’ country, Mexico, in the international stage.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Olivia Schough (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In this year’s Rio Olympics, Olivia won Silver medal for her country. She played a great role in bringing her team to the final.</h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->','30 Hottest Female Soccer Players In The World','','inherit','closed','closed','','354-revision-v1','','','2016-08-30 16:32:32','2016-08-30 16:32:32','',354,'http://feelsyoung.com/354-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(388,1,'2016-08-30 16:43:21','2016-08-30 16:43:21','<h3>In the recent years, female soccer players are rippling the world of sports with their skills and tactic; so much so that, today, they are not so far behind their male counterparts. Some of them have a glamorous presence in and outside the field.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Amanda Il