iator.png\" alt=\"The Aviator\" width=\"557\" height=\"284\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Django Unchained</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In almost every scene we see Django wearing cool sunglasses. The funny thing is, before 1929, sunglasses were only used for medical purposes.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-410\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Django-Unchained.jpg\" alt=\"Django Unchained (2012) Blu-ray Screenshot\" width=\"700\" height=\"288\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Titanic</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see Jack announcing that he and his father regularly went fishing on Lake Wissota. However, the lake was formed in 1917, five years after the Titanic sank!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-432\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Titanic.png\" alt=\"Titanic\" width=\"501\" height=\"419\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Forrest Gump</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, Forrest receives a letter of acknowledgement which dates back to 1975, when the company was yet to be publicly traded.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-411\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Forrest-Gump.jpg\" alt=\"Forrest Gump\" width=\"1000\" height=\"416\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Panic Room </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Meg lights the propane to set the intruders on fire and takes shelter under the bed. In reality, they would have been burned as well, since propane is heavier than air.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-417\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Panic-Room.png\" alt=\"Panic Room\" width=\"570\" height=\"319\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Gladiator</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, the protagonist was named ‘The Spaniard’ upon his capture. But the origin of the word didn’t come into being until 14th century. The movie was set in 180.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-412\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Gladiator.jpg\" alt=\"The Gladiator\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Back to the Future</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The license plate reads: OUTATTIME, which is way over the limit for characters in California license plates!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-408\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Back-to-the-Future.png\" alt=\"Back to the Future\" width=\"1500\" height=\"843\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Independence Day</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the Empire State Building located in the center of a street exploding in a cool way, but in reality the building is located on a corner.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-414\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Independence-Day.jpg\" alt=\"Independence Day\" width=\"666\" height=\"289\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Goonies</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the boy finding a 1973 baseball card in the dead body. The body however had been there since 1930.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-426\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Goonies.jpg\" alt=\"The Goonies\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Halloween</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The events of the movie were described as taking place in Illinois, whereas the street signs indicate that it was shot in California.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-413\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Halloween.png\" alt=\"Halloween\" width=\"644\" height=\"399\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Hurt Locker</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>One character says that the Iraqi with the video camera would post something on YouTube. But the video sharing site was not launched until 2005, whereas the events in the movie took place in 2004.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-428\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Hurt-Locker.jpg\" alt=\"The Hurt Locker\" width=\"651\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Dr. Jones as an attempt to save his father’s book visits Berlin in 1938. But, the real book burning took place in 1933.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-415\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Indiana-Jones-and-the-Last-Crusade.jpg\" alt=\"Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade\" width=\"696\" height=\"501\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Raiders of the Lost Ark</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In another Indiana Jones movie, the idol appears to be guarded by different traps. But there is a hole above which we can realize by seeing the sunlight passing through it!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-421\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Raiders-of-the-Lost-Ark.jpg\" alt=\"Raiders of the Lost Ark\" width=\"800\" height=\"451\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Malcolm X</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see Malcolm asking someone to call 911. In reality, the emergency service was introduced 3 years later after his death.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-416\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Malcolm-X.jpg\" alt=\"Malcolm X\" width=\"609\" height=\"455\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Patriot</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the character of Mel Gibson as a father of many children. The movie starts at the beginning of the Revolutionary war which ends 5 years later. But at the end of the movie we see the children as same as they were at the very beginning.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-429\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Patriot.jpg\" alt=\"The Patriot,\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Pirates of the Caribbean</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see captain Barbossa holding a Granny Smith apple, a variety which was not originated before 1868. The setting of the movie was way before that.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-419\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Pirates-of-the-Caribbean.jpg\" alt=\"Pirates of the Caribbean\" width=\"700\" height=\"302\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Public Enemies</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, the murders of Nelson and Floyd take place before that is of Dillinger’s. But in reality, both of them lived longer than Dillinger.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-420\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Public-Enemies.jpg\" alt=\"Public Enemies\" width=\"673\" height=\"540\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Saving Private Ryan</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see Captain Miller leaning against a motorcycle after being shot. But the type of motorcycle was not manufactured before 1963, which is way after the year in which the movie’s events took place.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Saving-Private-Ryan.jpg\" alt=\"Saving Private Ryan\" width=\"720\" height=\"400\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Green Mile</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, we see the execution of John Coffey taking place in Louisiana in 1935. But, the state introduced electric chair in 1940.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-427\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Green-Mile.jpg\" alt=\"The Green Mile\" width=\"638\" height=\"388\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Shawshank Redemption</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Andy Dufresne used a One Million Years B.C. poster to cover the hole he dug. He eventually made off through it in 1966. However, One Million Years B.C. was released in 1967.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-430\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Shawshank-Redemption.jpg\" alt=\"The Shawshank Redemption\" width=\"500\" height=\"639\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Sherlock Holmes</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The famous sewer chase scene starts under the parliament and ends on the top of Tower Bridge. These two places are located at a distance no less than 2 miles from each other.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-424\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Sherlock-Holmes.png\" alt=\"Sherlock Holmes\" width=\"665\" height=\"371\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Sound of Music</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Von Trapp family tries to get outside Salzburg to reach Switzerland, a neutral country during WWII. But outside Salzburg, Austria has borders with Germany, not Switzerland.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-431\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Sound-of-Music.png\" alt=\"The Sound of Music\" width=\"604\" height=\"308\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Robin’s companion Azeem gives him a telescope. The setting of the movie indicates that it was set in 1194, way before the telescope was invented by Hans Lippershey in 1608.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-422\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Robin-Hood.jpg\" alt=\"Robin Hood\" width=\"692\" height=\"389\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Pirates of the Caribbean: At World\'s End</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the events taking place in Singapore. But in reality Singapore didn’t exist then. It was founded in 1819.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-418\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Pirates-of-the-Caribbean-At-Worlds-End.jpg\" alt=\"Pirates of the Caribbean At World\'s End\" width=\"1502\" height=\"1000\" />','25 Great Movie Mistakes That We Just Can\'t Forget','','publish','open','open','','25-great-movie-mistakes-that-we-just-cant-forget','','','2016-10-06 17:29:39','2016-10-06 17:29:39','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/?p=390',0,'post','',0),(391,1,'2016-09-06 19:13:53','2016-09-06 19:13:53','<h3>In the recent years, female soccer players are rippling the world of sports with their skills and tactic; so much so that, today, they are not so far behind their male counterparts. Some of them have a glamorous presence in and outside the field.</h3>\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong>Amanda Ilestedt (Sweden)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The Swedish defender is known for her tactical skills. She plays for Damallsvenskan club FC Rosengård in the domestic arena.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-359\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Amanda-Ilestedt-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Amanda Ilestedt (Sweden)\" width=\"830\" height=\"552\" />\n\n<h2><strong>Amandine Henry (France)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The French international plays in the defensive midfield position. She won the Bronze Ball Award in a world cup.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-386\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Amandine-Henry-France-1.jpg\" alt=\"Amandine Henry (France)\" width=\"600\" height=\"814\" />\n\n<h2><strong>Angela Christ (Netherlands)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The Dutch footballer is the Netherlands’ last line of defense under the crossbar.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-361\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Angela-Christ-Netherlands.jpg\" alt=\"Angela Christ (Netherlands)\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Anna Green (New Zealand)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The kiwi defender is someone to keep an eye on. She represented her country in the Beijing Olympics.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-362\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anna-Green-New-Zealand.jpg\" alt=\"Anna Green (New Zealand)\" width=\"650\" height=\"360\" />\n\n<h2><strong>Anouk Hoogendijk (Netherlands)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Anouk Hoogendijk plays for top Dutch side Ajax. Her primary position is the midfield.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-363\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anouk-Hoogendijk-Netherlands.jpg\" alt=\"Anouk Hoogendijk (Netherlands)\" width=\"650\" height=\"487\" />\n\n<h2><strong>Christen Press (USA)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Christen was a part of the Rio Olympics team. She is famous for her athletic skills.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-364\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Christen-Press-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Christen Press (USA)\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Alex Morgan (USA)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The Portland Thorn Forward represented her country in highest levels like the Olympics and the World Cup.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-357\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alex-Morgan-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Alex Morgan (USA)\" width=\"683\" height=\"1024\" /><!--nextpage-->\n<h2> <strong>Lauren Sesselmann (Canada)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The Houston Dash defender won an Olympic bronze for her country. By the way, she was born in America.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-378\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Lauren-Sesselmann-1.jpg\" alt=\"Lauren Sesselmann\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" />\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\n<h2><strong>Daniela Cruz (Costa Rica)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Defender Daniela Cruz represents Costa Rica in the international arena.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-366\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Daniela-Cruz-Costa-Rica.jpg\" alt=\"Daniela Cruz (Costa Rica)\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Erika Cristiano dos Santos (Brazil)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Erika won silver medal for her country playing in the Beijing Olympics.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-367\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Erika-Cristiano-dos-Santos-Brazil.jpg\" alt=\"Erika Cristiano dos Santos (Brazil)\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Erin Nayler (New Zealand)</strong></h2>\n<h3>In the international level she is New Zealand’s proven goalkeeper. Besides, she also competes in Association football.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-368\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Erin-Nayler-New-Zealand.jpg\" alt=\"Erin Nayler (New Zealand)\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Florijana Ismaili (Switzerland)</strong></h2>\n<h3>In club level Florijana plays in Switzerland’s Nationalliga A. She plays both as a forward and midfielder.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-369\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Florijana-Ismaili-Switzerland.jpg\" alt=\"Florijana Ismaili (Switzerland)\" width=\"500\" height=\"763\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2> <strong>Alexia Putellas (Spain)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Playing for FC Barcelona, Alexia has already won 5 titles in total. In 2013, she scored a magnificent goal that made her famous.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-358\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alexia-Putellas.jpg\" alt=\"Alexia Putellas\" width=\"500\" height=\"294\" /><!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Hope Solo (USA)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Playing for her nation, Hope won the Olympic gold medal twice. She is a goalkeeper.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-370\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Hope-Solo-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Solo (USA)\" width=\"800\" height=\"787\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Jessica Landstrom (Sweden)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Jessica played for the Swedish national side both in the Olympics and the World cup.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-371\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Jessica-Landstrom-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Jessica Landstrom (Sweden)\" width=\"650\" height=\"843\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Julia Simic (Germany)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Apart from playing good football Julia is also known for her modeling skills. She posed for the German edition of Playboy.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-372\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Julia-Simic-Germany.jpg\" alt=\"Julia Simic (Germany)\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Julie Johnston (USA)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Julie plays as a defender for Chicago Red Stars and the US national women’s soccer team.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-373\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Julie-Johnston-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Julie Johnston (USA)\" width=\"736\" height=\"414\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Kaylyn Kyle (Canada)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Born in Saskatoon, Kaylyn is an effective playmaker in the midfield position.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-374\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Kaylyn-Kyle-Canada.jpg\" alt=\"Kaylyn Kyle (Canada)\" width=\"800\" height=\"647\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Kosovare Asllani (Sweden)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Swedish forward Kosovare plays club football in French Division 1 Féminine.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-375\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Kosovare-Asllani-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Kosovare Asllani (Sweden)\" width=\"400\" height=\"576\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Toni Duggan (England)</strong></h2>\n<h3>The English winger plays as a winger for Manchester City, a top side in England.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-385\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Toni-Duggan-England.jpg\" alt=\"Toni Duggan (England)\" width=\"736\" height=\"441\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Tatiana Ariza (Colombia)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Colombian midfield maestro Tatiana is an integral part of the national team.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-384\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Tatiana-Ariza-Colombia.jpg\" alt=\"Tatiana Ariza (Colombia)\" width=\"620\" height=\"400\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Lara Dickenmann (Switzerland)</strong></h2>\n<h3>A versatile footballer she is, Lara can cover both the midfield and defense.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-376\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Lara-Dickenmann-Switzerland.jpg\" alt=\"Lara Dickenmann (Switzerland)\" width=\"778\" height=\"937\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Laure Boulleau (France)</strong></h2>\n<h3>It is said that without Laure the French defense is unfulfilled. She plays for French club Paris Saint-Germain.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-377\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Laure-Boulleau-France.jpg\" alt=\"Laure Boulleau (France)\" width=\"700\" height=\"932\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Adriana Leon (Canada)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Adriana came into spotlight when she was selected for the U-20 team. She is now a member of the regular team.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Adriana-Leon-Canada.jpeg\" alt=\"Adriana Leon (Canada)\" width=\"500\" height=\"436\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Louisa Necib (France)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Considered as one of the best playmakers in the French side, Louisa has all the potentials to be one of the greatest footballers the world has ever known.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-379\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Louisa-Necib-France.jpg\" alt=\"Louisa Necib (France)\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Maria Coto (Costa Rica)</strong></h2>\n<h3>19 years old Maria Coto is relatively new in the international stage. She is however maturing up quickly.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-380\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Maria-Coto-Costa-Rica.jpg\" alt=\"Maria Coto (Costa Rica)\" width=\"638\" height=\"380\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Melanie Leupolz (Germany)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Melanie made her presence known to the world during her appearance in the U-17 World Cup. She is primarily a midfielder.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-381\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Melanie-Leupolz-Germany.jpg\" alt=\"Melanie Leupolz (Germany)\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Natalie Vinti (Mexico)</strong></h2>\n<h3>Though she was born in in the states, Natalie plays for her parents’ country, Mexico, in the international stage.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-382\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Natalie-Vinti-Mexico.jpg\" alt=\"Natalie Vinti (Mexico)\" width=\"600\" height=\"777\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Olivia Schough (Sweden)</strong></h2>\n<h3>In this year’s Rio Olympics, Olivia won Silver medal for her country. She played a great role in bringing her team to the final.</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-383\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Olivia-Schough.jpg\" alt=\"Olivia Schough\" width=\"650\" height=\"366\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h2><strong>Claire Lavogez (France)</strong></h2>\n21 year old Claire plays for Olympique Lyon as a midfielder. She is considered as one of the aspirant stars in the French national side.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-365\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Claire-Lavogez-France.jpg\" alt=\"Claire Lavogez (France)\" width=\"850\" height=\"565\" />','30 Hottest Female Soccer Players In The World','','inherit','closed','closed','','354-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-06 19:13:53','2016-09-06 19:13:53','',354,'http://feelsyoung.com/354-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(392,1,'2016-08-30 17:03:01','2016-08-30 17:03:01','<h3>In the recent years, female soccer players are rippling the world of sports with their skills and tactic; so much so that, today, they are not so far behind their male counterparts. Some of them have a glamorous presence in and outside the field.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Amanda Ilestedt (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Swedish defender is known for her tactical skills. She plays for Damallsvenskan club FC Rosengård in the domestic arena.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-359\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Amanda-Ilestedt-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Amanda Ilestedt (Sweden)\" width=\"830\" height=\"552\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Amandine Henry (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The French international plays in the defensive midfield position. She won the Bronze Ball Award in a world cup.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-386\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Amandine-Henry-France-1.jpg\" alt=\"Amandine Henry (France)\" width=\"600\" height=\"814\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Angela Christ (Netherlands)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Dutch footballer is the Netherlands’ last line of defense under the crossbar.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-361\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Angela-Christ-Netherlands.jpg\" alt=\"Angela Christ (Netherlands)\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anna Green (New Zealand)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The kiwi defender is someone to keep an eye on. She represented her country in the Beijing Olympics.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-362\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anna-Green-New-Zealand.jpg\" alt=\"Anna Green (New Zealand)\" width=\"650\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anouk Hoogendijk (Netherlands)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Anouk Hoogendijk plays for top Dutch side Ajax. Her primary position is the midfield.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-363\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anouk-Hoogendijk-Netherlands.jpg\" alt=\"Anouk Hoogendijk (Netherlands)\" width=\"650\" height=\"487\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Christen Press (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Christen was a part of the Rio Olympics team. She is famous for her athletic skills.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-364\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Christen-Press-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Christen Press (USA)\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Alex Morgan (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Portland Thorn Forward represented her country in highest levels like the Olympics and the World Cup.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-357\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alex-Morgan-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Alex Morgan (USA)\" width=\"683\" height=\"1024\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2> <strong>Lauren Sesselmann (Canada)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Houston Dash defender won an Olympic bronze for her country. By the way, she was born in America.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-378\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Lauren-Sesselmann-1.jpg\" alt=\"Lauren Sesselmann\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Daniela Cruz (Costa Rica)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Defender Daniela Cruz represents Costa Rica in the international arena.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-366\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Daniela-Cruz-Costa-Rica.jpg\" alt=\"Daniela Cruz (Costa Rica)\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Erika Cristiano dos Santos (Brazil)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Erika won silver medal for her country playing in the Beijing Olympics.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-367\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Erika-Cristiano-dos-Santos-Brazil.jpg\" alt=\"Erika Cristiano dos Santos (Brazil)\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Erin Nayler (New Zealand)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the international level she is New Zealand’s proven goalkeeper. Besides, she also competes in Association football.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-368\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Erin-Nayler-New-Zealand.jpg\" alt=\"Erin Nayler (New Zealand)\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Florijana Ismaili (Switzerland)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In club level Florijana plays in Switzerland’s Nationalliga A. She plays both as a forward and midfielder.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-369\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Florijana-Ismaili-Switzerland.jpg\" alt=\"Florijana Ismaili (Switzerland)\" width=\"500\" height=\"763\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2> <strong>Alexia Putellas (Spain)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Playing for FC Barcelona, Alexia has already won 5 titles in total. In 2013, she scored a magnificent goal that made her famous.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-358\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alexia-Putellas.jpg\" alt=\"Alexia Putellas\" width=\"500\" height=\"294\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Hope Solo (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Playing for her nation, Hope won the Olympic gold medal twice. She is a goalkeeper.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-370\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Hope-Solo-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Solo (USA)\" width=\"800\" height=\"787\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jessica Landstrom (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Jessica played for the Swedish national side both in the Olympics and the World cup.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-371\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Jessica-Landstrom-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Jessica Landstrom (Sweden)\" width=\"650\" height=\"843\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Julia Simic (Germany)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Apart from playing good football Julia is also known for her modeling skills. She posed for the German edition of Playboy.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-372\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Julia-Simic-Germany.jpg\" alt=\"Julia Simic (Germany)\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Julie Johnston (USA)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Julie plays as a defender for Chicago Red Stars and the US national women’s soccer team.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-373\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Julie-Johnston-USA.jpg\" alt=\"Julie Johnston (USA)\" width=\"736\" height=\"414\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kaylyn Kyle (Canada)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Born in Saskatoon, Kaylyn is an effective playmaker in the midfield position.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-374\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Kaylyn-Kyle-Canada.jpg\" alt=\"Kaylyn Kyle (Canada)\" width=\"800\" height=\"647\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kosovare Asllani (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Swedish forward Kosovare plays club football in French Division 1 Féminine.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-375\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Kosovare-Asllani-Sweden.jpg\" alt=\"Kosovare Asllani (Sweden)\" width=\"400\" height=\"576\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Toni Duggan (England)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The English winger plays as a winger for Manchester City, a top side in England.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-385\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Toni-Duggan-England.jpg\" alt=\"Toni Duggan (England)\" width=\"736\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tatiana Ariza (Colombia)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Colombian midfield maestro Tatiana is an integral part of the national team.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-384\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Tatiana-Ariza-Colombia.jpg\" alt=\"Tatiana Ariza (Colombia)\" width=\"620\" height=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lara Dickenmann (Switzerland)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>A versatile footballer she is, Lara can cover both the midfield and defense.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-376\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Lara-Dickenmann-Switzerland.jpg\" alt=\"Lara Dickenmann (Switzerland)\" width=\"778\" height=\"937\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Laure Boulleau (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>It is said that without Laure the French defense is unfulfilled. She plays for French club Paris Saint-Germain.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-377\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Laure-Boulleau-France.jpg\" alt=\"Laure Boulleau (France)\" width=\"700\" height=\"932\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Adriana Leon (Canada)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Adriana came into spotlight when she was selected for the U-20 team. She is now a member of the regular team.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Adriana-Leon-Canada.jpeg\" alt=\"Adriana Leon (Canada)\" width=\"500\" height=\"436\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Louisa Necib (France)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Considered as one of the best playmakers in the French side, Louisa has all the potentials to be one of the greatest footballers the world has ever known.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-379\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Louisa-Necib-France.jpg\" alt=\"Louisa Necib (France)\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Maria Coto (Costa Rica)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>19 years old Maria Coto is relatively new in the international stage. She is however maturing up quickly.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-380\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Maria-Coto-Costa-Rica.jpg\" alt=\"Maria Coto (Costa Rica)\" width=\"638\" height=\"380\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Melanie Leupolz (Germany)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Melanie made her presence known to the world during her appearance in the U-17 World Cup. She is primarily a midfielder.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-381\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Melanie-Leupolz-Germany.jpg\" alt=\"Melanie Leupolz (Germany)\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Natalie Vinti (Mexico)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though she was born in in the states, Natalie plays for her parents’ country, Mexico, in the international stage.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-382\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Natalie-Vinti-Mexico.jpg\" alt=\"Natalie Vinti (Mexico)\" width=\"600\" height=\"777\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Olivia Schough (Sweden)</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In this year’s Rio Olympics, Olivia won Silver medal for her country. She played a great role in bringing her team to the final.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-383\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Olivia-Schough.jpg\" alt=\"Olivia Schough\" width=\"650\" height=\"366\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Claire Lavogez (France)</strong></h2>\r\n21 year old Claire plays for Olympique Lyon as a midfielder. She is considered as one of the aspirant stars in the French national side.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-365\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Claire-Lavogez-France.jpg\" alt=\"Claire Lavogez (France)\" width=\"850\" height=\"565\" />','30 Hottest Female Soccer Players In The World','','inherit','closed','closed','','354-revision-v1','','','2016-08-30 17:03:01','2016-08-30 17:03:01','',354,'http://feelsyoung.com/354-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(393,1,'2016-08-30 17:14:18','2016-08-30 17:14:18','<h3>Making a movie is not like just another task. It takes sheer devotion and toil of those who are involved. The process of making a movie goes through an intense examination to make the finished product as accurate as possible. Some mistakes however remain till the end, and don’t get noticed until someone points them out. Exactly that’s what we did!</h3>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Braveheart</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see the hero, William Wallace wearing kilts throughout the movie. But the thing is, kilts were not used in Scotland before 16th century, which is way later Wallace’s time. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Aviator</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>The movie was set in 1928. We see the protagonist ordering chocolate chip cookies in a scene, when in reality, the confectionery was not invented before 1930.  \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Django Unchained</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>In almost every scene we see Django wearing cool sunglasses. The funny thing is, before 1929, sunglasses were only used for medical purposes. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Titanic</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see Jack announcing that he and his father regularly went fishing on Lake Wissota. However, the lake was formed in 1917, five years after the Titanic sank!    \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Forrest Gump</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>In the movie, Forrest receives a letter of acknowledgement which dates back to 1975, when the company was yet to be publicly traded. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Panic Room </strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Meg lights the propane to set the intruders on fire and takes shelter under the bed. In reality, they would have been burned as well, since propane is heavier than air.\r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Gladiator</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>In the movie, the protagonist was named ‘The Spaniard’ upon his capture. But the origin of the word didn’t come into being until 14th century. The movie was set in 180. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Back to the Future</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>The license plate reads: OUTATTIME, which is way over the limit for characters in California license plates! \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Independence Day</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see the Empire State Building located in the center of a street exploding in a cool way, but in reality the building is located on a corner.\r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Goonies</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see the boy finding a 1973 baseball card in the dead body. The body however had been there since 1930.\r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Halloween</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>The events of the movie were described as taking place in Illinois, whereas the street signs indicate that it was shot in California. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Hurt Locker</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>One character says that the Iraqi with the video camera would post something on YouTube. But the video sharing site was not launched until 2005, whereas the events in the movie took place in 2004. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dr. Jones as an attempt to save his father’s book visits Berlin in 1938. But, the real book burning took place in 1933.\r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Raiders of the Lost Ark</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>In another Indiana Jones movie, the idol appears to be guarded by different traps. But there is a hole above which we can realize by seeing the sunlight passing through it! \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Malcolm X</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see Malcolm asking someone to call 911. In reality, the emergency service was introduced 3 years later after his death.\r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Patriot</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see the character of Mel Gibson as a father of many children. The movie starts at the beginning of the Revolutionary war which ends 5 years later. But at the end of the movie we see the children as same as they were at the very beginning. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Pirates of the Caribbean</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see captain Barbossa holding a Granny Smith apple, a variety which was not originated before 1868. The setting of the movie was way before that.  \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Public Enemies</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>In the movie, the murders of Nelson and Floyd take place before that is of Dillinger’s. But in reality, both of them lived longer than Dillinger. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Saving Private Ryan</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>We see Captain Miller leaning against a motorcycle after being shot. But the type of motorcycle was not manufactured before 1963, which is way after the year in which the movie’s events took place.  \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>\r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Green Mile</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>In the movie, we see the execution of John Coffey taking place in Louisiana in 1935. But, the state introduced electric chair in 1940. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Shawshank Redemption</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Andy Dufresne used a One Million Years B.C. poster to cover the hole he dug. He eventually made off through it in 1966. However, One Million Years B.C. was released in 1967. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Sherlock Holmes</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>The famous sewer chase scene starts under the parliament and ends on the top of Tower Bridge. These two places are located at a distance no less than 2 miles from each other. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The Sound of Music</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Von Trapp family tries to get outside Salzburg to reach Switzerland, a neutral country during WWII. But outside Salzburg, Austria has borders with Germany, not Switzerland. \r\n\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Robin’s companion Azeem gives him a telescope. The setting of the movie indicates that it was set in 1194, way before the telescope was invented by Hans Lippershey in 1608. \r\n\r\n</h3>','25 Great Movie Mistakes That We Just Can\'t Forget','','inherit','closed','closed','','390-revision-v1','','','2016-08-30 17:14:18','2016-08-30 17:14:18','',390,'http://feelsyoung.com/390-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(408,1,'2016-08-30 17:26:29','2016-08-30 17:26:29','','Back to the Future','','inherit','open','closed','','back-to-the-future','','','2016-08-30 17:26:29','2016-08-30 17:26:29','',390,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Back-to-the-Future.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(409,1,'2016-08-30 17:26:33','2016-08-30 17:26:33','','Braveheart','','inherit','open','closed','','braveheart','','','2016-08-30 17:26:33','2016-08-30 17:26:33','',390,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Braveheart.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(410,1,'2016-08-30 17:26:34','2016-08-30 17:26:34','','Django Unchained (2012) Blu-ray Screenshot','','inherit','open','closed','','django-unchained-2012-blu-ray-screenshot','','','2016-08-30 17:27:59','2016-08-30 17:27:59','',390,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Django-Unchained.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(411,1,'2016-08-30 17:26:35','2016-08-30 17:26:35','','Forrest Gump','','inherit','open','closed','','forrest-gump','','','2016-08-30 17:26:35','2016-08-30 17:26:35','',390,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Forrest-Gump.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(412,1,'2016-08-30 17:26:37