n warships are developed in such a way that they can change the course of any war in no time. We gather here 28 most advanced warships that can win a naval conflict from nothing.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>HMCS Chicoutimi</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The diesel powered submarine is owned by the Royal Canadian Navy. It has 6 submarine tubes, along with a very effective decoy system.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-496\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/HMCS-Chicoutimi.jpg\" alt=\"HMCS Chicoutimi\" width=\"728\" height=\"481\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>HDMS Absalon</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>One of the most sophisticated warships ever built, HDMS Absalon is used by the Royal Danish Navy. It is equipped with 7 heavy machineguns. Two helicopters can land on it at the same time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-494\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/HDMS-Absalon.jpg\" alt=\"HDMS Absalon\" width=\"728\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>SAS Mendi</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Despite its heavy weight, the frigate has a marvelous speed of 30 knots. It has multiple radar systems to detect any upcoming enemies.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-504\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/SAS-Mendi.jpg\" alt=\"SAS Mendi\" width=\"728\" height=\"485\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>JDS Hyuga</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>To counter Pyongyang’s bigger fleet, this ship was included in the Japanese Maritime Self-defense force about 7 years ago.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-502\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/JDS-Hyuga.jpg\" alt=\"JDS Hyuga\" width=\"728\" height=\"406\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>TCG Heybeliada</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though it is not a proper warship, it has advanced features like anti-aircraft system. The patrol vessel is known for its stealth capability.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-506\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/TCG-Heybeliada.jpg\" alt=\"TCG Heybeliada\" width=\"728\" height=\"403\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>BNS Riachuelo</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The 75 feet long submarine is one of the stealthiest in the world. It is run by electric power, and has 6 torpedo tubes.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-489\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/BNS-Riachuelo.jpg\" alt=\"BNS Riachuelo\" width=\"728\" height=\"484\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>INS Vishal</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The aircraft carrier will be added to the Indian Navy’s fleet in 2023. It can accommodate 1,400 crew members.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-501\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/INS-Vishal.jpg\" alt=\"INS Vishal\" width=\"728\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>HMS Agamemnon</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The submarine is built keeping in mind a whale’s shape. It can store 3 months’ worth supply. The submarine will be added to the British Navy in 2020.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-497\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/HMS-Agamemnon.jpg\" alt=\"HMS Agamemnon\" width=\"706\" height=\"530\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>HMAS Canberra</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The warship has a sophisticated radar and weapon system. It has a superior missile system that can deflect missiles. 18 helicopters can land on this ship.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-495\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/HMAS-Canberra.jpg\" alt=\"HMAS Canberra\" width=\"728\" height=\"416\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>CNS Linyi</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>One of the most sophisticated ships owned by the Chinese Navy, the CNS Linyi has anti-submarine capability. It can jam any incoming missiles. It can carry both aircrafts and helicopters.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-491\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CNS-Linyi.jpg\" alt=\"CNS Linyi\" width=\"728\" height=\"486\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>CNS Kunming</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The PLA Navy’s ship is aimed at countering piracy and other subversive activities. It has 6 torpedo tubes.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-490\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CNS-Kunming.jpg\" alt=\"CNS Kunming\" width=\"706\" height=\"530\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>INS Makar\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Indian Navy uses this vessel to survey coast. It can also be used as a rescue vessel.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-500\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/INS-Makar.jpg\" alt=\"INS Makar\" width=\"728\" height=\"485\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>French Frigate Forbin\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The sophisticated PAAM radar system made it an effective savior of other ships and aircraft carriers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-493\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/French-Frigate-Forbin.jpg\" alt=\"French Frigate Forbin\" width=\"728\" height=\"486\" />\r\n<h2><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Dixmude\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>This assault ship used by the French navy can do wonders. Apart from its helicopter carrying capability, it can also accommodate one tank and many other vehicles.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-492\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Dixmude.jpg\" alt=\"Dixmude\" width=\"728\" height=\"485\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Russian Corvette Boiky\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>A light ship in nature, this corvette weighs only 2,100 tons. It has two torpedo tubes that can neutralize submarines.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-503\" src=\"ht