"350\" height=\"228\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>6. Try to avoid anything made of sugar during lunch hour or anytime of the day. Sugar highs and lows impact your brain negatively and thwart its regular capability.\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-638\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/6-3.jpg\" alt=\"6\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>7. Don’t visit social media or meme sites more than twice a day. When you indulge in something that switches fast, your brain also gets adjusted to it and later results in difficulty concentrating.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-639\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/7-2.jpg\" alt=\"7\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>8. Gaming is a better choice than watching TV shows or movies. When you do the latter, your brain keeps taking input but doesn’t produce anything in return. On the other hand, gaming works as an exercise for your brain through interaction and processing.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-640\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/8-2.jpg\" alt=\"8\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>9. Similarly, reading a book is preferable to watching TV. While reading a book your brain works to prepare a mental image of the descriptions you have been reading.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-641\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/9.jpeg\" alt=\"9\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>10. Learning a little bit programming won’t do any harm. Programming helps you to think logically and rationally. Don’t fret. There are many free websites that offer programming lessons for beginners.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-642\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/10-3.jpg\" alt=\"10\" width=\"500\" height=\"358\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>11. It’s not a problem if you are not that into hard exercises. Instead of hitting the gym you can do some simple exercises to reap the most benefits.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-643\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/11-2.jpg\" alt=\"11\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>12. Passing time with people who are smarter than you can help see the world from a new angle. Remember, knowingly or unknowingly, you are influenced by those with whom you spend time.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-644\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/12-2.jpg\" alt=\"12\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>13. Try to get into friendly conversation with people who don’t agree with you. It will sharpen your ability to argument in a gentle way. And, you will be able to get rid of misconceptions that you were nurturing previously.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-645\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/13-1.jpg\" alt=\"13\" width=\"450\" height=\"270\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>14. Every day make time for walk through places where trees are aplenty. As a result your mind will calm down and bodily blood circulation will improve.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-646\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/14-2.jpg\" alt=\"14\" width=\"558\" height=\"364\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>15. Always keep a notepad with you and note down anything interesting or curious that come down your way. Working on them later will improve your logical thinking.</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-647\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/15-2.jpg\" alt=\"15\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>16. Every day take 10 minutes before you go to sleep to plan what’s to be done the next 