/08/Ally-Sheedy.jpg\" alt=\"Ally Sheedy\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Judd Nelson </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Judd set his mark with “The Breakfast Club”. Prior to that, he acted in Nikita.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-453\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Judd-Nelson.jpg\" alt=\"Judd Nelson\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Molly Ringwald</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The charming redhead gained fame for her role in “Sixteen Candles”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-459\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Molly-Ringwald.jpg\" alt=\"Molly Ringwald\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Andrew McCarthy</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Andrew got himself another contract with hit Brat Pack lineup in “Pretty in Pink”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-442\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Andrew-McCarthy.jpg\" alt=\"Andrew McCarthy\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Emilio Estevez</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>You might not know but Emilio is actor Charlie Sheen’s elder brother. He worked with stars like Sean Penn, during the 80’s.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-449\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Emilio-Estevez.jpg\" alt=\"Emilio Estevez\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Madonna</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>If you ask an 80’s kid about his or her music preference, they are most likely to answer: Madonna.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-455\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Madonna.jpg\" alt=\"Madonna\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anthony Michael Hall</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Anthony got spotlight after appearing in hit comedy “National Lampoon’s Vacation”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-443\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Anthony-Michael-Hall.jpg\" alt=\"Anthony Michael Hall\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>George Michael</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>People still remember the English singer for hit tracks like Careless Whisper and Last Christmas.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-450\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/George-Michael.jpg\" alt=\"George Michael\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Demi Moore</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Leaving behind her disappointment in school, Moore established herself as one of the most desirable actresses in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-447\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Demi-Moore.jpg\" alt=\"Demi Moore\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>John Cusack</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Cusack entered the world of showbiz with his enthralling performance in “Better Off Dead”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-452\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/John-Cusack.jpg\" alt=\"John Cusack\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Alyssa Milano</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Alyssa got breakthrough with her performance in ABC sitcom “Who\'s the Boss?”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-441\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Alyssa-Milano.jpg\" alt=\"Alyssa Milano\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tom Cruise</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Cruise is still one of the big shots in Hollywood. Many of us don’t know that Cruise began his career with a minor role in the movie “The Outsiders”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-464\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Tom-Cruise.jpg\" alt=\"Tom Cruise\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Rob Lowe</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Rob was also a part of “The Outsiders” cast along with Tom Cruise. He also appeared in Brat Pack.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Rob-Lowe.jpg\" alt=\"Rob Lowe\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Cyndi Lauper</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Her first album “She\'s So Unusual” was released in 1983. She eventually established herself as the pop sensation of the decade.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-445\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Cyndi-Lauper.jpg\" alt=\"Cyndi Lauper\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kevin Bacon</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He became a household name after playing the character of Ren McCormack. Even today he is a regular face in Hollywood movies.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-454\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Kevin-Bacon.jpg\" alt=\"Kevin Bacon\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Patrick Dempsey</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The actor became audience favorite after playing a nerdy character in “Can’t Buy Me Love”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-461\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Patrick-Dempsey.jpg\" alt=\"Patrick Dempsey\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Matthew Broderick</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Matthew set his footprint with his acting in “Ferris Bueller\'s Day Off”. He eventually made it to some of the biggest hits in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-457\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Matthew-Broderick.jpg\" alt=\"Matthew Broderick\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Matt Dillon</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Bad boy Matt Dillon took part in many 80’s flicks. He was one of the heartthrobs of the decade.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-456\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Matt-Dillon.jpg\" alt=\"Matt Dillon\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Michael J. Fox</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Canadian Michael J. Fox became known for his acting skills with his role in “Family Ties”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-458\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Michael-J.-Fox.jpg\" alt=\"Michael J. Fox\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mr. T</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Anyone who grew up during the 80’s will go WOW if you asked them about “The A-Team”. Indeed the name Mr. T became synonymous with the hit show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-460\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Mr.-T.jpg\" alt=\"Mr. T\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Corey Feldman</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Corey commenced his acting career when he was just 3. He became popular for his performance in “The Goonies”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-444\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Corey-Feldman.jpg\" alt=\"Corey Feldman\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Drew Barrymore</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Successful Hollywood actress Drew Barrymore appeared on television when she was just 11! Her first breakthrough came with E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-448\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Drew-Barrymore.jpg\" alt=\"Drew Barrymore\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Debbie Gibson</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Her hit single Foolish Beat hit the top of the Billboard soon after it was released; making her one of the youngest artists to achieve that feat.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-446\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Debbie-Gibson.jpg\" alt=\"Debbie Gibson\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />','See How These Stars From The 80’s Aged UP','','inherit','closed','closed','','438-autosave-v1','','','2017-01-23 12:01:45','2017-01-23 12:01:45','',438,'http://feelsyoung.com/438-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(712,1,'2016-10-06 17:17:00','2016-10-06 17:17:00','<h3>They were once our favorite stars and were the most familiar faces on TV. Those who were children during the 80’s, still allot a special place to these stars. We, however, don’t see them as frequently as before. What happened to them? Some of them left the world of showbiz and now, spending their time in retirement. And the others are still dominating the sliver screen, as they did before.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Ricky Schroder</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When he was just 12, he played the lead role in the famous TV show Silver Spoons.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-462\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Ricky-Schroder.jpg\" alt=\"Ricky Schroder\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ally Sheedy</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Brat Pack star began her journey with the 1983 hit: Bad Boys.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-440\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Ally-Sheedy.jpg\" alt=\"Ally Sheedy\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Judd Nelson </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Judd set his mark with “The Breakfast Club”. Prior to that, he acted in Nikita.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-453\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Judd-Nelson.jpg\" alt=\"Judd Nelson\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Molly Ringwald</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The charming redhead gained fame for her role in “Sixteen Candles”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-459\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/upl