ight=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kevin Bacon</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He became a household name after playing the character of Ren McCormack. Even today he is a regular face in Hollywood movies.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-454\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Kevin-Bacon.jpg\" alt=\"Kevin Bacon\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Patrick Dempsey</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The actor became audience favorite after playing a nerdy character in “Can’t Buy Me Love”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-461\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Patrick-Dempsey.jpg\" alt=\"Patrick Dempsey\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Matthew Broderick</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Matthew set his footprint with his acting in “Ferris Bueller\'s Day Off”. He eventually made it to some of the biggest hits in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-457\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Matthew-Broderick.jpg\" alt=\"Matthew Broderick\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Matt Dillon</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Bad boy Matt Dillon took part in many 80’s flicks. He was one of the heartthrobs of the decade.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-456\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Matt-Dillon.jpg\" alt=\"Matt Dillon\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Michael J. Fox</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Canadian Michael J. Fox became known for his acting skills with his role in “Family Ties”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-458\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Michael-J.-Fox.jpg\" alt=\"Michael J. Fox\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mr. T</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Anyone who grew up during the 80’s will go WOW if you asked them about “The A-Team”. Indeed the name Mr. T became synonymous with the hit show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-460\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Mr.-T.jpg\" alt=\"Mr. T\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Corey Feldman</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Corey commenced his acting career when he was just 3. He became popular for his performance in “The Goonies”.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-444\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Corey-Feldman.jpg\" alt=\"Corey Feldman\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Drew Barrymore</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Successful Hollywood actress Drew Barrymore appeared on television when she was just 11! Her first breakthrough came with E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-448\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Drew-Barrymore.jpg\" alt=\"Drew Barrymore\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Debbie Gibson</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Her hit single Foolish Beat hit the top of the Billboard soon after it was released; making her one of the youngest artists to achieve that feat.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-446\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Debbie-Gibson.jpg\" alt=\"Debbie Gibson\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />','See How These Stars From The 80’s Aged UP','','inherit','closed','closed','','438-revision-v1','','','2016-10-06 17:17:00','2016-10-06 17:17:00','',438,'http://feelsyoung.com/438-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(713,1,'2016-10-06 17:29:39','2016-10-06 17:29:39','<h3>Making a movie is not like just another task. It takes sheer devotion and toil of those who are involved. The process of making a movie goes through an intense examination to make the finished product as accurate as possible. Some mistakes however remain till the end, and don’t get noticed until someone points them out. Exactly that’s what we did!</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Braveheart</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the hero, William Wallace wearing kilts throughout the movie. But the thing is, kilts were not used in Scotland before 16th century, which is way later Wallace’s time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-409\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Braveheart.jpg\" alt=\"Braveheart\" width=\"600\" height=\"337\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Aviator</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The movie was set in 1928. We see the protagonist ordering chocolate chip cookies in a scene, when in reality, the confectionery was not invented before 1930.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-425\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Aviator.png\" alt=\"The Aviator\" width=\"557\" height=\"284\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Django Unchained</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In almost every scene we see Django wearing cool sunglasses. The funny thing is, before 1929, sunglasses were only used for medical purposes.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-410\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Django-Unchained.jpg\" alt=\"Django Unchained (2012) Blu-ray Screenshot\" width=\"700\" height=\"288\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Titanic</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see Jack announcing that he and his father regularly went fishing on Lake Wissota. However, the lake was formed in 1917, five years after the Titanic sank!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-432\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Titanic.png\" alt=\"Titanic\" width=\"501\" height=\"419\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Forrest Gump</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, Forrest receives a letter of acknowledgement which dates back to 1975, when the company was yet to be publicly traded.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-411\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Forrest-Gump.jpg\" alt=\"Forrest Gump\" width=\"1000\" height=\"416\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Panic Room </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Meg lights the propane to set the intruders on fire and takes shelter under the bed. In reality, they would have been burned as well, since propane is heavier than air.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-417\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Panic-Room.png\" alt=\"Panic Room\" width=\"570\" height=\"319\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Gladiator</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, the protagonist was named ‘The Spaniard’ upon his capture. But the origin of the word didn’t come into being until 14th century. The movie was set in 180.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-412\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Gladiator.jpg\" alt=\"The Gladiator\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Back to the Future</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The license plate reads: OUTATTIME, which is way over the limit for characters in California license plates!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-408\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Back-to-the-Future.png\" alt=\"Back to the Future\" width=\"1500\" height=\"843\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Independence Day</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the Empire State Building located in the center of a street exploding in a cool way, but in reality the building is located on a corner.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-414\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Independence-Day.jpg\" alt=\"Independence Day\" width=\"666\" height=\"289\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Goonies</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the boy finding a 1973 baseball card in the dead body. The body however had been there since 1930.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-426\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Goonies.jpg\" alt=\"The Goonies\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Halloween</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The events of the movie were described as taking place in Illinois, whereas the street signs indicate that it was shot in California.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-413\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Halloween.png\" alt=\"Halloween\" width=\"644\" height=\"399\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Hurt Locker</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>One character says that the Iraqi with the video camera would post something on YouTube. But the video sharing site was not launched until 2005, whereas the events in the movie took place in 2004.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-428\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Hurt-Locker.jpg\" alt=\"The Hurt Locker\" width=\"651\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Dr. Jones as an attempt to save his father’s book visits Berlin in 1938. But, the real book burning took place in 1933.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-415\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Indiana-Jones-and-the-Last-Crusade.jpg\" alt=\"Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade\" width=\"696\" height=\"501\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Raiders of the Lost Ark</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In another Indiana Jones movie, the idol appears to be guarded by different traps. But there is a hole above which we can realize by seeing the sunlight passing through it!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-421\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Raiders-of-the-Lost-Ark.jpg\" alt=\"Raiders of the Lost Ark\" width=\"800\" height=\"451\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Malcolm X</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see Malcolm asking someone to call 911. In reality, the emergency service was introduced 3 years later after his death.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-416\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Malcolm-X.jpg\" alt=\"Malcolm X\" width=\"609\" height=\"455\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Patriot</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the character of Mel Gibson as a father of many children. The movie starts at the beginning of the Revolutionary war which ends 5 years later. But at the end of the movie we see the children as same as they were at the very beginning.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-429\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Patriot.jpg\" alt=\"The Patriot,\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Pirates of the Caribbean</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see captain Barbossa holding a Granny Smith apple, a variety which was not originated before 1868. The setting of the movie was way before that.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-419\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Pirates-of-the-Caribbean.jpg\" alt=\"Pirates of the Caribbean\" width=\"700\" height=\"302\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Public Enemies</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, the murders of Nelson and Floyd take place before that is of Dillinger’s. But in reality, both of them lived longer than Dillinger.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-420\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Public-Enemies.jpg\" alt=\"Public Enemies\" width=\"673\" height=\"540\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Saving Private Ryan</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see Captain Miller leaning against a motorcycle after being shot. But the type of motorcycle was not manufactured before 1963, which is way after the year in which the movie’s events took place.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Saving-Private-Ryan.jpg\" alt=\"Saving Private Ryan\" width=\"720\" height=\"400\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Green Mile</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the movie, we see the execution of John Coffey taking place in Louisiana in 1935. But, the state introduced electric chair in 1940.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-427\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Green-Mile.jpg\" alt=\"The Green Mile\" width=\"638\" height=\"388\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Shawshank Redemption</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Andy Dufresne used a One Million Years B.C. poster to cover the hole he dug. He eventually made off through it in 1966. However, One Million Years B.C. was released in 1967.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-430\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Shawshank-Redemption.jpg\" alt=\"The Shawshank Redemption\" width=\"500\" height=\"639\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Sherlock Holmes</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The famous sewer chase scene starts under the parliament and ends on the top of Tower Bridge. These two places are located at a distance no less than 2 miles from each other.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-424\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Sherlock-Holmes.png\" alt=\"Sherlock Holmes\" width=\"665\" height=\"371\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Sound of Music</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Von Trapp family tries to get outside Salzburg to reach Switzerland, a neutral country during WWII. But outside Salzburg, Austria has borders with Germany, not Switzerland.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-431\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-Sound-of-Music.png\" alt=\"The Sound of Music\" width=\"604\" height=\"308\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Robin’s companion Azeem gives him a telescope. The setting of the movie indicates that it was set in 1194, way before the telescope was invented by Hans Lippershey in 1608.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-422\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Robin-Hood.jpg\" alt=\"Robin Hood\" width=\"692\" height=\"389\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Pirates of the Caribbean: At World\'s End</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We see the events taking place in Singapore. But in reality Singapore didn’t exist then. It was founded in 1819.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-418\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Pirates-of-the-Caribbean-At-Worlds-End.jpg\" alt=\"Pirates of the Caribbean At World\'s End\" width=\"1502\" height=\"1000\" />','25 Great Movie Mistakes That We Just Can\'t Forget','','inherit','closed','closed','','390-revision-v1','','','2016-10-06 17:29:39','2016-10-06 17:29:39','',390,'http://feelsyoung.com/390-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(714,1,'2016-10-06 17:42:06','2016-10-06 17:42:06','<h3>Maybe you are at the turning point of life where you have started feeling the vibe of hitting the 35 year mark. This is considered as the time of life where you need to settle down. So, a change in everything is inevitable. Every age has its pros and cons. If you are a middle-aged woman, you should avoid wearing a few things that would not suit your personality and look, as they did before.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>25. Costume Shoes</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>We all gave up to our urge to get a pair of costume shoes one time or another. But if you are around 40, you should not be wearing those for comfortability’s sake.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-346\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Costume-shoes.jpg\" alt=\"Costume shoes\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>24. Bedazzled Anything</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The bedazzled trend began about 16 years ago. Now it is considered as one of the biggest fashion flops. Unless you are in your early teen, you should not be trying them.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-333\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Bedazzled-anything.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>23. Blue Eyeshadow</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>To be honest, no matter how old are you, you should avoid wearing them for good.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-344\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Blue-Eyeshadow.jpg\" alt=\"Blue Eyeshadow\" width=\"440\" height=\"329\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>22. Victoria\'s Secret PINK</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Pink is something predetermined for teens. Don’t harass yourself when you are in your 30s.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-330\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/21.-Victorias-Secret-PINK.jpg\" alt=\"Victoria\'s Pink\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>21. Leopard Print</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Unless you want to do something extraordinary, you should reconsider your decision. At the end of the day nobody wants to end up getting a title what they are not.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-329\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/20.-Leopard-Print.jpg\" alt=\"20. Leopard Print\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>20. Sparkly Pants</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Don’t make your pants a place to compete with the sun; believe me, they look worse than you can imagine.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-328\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/19.-Sparkly-Pants.jpg\" alt=\"19. Sparkly Pants\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>19. Oversized Sunglasses </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>This is one of those things allotted for young people, only. Unless you don’t care about your personality, you should give them up for good.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-327\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/18.-Oversized-Sunglasses.jpg\" alt=\"18. Oversized Sunglasses\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>18. Crop Tops &amp; Hotpants</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When you are more than fit, you can flaunt that beautiful body of yours. But, you should not be wearing crop tops and hotpants at an age when a fat belly can distract others and be a mismatch for your personality.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-335\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/crop-tops-and-hotpants.jpg\" alt=\"crop tops and hotpants\" width=\"500\" height=\"466\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>17. Non-matching Socks</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Your socks often say who you are. Be careful about that.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-326\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/17.-Non-matching-Socks.jpg\" alt=\"17. Non-matching Socks\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>16. Hoop Earrings</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>They are more suitable for girls who are attending high school. Get yourself some mature stuff.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-325\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/16.-Hoop-Earrings.jpg\" alt=\"16. Hoop Earrings\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>15. Furry Boots</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>“Only for teenagers” – doesn’t that say it all! You would regret wearing them.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-324\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/15.-Furry-Boots.jpg\" alt=\"15. Furry Boots\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>14. Furry Anything</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Anything furry has never been a great choice to look age appropriate. They will just add up to your misery!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-323\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/14.-Furry-Anything.jpg\" alt=\"14. Furry Anything\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>13. Tube Tops</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Cameron Diaz recently announced that she is not going to wear them anymore. So, why do you bother?</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-348\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Tube-Tops.jpg\" alt=\"Tube Tops\" width=\"400\" height=\"533\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>12. Short Dresses</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>You have other ways to look sexy. Don’t bare it all to attract people.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-321\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/12.-Short-Dresses.jpg\" alt=\"12. Short Dresses\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>11. Mini-Skirts</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>“Know thyself”. Remember, you can’t always mix it up.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-320\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/11.-Mini-Skirts.jpg\" alt=\"11. Mini-Skirts\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>10. Woman Overalls</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Do you work at a farm? If not, help yourself.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-351\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Woman-Overalls.jpg\" alt=\"Woman Overalls\" width=\"570\" height=\"570\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>9. Anything Showing Excessive Cleavage</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>A mature woman should never flaunt too much. It makes her look vulnerable and helpless.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-337\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Showing-Excessive-Cleavage.jpg\" alt=\"Showing Excessive Cleavage\" width=\"600\" height=\"330\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>8. American Eagle</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>They have cool, fitting jeans. But they are no longer for you.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-349\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/w926-ae-american-eagle-skinny-dark-wash-jeans-size-0-short-womens-jeans-815d30d5689245458a25f910b1e30c84.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"471\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>7. Booty Shorts</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>To be honest, I am yet to find out at what age you can wear them!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-345\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Booty-Shorts.jpg\" alt=\"Booty Shorts\" width=\"564\" height=\"564\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>6. Old Sneakers</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Rundown tennis shoes are not for you. You deserve better than that.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-316\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/6.-Old-Sneakers.png\" alt=\"6. Old Sneakers\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>5. Cheap Bras</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Don’t deprive your boobies of some quality stuff. They are not young anymore and deserve something more comfortable.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-315\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/5.-Cheap-Bras.jpg\" alt=\"5. Cheap Bras\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>4. Glitter Eyeshadow</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Glitter should be put on things that need to sparkle. It’s not the other way around.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-347\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Glitter-Eyeshadow.jpg\" alt=\"Glitter Eyeshadow\" width=\"853\" height=\"563\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>3. Platform Flip-Flops</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Nobody should wear them. They are neither cool, nor sexy.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-313\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/3.-Platform-Flip-Flops.jpg\" alt=\"3. Platform Flip-Flops\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>2. Abercrombie &amp; Fitch</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Can you even fit yourself in them? I don’t think so.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-312\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/2.-Abercrombie-Fitch.jpg\" alt=\"2. Abercrombie &amp; Fitch\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>1. Scrunchies</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Don’t look like someone who has no time to do her hair. Your hair is a part and parcel of your personality.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-311\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/1.-Scrunchies.jpg\" alt=\"1. Scrunchies\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />','25 Things That Middle-Aged Women Should Not Wear','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2016-10-06 17:42:06','2016-10-06 17:42:06','',287,'http://feelsyoung.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(715,1,'2016-10-06 17:55:09','2016-10-06 17:55:09','<h3>With new threats popping up every day, army of a country plays the most crucial role in saving sovereignty and the population of a country from external and internal threats. A powerful army doesn’t always necessarily need to be huge, if it can make advances in other fields like cyber warfare and modern technology. Often building on tactical ability could be proven more effective than raising an army with huge firepower.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>30. Portugal</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3>The Portuguese army’s golden days lie in its colonial past when the country ruled many African countries. Today it might not have the same might as it had before, but it still has an army that is superior to many other nations’.</h3>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-226\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Portugal.jpg\" alt=\"Portugal\" width=\"700\" height=\"500\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong> 29. South Africa</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>There was a time when the South African army was used as a tool to oppress its own people. But after the end of the apartheid regime, the country has rebuilt its army and established it as a protector of the people.</h3>\r\n<h2><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-304\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/South_African_Army.jpg\" alt=\"South_African_Army\" width=\"640\" height=\"416\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>28. Malaysia</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3>Despite having a modern and well-equipped military, the Malaysians have a neutral policy to deal with major conflicts. The country’s army is however playing a pivotal role in peacekeeping missions.</h3>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-219 size-full\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/malaysian.jpg\" alt=\"malaysian\" width=\"568\" height=\"390\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--><strong>27. Norway</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>You might be frowning to see the name of the country where Nobel peace prize is given. The Norwegian army is one of the most skilled in the world.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-222 \" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Norway.jpg\" alt=\"Norway\" width=\"612\" height=\"408\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>26. Singapore </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>A tiny city state like Singapore always has different security concerns. The country’s leaders gave the duty to build their army to the Israelis. The result? Singapore has one of the most professional armies in the South East Asian region.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Singapore.jpg\" alt=\"Singapore\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>25. North Korea</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>After the fall of the Soviet Union the authoritarian country found itself friendless. To tackle its neighbor in the South, the country has never stopped developing nuclear weapons that empower the army.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-221\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/North-Korea.jpg\" alt=\"North Korea\" width=\"750\" height=\"406\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>24. Mexico</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Mexican army played a vital role in helping the government and local administration in containing drug related violence. Thanks to the Mexican army, the law and order situation in that country is much better, if not the best.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Mexico.jpg\" alt=\"Mexico\" width=\"640\" height=\"395\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>23. The Netherlands </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Dutch army was harassed in the hands of the Nazis during WWII. After the war, the country worked hard on building a reliable army to defend its territories.</h3>\r\n<h2><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-301\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Dutch-army.jpg\" alt=\"Dutch-army\" width=\"1080\" height=\"720\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<strong>22. Sweden </strong>\r\n<h3>When you have border with a country that boasts one of the biggest armies in the world, there is no way to take the matter of defense lightly. The Swedes are also prominent for making high-end military hardware.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-231\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Sweden-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"Sweden\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>21. Switzerland</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though Switzerland always maintains neutrality, in this ever changing global scenario there is no alternative to having a decent military. And the Swiss have it.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Switzerland1.jpg\" alt=\"Switzerland1\" width=\"800\" height=\"505\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>20. Syria</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Syrian army was one of the strongest in the Middle East, before all hell broke loose. Their presence in Lebanon was a major headache for the Israelis.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-305\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Syrian-army.jpg\" alt=\"Syrian army\" width=\"669\" height=\"377\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>19. Iran</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Years of sanctions slapped by the world could not stop the Iranians from building a strong army. In today’s major regional conflicts Iranian presence shows this clearly.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Iran.jpg\" alt=\"Iran\" width=\"650\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>18. Australia </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though Australia is a huge country, the army is relatively small. But it doesn’t mean that it is weak.</h3>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-206\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Australia.jpg\" alt=\"Australia\" width=\"650\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<strong>17. Indonesia</strong>\r\n<h3>In all fields, Indonesians are open to everything west. Through vigorous cooperation with major Western military powers, the island nation has formed a strong army.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Indonesian.jpg\" alt=\"Indonesian\" width=\"736\" height=\"572\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>16. Poland </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Poland has one of the finest armies in Eastern Europe. With US logistic support and training the Polish army is now able to give any intruder a big fight.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-303\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Polish_Army.jpeg\" alt=\"Polish_Army\" width=\"770\" height=\"447\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>15. Canada</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though the number of the Canadian armed forces personnel is meager in comparison to the Americans, Canada has a modern and professional army.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-208\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Canada.jpg\" alt=\"RIMPAC 2012\" width=\"750\" height=\"536\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>14. Brazil</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The second largest army in South America has been involved in different peace keeping missions. The Brazilian army’s role in Haiti is praiseworthy for bringing stability.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-307\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/brazilian-army.jpg\" alt=\"brazilian army\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>13. Egypt</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Thanks to years of US military aid, the Egyptian army is one of the biggest and strongest in the Middle East. The army there also is a potent force during major political upheavals.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-210\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Egypt.jpg\" alt=\"Egypt\" width=\"623\" height=\"315\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>12. Israel</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The IDF or Israeli Defense Force is one of the strongest in the world. Till now, it has won all the wars against its larger Arab neighbors.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/israel-1.jpg\" alt=\"israel 1\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>11. Japan</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Japan has recently removed the last barrier to erase the pacifist clause from its constitution. In the coming years we are sure to see a more assertive Japanese Self Defense Force.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Japan.jpg\" alt=\"Japan\" width=\"750\" height=\"500\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>10. South Korea</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>With an effective conscription system, the South Koreans have made their army ready for any untoward situation. The formidable army is a good match for its bitter rivals in the North.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-230\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/south-korean.jpg\" alt=\"A South Korean army soldier runs in front of K-1 tanks after a live-fire military exercise as a part of the Seoul International Aerospace and Defense Exhibition 2011 on the Seungjin fire training field in Pocheon\" width=\"1000\" height=\"568\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>9. Turkey</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Turkey boasts the second largest army in NATO, right after USA. The Turkish army has been able to effectively contain the Kurdish insurgency.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-237\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Turkey.jpg\" alt=\"Turkey Army Troops, Militants Mass in Aleppo: Russian Monitor\" width=\"650\" height=\"375\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>8. Germany</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Experts believe that the German army is yet to match its formidable economic might. The biggest economy in Europe is however making rapid advance in the defense sector.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Germany.jpg\" alt=\"Germany\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>7. Pakistan </strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Pakistan army is still the most potent state institution in that country. At the moment it is fighting a fanatic Taliban faction in the country’s North Waziristan.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Pakistan.jpg\" alt=\"Pakistan\" width=\"580\" height=\"386\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>6. The United Kingdom</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Though the British army went through several budget cuts in the last few years, it’s still one of the strongest militaries in the world. The army still maintains presence in different British overseas territories.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-united-kingdom.jpg\" alt=\"The united kingdom\" width=\"940\" height=\"467\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>5. France</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>France is one of the forces leading the fight against the brutal Islamic State. Besides they have presence in different African countries, where extremism is at rise.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-302\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/french-army.jpg\" alt=\"french army\" width=\"1110\" height=\"624\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>4. India</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The archrival of Pakistan, India has one of the biggest armies in the world. The Indian army has so far beaten the Pakistanis in three big wars.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/india.jpg\" alt=\"india\" width=\"640\" height=\"392\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>3. China</strong></h2>\r\n<h2>The Chinese has the biggest army in the world with more than 2 million active personnel. In the recent years the country has continued defense budget spending spree to match the likes of United State.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-300\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Chinese-army.jpg\" alt=\"Chinese army\" width=\"885\" height=\"516\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>2. Russia</strong></h2>\r\n<h2>The Russian army might not be in the best position in comparison to its Western rivals, but it still has supremacy around its borders. The annexation of Crimea is the best example of it. The Russians have started modernizing its army after years of stalemate following the collapse of the Soviet Union, though.</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/russia.jpg\" alt=\"russia\" width=\"670\" height=\"400\" /><!--nextpage--></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>1. The United States Army</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The US army is still the strongest army in the world with the most advanced technologies, weapons, and an effective training system. The country’s defense budget is also the world’s biggest, and no other country is likely to overlap it in the upcoming years.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-244\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/United-States.jpg\" alt=\"United States\" width=\"752\" height=\"423\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>','30 Most Powerful Armies In The World','','inherit','closed','closed','','172-revision-v1','','','2016-10-06 17:55:09','2016-10-06 17:55:09','',172,'http://feelsyoung.com/172-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(716,1,'2016-10-25 12:51:53','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2016-10-25 12:51:53','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/?p=716',0,'post','',0),(717,1,'2016-10-25 12:57:15','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<ol>\n 	<li>test</li>\n</ol>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-683\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Filipina.jpg\" alt=\"Filipina\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->\n\n2.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-665\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Thailand.jpg\" alt=\"Thailand\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" />\n\n<!--nextpage-->','test','','draft','open','open','','','','','2016-10-25 12:57:15','2016-10-25 12:57:15','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/?p=717',0,'post','',0),(718,1,'2016-10-25 12:56:09','2016-10-25 12:56:09','<ol>\r\n 	<li>test</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-683\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Filipina.jpg\" alt=\"Filipina\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n2.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-665\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Thailand.jpg\" alt=\"Thailand\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->','test','','inherit','closed','closed','','717-revision-v1','','','2016-10-25 12:56:09','2016-10-25 12:56:09','',717,'http://feelsyoung.com/717-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(719,1,'2016-10-25 17:30:36','2016-10-25 17:30:36','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Helen Hunt - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-722 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/hellen1.jpg\" alt=\"hellen1\" width=\"564\" height=\"306\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Helen Hunt - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Helen has never dropped the ball. She is always in movies and TV. Her Oscar-winning performance in the As Good As It Gets is one of her recent films. She had her own hit comedy Ride, back in 2014. During the 911New York attack, she witnessed the ordeal from her apartment. She moved out three days later to Connecticut.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-723 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/hellen2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"hellen2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Janet - Then\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Janet is the youngest member of the Jackson family. She performed in a number of shows with her older brothers. She was, however, more into acting than singing. She took the role of Penny in the “Good Ties” show as a kid. She played a battered and frightened child, neighbor to the Evans family. She appeared in “Different Strokes” and “Fame” hit shows but still managed her singing career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-724 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/janet1.jpg\" alt=\"janet1\" width=\"578\" height=\"423\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Janet - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Janet has grown to be only second to her brother Michael in the recording industry. She is highly celebrated and sold millions of records. She has starred in hit movies, awarded with multi-platinum albums, and appearing in performances. She is now married to billionaire Wissam Al Mana.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\" wp-image-725 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/janet2.jpg\" alt=\"162420084SR00004_Sergio_Ros\" width=\"620\" height=\"310\" /></h3>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>David Cassidy - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In “The Partridge Family” hit show, David starred as Keith Partridge. Keith was the lead singer in the family band. He was hired solely for his good looks. In reality, the show producers never cared whether or not he could sing.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-726 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/David-cassidy-then.jpg\" alt=\"david-cassidy-then\" width=\"664\" height=\"336\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>David Cassidy - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He lived on to prove to the producers that he could sing. This went on, and David produced ten albums with The Partridge Family. This saw the plunge of David into superstardom. He has a successful career in music and television.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-727 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cassidy1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"cassidy1\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kim Richards - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She starred in a number of shows and films through the 70s. She was one the most popular child actors around. She seemed to be all over the public eye with her role in films like Escape to Witch Mountain and its Return from Witch Mountain sequel and shows like “Nanny and the Professor” and “James at Sixteen.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-728 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/kim1.jpg\" alt=\"kim1\" width=\"644\" height=\"362\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kim Richards - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In 2010, Kim came back into the public and was part of the hit reality series “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills” together with her sister Kyle. There was a rumor of drugs and alcohol abuse soon after starting the show. This was rumored to be partly due to her erratic behavior on camera. Her tribulations went on back in 2015 when she was arrested for public intoxication, trespassing, battery on a police officer and resisting an officer at the Beverly Hills Hotel. She now returns to the show as guest star occasionally.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-729 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/kim2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"kim2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Jacksons - Then\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Remember the “Jackson Five”? The hit group was made of Jackie, Jermaine, Marlon, Michael, and Tito. Their first 4 singles shot to the billboard charts as number one setting a record in the music business back in 1970. The singles were “I Want You Back,” “ABC,” “The Love You Save,” and “I’ll Be There.” The 4 songs were released over 9 months and “I’ll Be There” maintained at the top for 5 weeks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-730 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/jackson1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"jackson1\" width=\"624\" height=\"312\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Jacksons - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>After 17-year hiatus, the Jacksons reunited to celebrate Michael Jackson’s solo career, back in 2011. They had a Unity Tour where they performed. The brothers still perform even though Michael is dead and Randy retired years ago.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-731 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/jackson2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"jackson2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Johnny Whitaker - Then\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>From “Family Affair” to “General Hospital,” John played in a number of television series. In the Tom Sawyer film, John became the first to give Jodie Foster an on-screen kiss. After the death of his on-screen sister (“Family Affair) Anissa Jones, John had a difficult life and retired from acting for some time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-732 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/johny1.jpg\" alt=\"johny1\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Johnny Whitaker - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>John went through a hard life of substance abuse. His family came to his rescue and his 12-step program cleansed him for over a decade now. He can fluently speak Spanish, Portuguese, French and American Sign Language.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-733 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/johny2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"johny2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ron Howard - Then\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Back in the days, Ron was prominent for his acting. His role in “The Andy Griffith Show” made him so popular in the 60s. His most successful acting role came through the “Happy Days” show as Richie Cunningham, the lead character. He grew up in Milwaukee as a mild-mannered teenager.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-734 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ron1.jpg\" alt=\"ron1\" width=\"632\" height=\"316\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ron Howard - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Howard is one of the most successful people in the world of television and film in the Hollywood’s history. To say he has succeeded as an actor, producer, or director is not enough. He has been in over 27 files, directed over 28 motion picture films and produced close to 20 other films. He has truly lived to his potential.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-735 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ron2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"ron2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robbie Rist - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the last 6 episodes of “The Brandy Bunch” show, he joined as Cousin Oliver. Rist was actually 9 even though he played as 8-year old Oliver. He came into the show to help in boosting the ratings due to completion from “Sanford &amp; Son” show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-736 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/robbie-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"robbie\" width=\"660\" height=\"330\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robbie Rist - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Rist provides voiceover as an adult in various films including the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and other animated shows like the “Batman: The Animated Series.” Film soundtracks for movies like Sharknado and Sharknado 2 are some of his talented works. He also performs as a guitarist, lead singer, drummer and/or bassist of a number Los Angeles rock bands.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-737 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/robbie2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"robbie2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Barry Williams - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the hit series “The Brady Bunch”, Barry played the role of Greg Brady, the eldest child. Her career was flourished and soon after, he became a love for many female fans across the United States. He also recorded 4 albums and together with his TV siblings, the fame came calling.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-739 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/barry1.jpg\" alt=\"barry1\" width=\"660\" height=\"481\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Barry Williams - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Barry scooped the Young Artist Foundation Former Child Star Lifetime Achievement Award in 1989. Three years later, the honor was followed by releasing an autobiography, Growing Up Brady…I Was A Teenage Greg. It remained in the list of best-seller for3 months. In 2001, as an executive producer, he turned his book into a made-for-TV movie on NBC. He recently held a guest role in “Brady Bunch” specials and other shows like “That 70’s Show” and “Three’s Company”. Barry spent a good time in the musical theater for roles like in “The Sound of Music,” “West Side Story,” and “Grease.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-740 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/barry2.jpg\" alt=\"barry\" width=\"651\" height=\"434\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Erin Murphy - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The popular television series “Bewitched”, made Erin very famous. The series ran from 1964 to 1972. In the early seasons, she played young Tabitha Stephens with Diane, her fraternal twin sister. Erin later took the role herself as the kids grew less alike. She became one of the most famous actresses in the world.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-741 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/erin1.jpg\" alt=\"erin1\" width=\"612\" height=\"459\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Erin Murphy - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>After the end of “Bewitched”, Erin bounced to various auditions, turning down various commercials and modeling jobs. The family later moved to Orange County, and she attended 6th grade here. She married and got her first kid at 21 years. She loved acting, and this led her into teaching the craft. Whenever film shooting was in town, she would work in makeup and production. Her stunt double role for Melissa Leo and Virginia Madsen was great. 10 years later, she went back to Los Angeles and began working on reality TV shows, celebrity judge, and commercials. She owns two companies, and one of them sells frozen vodka martini ice pops. She is married and mother of 6 boys.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-742 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Erin2-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"erin2\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Maureen McCormick - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Maureen was the leading lady for “The Brady Bunch” show. She is best known for the role played in the show as Marcia Brady between 1969 and 1974.she was Brady’s oldest girl. She portrayed a smart, pretty, and confident girl that was popular in school and home. She was a politics’ enthusiast. Her iconic role came when she was 12 years old.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-743 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Maureen1.jpg\" alt=\"maureen1\" width=\"650\" height=\"486\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Maureen McCormick - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She married Michael Cummings and got a daughter in 1989, Natalie. After the end of her TV life, she struggled with drug addiction but eventually overcame it. She appeared as a contestant in the “VH1’s Celebrity Fit Club” and won in 2007.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-744\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Maureen2.jpg\" alt=\"maureen2\" width=\"613\" height=\"389\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Mindy Cohn - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Her Natalie portrayal made her so popular. She was an irrepressible “Facts of Life” series’ student back in 1979to 1988. The show’s success is argued to be on Natalie’s character. In some way, this role ‘cursed’ her television role: she could never get a new one.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-745 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mindy1.jpg\" alt=\"mindy1\" width=\"586\" height=\"293\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mindy Cohn - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She earned a Cultural Anthropology degree while still acting. She is a founder of the weSPARK cancer support center. She makes guest television appearances but majorly on voiceover. The “Velma” if the “Scooby-Doo” animation series is her famous voice. She was nominated for Emmy for her work.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-746 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mindy2.jpg\" alt=\"mindy2\" width=\"626\" height=\"313\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ron Paolillo - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>If you have ever watched “Welcome Back Kotter”, then you know Arnold Horshack. He played as a group’s clown in a class of high school kids known as the Sweathogs. He went ahead to perfect his character and learned to love like a hyena.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-747 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ronp1.jpg\" alt=\"ronp1\" width=\"590\" height=\"295\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ron Paolillo - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In his adult life, Ron was highly demanded. He played a variety of characters for various TV shows and films including “Laverne and Shirley in The Army,” and Friday The Thirteenth among others. He has directed a number of Broadway plays and musicals. He is a fashion designer and wrote a couple of children books. He passed on in 2012 due to a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-748 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ronp2.jpg\" alt=\" Ron P\" width=\"636\" height=\"358\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Danny Bonaduce - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the 70s, Danny rose as a child actor to fame. He played as Danny Partridge in the famous “The Partridge Family.” His bright-red hair and the great ways as a child in the family band bought his name. He was the group’s fictional bass guitar player. In the show, he Danny costarred with David Cassidy. They have remained friends since the first show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-749 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Danny1.jpg\" alt=\"danny1\" width=\"636\" height=\"446\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Danny Bonaduce - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He is now a television and radio personality, professional wrestler, and comedian.  He starred in a number of TV series after the show ended. Some of the series include “Breaking Bonaduce”, a VH1’s reality show back in 205. He hosted radio shows in Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Danny has also been a regular music and talk show host at a Seattle radio known as KZOK-FM as from November 2011.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-750 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Danny2.jpg\" alt=\"danny2\" width=\"569\" height=\"497\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Susan Dey - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In “The Partridge Family” hit show, Susan played Laurie Partridge. She was joined by Shirley Jones and David Cassidy and other actors to make up the cast for the show. Before joining the cast, Dey was a fashion model. Before the show, she had no acting experience.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-751 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/susan-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"Susan\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Susan Dey - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Dey has been involved in many films including Skyjacked, Disappearance, and Little Women. She has played in various television shows including “L.A.Law.” She refuses the joining of the Partridge Family Reunion and to date, she and Cassidy never speak after their romantic encounter went horrible.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-752 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/susan2.jpg\" alt=\"susan2\" width=\"592\" height=\"296\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mackenzie Phillips - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When she worked on the American Graffiti hit, Mackenzie was only 12. Her stardom continued in the 1970s with her Julie Cooper role in the “One Day at a Time” TV series. By then, she was taking home $50,000 a week. She started doing drugs and drinking by the third season leading to late arrivals on the TV show. She was forced into taking a 6-week break and later entered the Fair Oaks Hospital for treatment. In 1981, she was invited by the producers of the “One Day at a Time” back into the show. She collapsed into the show’s set after getting back into cocaine addiction. She was fired for good.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-753 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Mackenzie1.jpg\" alt=\"mackenzie1\" width=\"605\" height=\"340\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mackenzie Phillips - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She checked into rehabilitation for long-term in 1992. She remained here for close to 9 months. Later, she co-starred in the Disney Channel series with Cara DeLizia in 1999. It was called “So Weird” playing a fictional rock star Molly Phillips. During her time in the “ER,” “Without a Trace,” “Cold Case,” and “7th Heaven”, she was a guest star. She later became a rehab counselor to help others at the Breathe Life Healing Center in West Hollywood, California.<img class=\"wp-image-754 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Mackenzie2.jpg\" alt=\"mackenzie2\" width=\"616\" height=\"301\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Valerie Bertinelli - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Valerie was born in 1960, and by 1975 she had made a name for herself. She had already started appearing in the “One Day at a Time”, a new sitcom. She appeared in the series’ 208 of the 209 episodes before it came to an end in 1984. In 2005, she reunited with the rest of the show’s cast for the “One Day at a Time Reunion Special.” In 1981, she scooped the Golden Globe at 21 years of age.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-755 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Valerie1.jpg\" alt=\"valerie1\" width=\"585\" height=\"441\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Valerie Bertinelli - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Valerie’s career hasn’t shown any signs to slow down. She has been acting all along. She starred in 2 of the ‘90s sitcoms “Café Americain” and “Sydney.” She joined “Touched by an Angel” show that lasted 2 seasons. She later became Jenny Craig’s spokesperson after struggling with her weight for long. She appeared in many commercials for the diet company. She later joined Betty White, Jane Leeves, and Wendie Malick for the TV Land series “Hot in Cleveland” in 2010. The series lasted until June 3 2015.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-756 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Valerie2.jpg\" alt=\"valerie2\" width=\"521\" height=\"348\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tatum O’Neal - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Her stats says it all: she won the 1974 Academy Award while at the age of 10. Her turn as Addie Loggins in the Paper Moon made her take home the golden statue. In 1976, she made an appearance in The Bad News Bears and also Nickelodeon the same year. She left a lasting mark in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-757 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tatum1.jpg\" alt=\"tatum1\" width=\"572\" height=\"381\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tatum O’Neal- Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She got married in 1986 to John McErnroe and got three kids. They divorced in 1994 after separating in 1992. She had a flourishing career in the film industry back in the ‘70s. However, things changed and for the next 15 years, she would only appear in 5 films. Her guest appearance on “8 Simple Rules for Dating My Teenage Daughter” marked her return to the film world in the 2000s. She also appeared in “Law and Order: Criminal Intent” as well as the “Sex and the City.” In 2005, she got a recurring role in the “Rescue Me” hit series. She has gone ahead acting while focusing on her TV shows work.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-758 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tatum2.jpg\" alt=\"tatum2\" width=\"596\" height=\"398\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Scott Baio - Then\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The former heart-throb teen is popularly known for his role in the “Happy Days” show as Chachi. He was the love interest for Joanie Cunningham (Erin Moran). He played as the leading the musical gangster film called “Bugsy Malone”. The child actors in the film gave it a great twist. Jodie Foster, one of the actors; won the future Academy winner. Baio had beaten over 2,000 kids for this part.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-759 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/scot1-1024x678.jpg\" alt=\"scot1\" width=\"616\" height=\"408\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Scott Baio - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Scott later joined “Joanie Loves Chachi”, a spin-off show after his “Happy Days” time. He later played in other films like Skatetown USA, Zapped, and Foxes among others. He has recently starred in his own reality show. He produces shows for Nick at Nite. He is a registered Republican and was reported to be in an altercation with a barista for failing to name the 2016 Republican presumptive nominee.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-760 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/scot2.jpg\" alt=\"scot2\" width=\"553\" height=\"373\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mike Lookinland - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In “The Brandy Bunch” show, Mike played the Bobby Brandy role. He was the youngest boy in the family and was usually nice and energetic. His natural hair was sandy brown and curly. His hair had to be dyed and straightened to match the rest in the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-761 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mike1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"mike1\" width=\"598\" height=\"299\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mike Lookinland - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Mike has played in a number of shows like “Little House on The Prairie” and other Brandy Bunch specials and movies such as the Towering Inferno before leaving the show world entirely. He is now married and has two kids with a flourishing concrete business in Utah.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-762 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mike2.jpg\" alt=\"mike2\" width=\"581\" height=\"327\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kristy McNichol - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>McNichol began her young career in commercials and then into guest appearances in some series like “Starsky &amp; Hutch,” “Love American Style” and “The Bionic Woman” as well as “The Love Boat.” Her Patricia Apple role in the “Apple’s Way” series was her first regular series job. The 1976 “Family” drama series saw her earn the Emmy Awards for Best Supporting Actress in a Dramatic Series. Later, she went into music and recorded the Kristy &amp; Jimmy McNichol album for RCA Records. “He’s So Fine” hit was her best and it peaked at #70.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-763 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kristy1.jpg\" alt=\"kristy1\" width=\"646\" height=\"364\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kristy McNichol - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>her role in the Little Darlings movie continued to make a name for her. She co-starred with Matt Dillon, Cynthia Dixon, and Tatum O’Neal. Alongside Dennis Quaid and Mark Hamill, she appeared in The Night the Lights Went Out in Georgia. A year later, Kristy would appear in Only When I Laugh by Neil Simon. She was then nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress. Before leaving the cast of “Empty Nest”, Kristy appeared in several seasons but returned for the final episode in 1995. She has left the screen since then but continues to voice characters in various animated series like “Invasion America” and “Extreme Ghostbusters.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-764 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kristy2.jpg\" alt=\"kristy2\" width=\"619\" height=\"348\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tanya Tucker - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At just 13 years of age, this kid shot into the country charts thanks to her “Delta Dawn” hit. Mel Tillis was the first one to discover her. This was through a stage invitation thanks to her vocal skills. In 1969, her family moved to Las Vegas and not long before she was regularly performing in the city. She gained Dolores Fuller’s attention and later signed to Colombia Records.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-765 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tanya1.jpg\" alt=\"tanya1\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tanya Tucker - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Tanya had a successful career. Decades after her first hit, she became one of the most successful country singers of all time. She collected a streak of Top 10 and Top 40 hits. Her country music prowess saw her get nominated for various Country Music Association awards. She released various albums that were popular.  Some of her hits included “Blood Red and Goin’ Down” and “What’s Your Mama’s Name?” of 1973. 2 years later, another hit came by: “Lizzie and Rainman.” It was later followed by the “Strong Enough to Bend” in 1988. She is arguably one of the few childhood stars to carry their fans into adulthood stardom. She has been reckoned as a top influence in the female country music world.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-766 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tanya2.jpg\" alt=\"tanya2\" width=\"617\" height=\"347\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Haywood Nelson - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>His Dwayne Nelson role in the “What’s Happening!!” series made him so popular. The series aired between 1976 and 1979. He starred in the spin-off series “What’s Happening Now!!” from1985 to 1988. As a child, Nelson appeared in various national commercials and later in the movie Mixed Company. In 1974, alongside Mario Thomas, Nelson appeared on Broadway in Thieves. He starred in “Sanford and Son” at 14 years as Grady’s grandson. He later starred in the “Grady”, a spin-off of “Sanford and Son.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-767 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Haywood1.jpg\" alt=\"haywood1\" width=\"568\" height=\"394\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Haywood Nelson - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Nelson had difficulties landing another TV show of such a national appeal. However, he has continued to work in TV. He guest-starred in the “Kojak” before he went to work behind the scenes. He has been recently working with talk shows’ crew, TV shows, and interview programs. He is among the first African American teen idols to be nationally recognized.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-768 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Haywood2.jpg\" alt=\"haywood2\" width=\"622\" height=\"311\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Danielle Spencer - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Danielle played the part of Dee Thomas in the “What’s Happening” television show. In the cast, she played as the “more than annoying little sister” and did so with aplomb. She is famously known for her favorite saying: “Ooooohh, I’m tellin’ Mama!” The show lasted from August 1976 to April 1979.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-769 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Danielle1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"danielle1\" width=\"616\" height=\"308\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Danielle Spencer - Now\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Spencer is now a doctor of veterinary medicine in California. In 2014, she was diagnosed with breast cancer but she was lucky to beat it. She is the only kid actor to be inducted into the Smithsonian Museum as a permanent exhibition on African American Culture.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-770 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Danielle2.jpg\" alt=\"danielle2\" width=\"614\" height=\"307\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Adam Rich - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Rich is best known for the television series “Eight Is Enough.” He played as Nicholas Bradford, the youngest son. It ran from 1977 to 81 for five seasons. His bowl haircut was an inspiration to many parents who did the same for their kids.it was one of his recognizable aspects. He was known as “America’s little brother” for this iconic role. He had a rough encounter in the ‘80s, and he went under for good.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-771 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Adam1.jpg\" alt=\"adam1\" width=\"610\" height=\"466\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Adam Rich - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 14, Rich had started smoking Marijuana. Things went even worse at 17 when he dropped out of high school. He almost lost his life to Valium overdose in 1989. His pharmacy burglar attempt in 1991 got him arrested. 5 years later, Might – a San Francisco-based magazine – published a death hoax through his consent claiming to have been murdered. In 2001, he was arrested for driving under the influence. He has entered and left the rehab for at least 3 times. Currently, he is shopping around for new TV films and shows’ script ideas.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-772 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Adam2.jpg\" alt=\"adam2\" width=\"609\" height=\"343\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Karen Carpenter - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Karen plunged into fame as a drummer and singer. Her skill on the instrument was an admiration for many. Luminaries would go on to love her style. Her massive success in the 70s came thanks to her contralto vocal range. Together with Richard, her brother, they had various performances. Her “Close to You” album featured various singles that peaked in the Hot 100.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-773 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/karen1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"karen1\" width=\"605\" height=\"454\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Karen Carpenter - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She passed away on European tour where The Carpenters were to perform for Queen Elizabeth. She was involved in performances up until her death.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-774 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/karen2.jpg\" alt=\"karen2\" width=\"613\" height=\"316\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Linda Blair - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She is mostly known for her tricks to vomit pea soup after spinning her head around in circles. Her role in The Exorcist came at 14 years of age. In The Exorcist II: The Heretic, she decided to renew her role as a posse child in 1977. Her Academy Award nomination was thanks to her first role. She won the Golden Globe. She began as a child model at 6 years. Her short-lived daytime soap opera role in the “Hidden Fences” helped to boost her career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-775 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Linda1.gif\" alt=\"linda1\" width=\"598\" height=\"472\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Linda Blair - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Blair appeared in various horror, and other low-budget exploitation films in the 1980s such films included Hell Night, Savage Streets, and Chained Heat. Later in 1990, her appearance in the Repossessed comedy she made fun of her horror movie roots. In 1996, she made a cameo in the film Scream. She later appeared in the “L.A. 7” BBC TV show and “Grease”. She hosted the “Scariest Places on Earth” by Fox Family between 2000 and 2006. Her guest role in the ”Supernatural” TV show was her recent one.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-776 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Linda2.jpg\" alt=\"LINDA\" width=\"611\" height=\"459\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Melissa Gilbert - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Melissa started her career in the late ‘60sand early ‘70s. She did a number of commercials before starring as a guest in various TV roles. During her role as Laura Ingalls Wilder in the “Little House on the Prairie”, she had a big breakthrough. This was between 1974 and 1984. She also appeared in various TV movies such as The Miracle Worker as well as The Diary of Anne Frank.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-777 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Melissa1-1024x538.jpg\" alt=\"melissa1\" width=\"640\" height=\"336\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Melissa Gilbert - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Melissa has continued acting appearing in various TV programs. “Batman: The Animated Series” is one of her well-known roles wither her voice. From 2001 and 2005, she acted as the President of the Screen Actors Guild. In the “Little House of the Prairie, the Musical”, she played Caroline “Ma” Ingalls. She is loved by her fans and when she contested for hit reality TV show, “Dancing with the Stars”, on NBC it was great for her fans. Some health issues forced her to drop from the Michigan US Congress Democratic race in 2016.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-778 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Melissa2.jpg\" alt=\"melissa2\" width=\"637\" height=\"359\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Leif Garrett - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Like David Cassidy, Leif was a brilliant child actor, TV personality, and singer.Leif started the ‘70s with a bang: the film Walking Tall was the opener and drew the curtains with Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. He made appearances in at least 10 films and TV shows. He impressed everyone he worked with. In the late 70s, his personal difficulties.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-779 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Leif1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"leif1\" width=\"620\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Leif Garrett - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>It is true to say that Leif’s downfall was crafted by his partying, drugs and celebrity life. At 17, he crashed a leased Porsche 1979, leaving his friend a paraplegic. He has been in and out of drug and legal troubles. He has been arrested for heroin possession and once bought cocaine from undercover cops. His adult life has been marred by controversy and drama. He was ordered for rehab.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-780 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Leif2-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"leif2\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jodie Foster - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 3 years, Jodie had begun her acting career. At 5 years, she made her way into the TV series “Mayberry R.F.D.” she had become a regular fixture of the primetime TV by the late 1960s. She starred in a number of children films. In her teens, she had a breakout and made appearances in The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, Taxi Driver, and Disney’s Freaky Friday, and Candleshoe.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-781 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jodie1.jpg\" alt=\"jodie1\" width=\"613\" height=\"334\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jodie Foster - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Her Hollywood life continued to flourish. She decided to attend Yale and appeared in the controversial The Accused film. She won the Academy Award and Golden Globe. 3 years later, she took home another Oscar thanks to her role in The Silence of the Lambs as Claire. She still thrives in Hollywood.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-782 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jodie2.jpg\" alt=\"jodie2\" width=\"622\" height=\"414\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mason Reese - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>His look and talent were Mason’s perfect recipe for his stardom in the 70s. He acted in 70 TV commercials alone. He was ever on shows such as “Mike Douglas” and “Howard Cosell.” He was literally on almost every talk show back then. He lived as a pop star back in the days.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-783 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Mason1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"mason1\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mason Reese - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Mason became a restaurateur after his TV retirement. He opened a number of restaurants like Paladar and Destination Bar and Grille in the area of Manhattan. He has been raising money to make the pending “Life Interrupted” TV pilot. The show featured Dan Wells, who played in “Gilligan’s Island” as Mary Ann; Alison Arngrim, who played Neil Oleson in ”Little House on the Prairie;” Erin Murphy, who played Tabitha on “Bewitched;” and Michael Learned, who played Olivia Walton in “The Waltons;” as well as “The Brady Bunch’s” Robbie Rich, who played Cousin Oliver among other television icons.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"wp-image-784 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Mason2.jpg\" alt=\"mason2\" width=\"580\" height=\"290\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Erin Moran - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the television show “Happy Days”, Erin played the youngest child of the Cunningham family. She played Joanie Cunningham with a sense of timing and comedy skills that were considered perfect for a “brat sister.” She played this part from 1974 to 1984 and later from 1982 to 1983 during the spin-off “Joanie Loves Chachi.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-785 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Erin-Moran1.jpg\" alt=\"erin\" width=\"606\" height=\"303\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Erin Moran - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>After “Happy Days”, she played sporadic roles. She would later get into financial issues. Things went south when Moran’s downward took to a spiral and the world watched her drink in public. She was evicted from their house and forced to move into a trailer with her mother-in-law and husband.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-786 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Erin-Moran2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"erin-moran2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mark Lester - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Best known by US fans thanks to his Oliver Twist’s character, Lester made his film debut at 6 years. During the musical adaption of the film, he took the role of Oliver at 8 years. He could never sing, so all his singing was dubbed by musical director’s daughter in the Oliver Twist.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-787 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Mark1-1024x819.jpg\" alt=\"mark1\" width=\"640\" height=\"512\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Mark Lester - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At the age of 19 Lester retired from acting and went to school. He went to be an osteopath. He was a close friend of Michael Jackson, and they became Godfathers to each other’s children. There claims that he gave sperm to Michael Jackson to conceive and the chances are that the children are his biologically.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-788 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Mark2.jpg\" alt=\"mark2\" width=\"614\" height=\"614\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robby Benson - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Best known for his film work, Robby was also a star in the TV. He played in show like the “Search for Tomorrow” soap opera and films like Jory, Jeremy, and Ode to Billy Joe, which was a hit. Robby was forced to learn skating so as to play in his famous Ice Castles film.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-789 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/robby1-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"robby1\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robby Benson - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Thanks to the Disney film Beauty and The Beast, Robby is now known as the voice of the ‘Beast’. He has served as a professor in Utah, New York, South Carolina, and Indiana. He has had around 4 heart surgeries, but he never wanted to discuss the condition with his producers and directors.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-790 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/robby2-1024x512.jpg\" alt=\"robby2\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lance Kerwin - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>If you are familiar with Salem’s Lot, “The Family Holvak,” and “James at Fifteen (and Sixteen),” then you know who Lance Kerwin. He played all of them with other 20 more roles in television and film in the 70s. As a child star, Kerwin played in his show of the decade “Emergency” and in 1979, he played his last: Salem’s Lot.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-791 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Lance1.jpg\" alt=\"lance1\" width=\"606\" height=\"303\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lance Kerwin - Now</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Kerwin retired in 1995 after a successful acting career. He worked as a minister in Kaua’i, Hawaii. He still lies there. Lance had admitted to having smoked pot before his 10th birthday. He was a crack user at his 20s. He had to go through a number of rehab stints. He got clean, and his wife pledged guilty to fraud. It was later discovered that he had falsified papers to get food stamps. He had around 3 homes in the USA.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-792\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Lance2.jpg\" alt=\"lance2\" width=\"652\" height=\"326\" />','Child Stars - Then and Now','','publish','open','open','','top-child-stars-of-the-70s','','','2016-10-25 17:50:28','2016-10-25 17:50:28','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/?p=719',0,'post','',0),(720,1,'2016-10-25 14:33:23','2016-10-25 14:33:23','','home','','inherit','open','closed','','home-2','','','2016-10-25 14:33:23','2016-10-25 14:33:23','',719,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Home.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(721,1,'2016-10-25 14:37:42','2016-10-25 14:37:42','<h3>Any memories from back in the days? Most of us can only remember the ‘70s with nostalgia. It was an era of its kind. Watching TV was a special thing: it was a thrilling family affair. This was way before the entrant of Netflix and DVR to the home entertainment world. From ‘The Brandy Bunch’ to ‘Good Times’ and ‘Happy Days’ or even the ‘What’s Happening’, every family had their choice. Those with a vivid memory of the days know pretty well the child stars involved and the episodes so well. Here, we will look at the various stars who rocked back then and how they are doing it now.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-720 size-full\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Home.jpg\" alt=\"home\" width=\"719\" height=\"484\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Helen Hunt - Then</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Throughout her life, she has been in the limelight. During her teen age, she had a brilliant TV and film career. She starred in various shows including “Amy Prentiss” (1974-75), “Swiss Family Robinson” (1975-76), and “The Fitzpatricks” (1977-78). She was also in the Rollercoaster in 1977.</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','From 8-Tracks To i-Tunes: Top Child Stars of the 70s, Then and Now','','inherit','closed','closed','','719-revision-v1','','','2016-10-25 14:37:42','2016-10-25 14:37:42','',719,'http://feelsyoung.com/719-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(722,1,'2016-10-25 14:39:15','2016-10-25 14:39:15','','hellen1','','inherit','open','closed','','hellen1','','','2016-10-25 14:39:15','2016-10-25 14:39:15','',719,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/hellen1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(723,1,'2016-10-25 14:40:26','2016-10-25 14:40:26','','hellen2','','inherit','open','closed','','hellen2','','','2016-10-25 14:40:26','2016-10-25 14:40:26','',719,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/hellen2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(724,1,'2016-10-25 14:42:18','2016-10-25 14:42:18','','janet1','','inherit','open','closed','','janet1','','','2016-10-25 14:42:28','2016-10-25 14:42:28','',719,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/janet1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(72