sweet gone sour’. Take a moment and think about it!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-866 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/So-Cute-It-Hurts.jpg\" alt=\"so-cute-it-hurts\" width=\"563\" height=\"422\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Rich People Are Horrible</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Wait, what just happened? Of the two groups, which one became a victim of rich mindlessness? Well, I can imagine what it takes to set up such an emphatic scene just for a selfie under the water – but that’s rich people’s problem!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-868 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Rich-People-Are.png\" alt=\"rich-people-are\" width=\"471\" height=\"468\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>I Can’t Blame Him</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>You got your selfie camera and as you walk in the open, this is what you land into: dogs at it! You do not just apologetically look at them and walk away – the perfect shot for you should be here. This is just mind-blowing!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-869\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/I-Can’t-Blame-Him.png\" alt=\"i-cant-blame-him\" width=\"560\" height=\"417\" />','The Most Cringeworthy Selfies!','','inherit','closed','closed','','836-revision-v1','','','2016-10-27 21:09:23','2016-10-27 21:09:23','',836,'http://feelsyoung.com/836-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(873,1,'2016-10-27 22:04:42','2016-10-27 22:04:42','<h3>With incredible endorsement deals and impressive paychecks, basketball players have found their way into the limelight, earning superstar status and even better pay as they are marketed around the world.  We found some of the top wealthiest NBA players of all time, most of whom are already retired.</h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Reggie Miller - $90 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Miller made a mark in the memories of NBA fans as one of the most skillful shooters. He had a flourishing 18-year spell at Indiana Pacers. Today, he lives happily and works as a Turner Sports commentator.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-874 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Reggie-Miller.jpg\" alt=\"reggie-miller\" width=\"592\" height=\"333\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Shawn Marion - $60 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Shawn was regarded as one of the most versatile players in the NBA league. On July 9, 2009, He signed a five-year contract worth $39 million.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-875 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Shawn-Marion.jpg\" alt=\"shawn-marion\" width=\"573\" height=\"434\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Vince Carter- $60 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The eight-time NBA all-star and Olympic gold medalist Vince Carter has had a long and bright career. In 2013, Carter became the 28th player in NBA history to eclipse the 22,000-point mark.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-876 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Vince-Carter.jpg\" alt=\"vince-carter\" width=\"606\" height=\"520\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Michael Finley - $65 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Finley had an impressive NBA career. He was the third rookie in Phoenix Suns history to score over 1,000 points in a season. Although he’s retired, Finley currently works in the front office for the Mavericks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-877 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Michael-Finley.jpg\" alt=\"michael-finley\" width=\"593\" height=\"451\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>David Robinson - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He is known as one of the greatest centers in the history of the NBA. Nicknamed “The Admiral” when he served as an officer with the United States Navy.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-878 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/David-Robinson.jpg\" alt=\"david-robinson\" width=\"551\" height=\"368\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Derrick Rose - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Played for Chicago Bulls for three years and in 2011 he won the NBA MVP award becoming the youngest player to win the award at age 22.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-879 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Derrick-Rose.jpg\" alt=\"derrick-rose\" width=\"597\" height=\"405\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Amar’e Stoudamire - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He is a professional basketball player, actor, author, producer, and motivational speaker. His off-court ventures include a clothing line, record label, and a series of children books for Scholastic Press.  He also owns a significant share of the Hapoel Jerusalem Basketball Club, the club he currently plays for!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-880 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Amare-Stoudamire.jpg\" alt=\"amare-stoudamire\" width=\"563\" height=\"493\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Paul Pierce - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Ten-time All-Star and 2008 NBA Champion and Finals Paul Pierce embodies what it means to be a champion on and off the court. Pierce currently plays for the Los Angeles Clippers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-881 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Paul-Pierce-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"paul-pierce\" width=\"592\" height=\"333\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Elton Brand - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The two-time NBA All-Star established himself as one of the top power forwards in the NBA league. He announced his retirement from professional basketball but returned on January 4, 2016, signing for the 76ers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-882 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Elton-Brand.jpg\" alt=\"Los Angeles Clippers v Utah Jazz\" width=\"603\" height=\"402\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Alonzo Mourning - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He played most of his 15 years as a center for Miami Heat and took the philanthropy route after retiring through his charity “Alonzo Mourning Charities.”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-883 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Alonzo-Mourning.jpg\" alt=\"alonzo-mourning\" width=\"594\" height=\"443\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Antawn Jamison - $70 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He was drafted fourth by the Toronto Raptors and was later traded to the Cleveland Cavaliers as part of a three-team, six-player trade. On August 28, 2013, he signed with the Los Angeles Clippers, and in October 2014, Jamison retired from professional basketball.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-884 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Antawn-Jamison.jpg\" alt=\"antawn-jamison\" width=\"587\" height=\"350\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tracy McGrady - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He was drafted into the NBA by the Raptors. Now retired, McGrady has deals with Adidas, and at one time he was featured on the cover of the NBA live.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-885 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tracy-McGrady.jpg\" alt=\"tracy-mcgrady\" width=\"562\" height=\"398\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Rasheed Wallace - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He played for the University of North Carolina before being drafted into the NBA in the year 1995 by the Washington Wizards. He retired in 2010 after 15 years in the NBA and again in 2013 after a brief comeback.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-886 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Rasheed-Wallace.jpg\" alt=\"Cleveland Cavaliers v Boston Celtics, Game 6\" width=\"606\" height=\"404\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Karl Malone - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Karl Malone is considered s one of the best power forward in the history of the NBA and was often referred to as “The Mailman” for his consistency delivery.  He played for Utah Jazz for 18 seasons before being signed by the Los Angeles Lakers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-887 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Karl-Malone.jpg\" alt=\"karl-malone\" width=\"614\" height=\"345\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jason Kidd - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He is the former player for the New York Knicks and now the head coach of the Milwaukee Bucks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-888 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jason-Kidd.jpg\" alt=\"jason-kidd\" width=\"565\" height=\"377\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tony Parker - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Parker played for the French Basketball League for two years before being drafted into the NBA in the year 2001. He was named the NBA Western Conference Player of the Month for the month of January 2013.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-889 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tony-Parker.jpg\" alt=\"tony-parker\" width=\"606\" height=\"341\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Chris Paul - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Chris Paul is one of the highest-paid athletes in the world.  He has huge endorsement deals with companies like State Farm and Nike.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-895 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Chris-Paul.jpeg\" alt=\"chris-paul\" width=\"572\" height=\"382\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Dikembe Mutombo - $75 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Dikembe is one of the most admired shot blockers and defensive players of all time. He is an eight-time All-Star and was elected into three All-NBA and six All-Defensive Teams.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-896 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Dikembe-Mutombo.jpg\" alt=\"NBA and UNICEF Launch Campaign for &quot;Unite for Children, Unite against AIDS&quot;\" width=\"609\" height=\"342\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Chris Webber - $80 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>As one of the former members of ‘Fab 5’, Webber had a prolific NBA career. He played in five All-Star games. Today, he works as an analyst on a TV as he enjoys the accumulated fortune.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-897 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Chris-Webber.jpg\" alt=\"chris-webber\" width=\"609\" height=\"405\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Pat Riley - $80 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The decorated, former Los Angeles Lakers player has been working as the Miami Heat team president since he retired. He has gone on to win NBA coach of the year for a cool three times.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-901 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pat-Riley.jpg\" alt=\"pat-riley\" width=\"604\" height=\"533\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Juwan Howard - $80 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Howard went into history books as the first NBA player to sign a contract worth $100 million. The retired professional basketball player works as an assistant coach for the Miami Heat. He has appeared in television shows and films.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-902 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Juwan-Howard.jpg\" alt=\"juwan-howard\" width=\"612\" height=\"344\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Carmelo Anthony - $ 80 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>He is a four times member of the USA Olympic basketball team, winning gold medals at 2008, 2012, and 2016 Olympics.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-907 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Carmelo-Anthony.jpg\" alt=\"carmelo-anthony\" width=\"557\" height=\"353\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Patrick Ewing - $85 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The renowned Hall-of-Fame player spent most of his basketball career with the New York Knicks. The Jamaican-American star was the main starting center for the Knicks. He had a short spell at SuperSonics and Orlando Magic. Ewing is currently the Charlotte Hornets’ head coach.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-905 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Patrick-Ewing.jpg\" alt=\"patrick-ewing\" width=\"546\" height=\"438\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Dwyane Wade - $95 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Dwyane Wade sent shock waves throughout the NBA by leaving Miami Heat after 13 seasons and three championships for $47.5 million. He scored six points in his debut with the Chicago Bulls.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-906 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Dwyane-Wade.jpg\" alt=\"dwyane-wade\" width=\"572\" height=\"380\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Steve Nash - $95 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>While playing for the Phoenix Suns, the Canadian point guard had a bright career: he was named twice as the NBA MVP. He is a consultant on player development for the Golden State Warriors and also the Canadian national team general manager.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-908\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Steve-Nash.jpg\" alt=\"steve-nash\" width=\"613\" height=\"404\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ray Allen - $100 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Allen shocked the NBA world recently with a hint for a possible comeback. The 41-year-old legend has played for Boston Celtics, Milwaukee Bucks, Miami Heat and Seattle SuperSonics.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-909 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Ray-Allen.jpg\" alt=\"ray-allen\" width=\"605\" height=\"399\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Dirk Nowitzki - $120 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Just recently, the German basketball star re-signed a staggering $50 million contract extension with the Dallas Mavericks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-910 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Dirk-Nowitzki.jpg\" alt=\"dirk-nowitzki\" width=\"589\" height=\"420\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Dwight Howard - $100 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Howard is a living legend in the game! He recently signed a new deal with Atlanta Hawks from Houston Rockets in less than a month ago. He lives to see his career compete with his bank account.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-911 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dwight-howard.jpg\" alt=\"dwight-howard\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Yao Ming - $120 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Ming lives as China’s most celebrated athlete. He swept sponsorship deals with many popular brands. As a rookie NBA player, the Chinese star was known for his role in ‘The Year of the Yao’ documentary. He is now a retired player.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-912 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Yao-Ming.jpg\" alt=\"yao-ming\" width=\"557\" height=\"485\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tim Duncan - $130 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Duncan spent his entire 19-year NBA career with the San Antonio Spurs as a power forward. He is said to have a dream of becoming a swimmer before he started playing basketball in 9th grade.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-913 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tim-Duncan.jpg\" alt=\"NBA: Playoffs-San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Clippers\" width=\"616\" height=\"385\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Gary Payton - $130 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Payton left a lasting mark in the history of NBA. He has lived to be one of the best point guards in the game. The retired Seattle SuperSonics point guard went into history books as the only point guard to have ever won the NBA Defensive Player of the Year award.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-904 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Gary-Payton-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"gary-payton\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Steph Curry - $175 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The high-flying Golden States player is worth enough to afford comfort. He was instrumental in the Golden States’ fight to the Finals in the last NBA championship.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-903\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Steph-Curry-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"steph-curry\" width=\"603\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Grant Hill - $180 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Hill has had a great basketball career. He has played for Phoenix Suns, Detroit Pistons, Los Angeles Clippers, and Orlando Magic. He has two children, married and happily collecting African American art.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-900 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Grant-Hill.jpg\" alt=\"grant-hill\" width=\"601\" height=\"420\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kevin Garnett - $180 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Currently playing a power forward for the Minnesota Timberwolves, Garnett lives a happy family life. He has two daughters and married.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-899 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kevin-Garnett.jpg\" alt=\"kevin-garnett\" width=\"608\" height=\"405\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Hakeem Olajuwon - $200 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Olajuwon played for Houston Rockets and the Toronto Raptors as a center. The Nigerian-American won two NBA championships with the Rockets in 1994 and 1995. He is regarded as one of the best centers in the game.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-898 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Hakeem-Olajuwon.jpg\" alt=\"hakeem-olajuwon\" width=\"602\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lebron James - $270 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>James led the CAVs to win their last NBA championship taking his tally to three championships. The overachieving player has four NBA MVP awards to his name and truly sits on a huge fortune.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-894 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Lebron-James.jpg\" alt=\"Cavaliers Mavericks Basketball\" width=\"589\" height=\"392\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kobe Bryant - $260 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The world has lived to celebrate Kobe, famously known as ‘The Black Mamba.\' He is one of the most referenced athletes. For two decades, Kobe played for Los Angeles Lakers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-893 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kobe-Bryant.jpg\" alt=\"kobe-bryant\" width=\"601\" height=\"393\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Shaquille O’Neal - $350 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The retired basketball professional player was nicknamed ‘Shaq.\' He is now an analyst in the ‘Inside the NBA’ sports show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-892 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Shaquille-ONeal.jpg\" alt=\"shaquille-oneal\" width=\"586\" height=\"396\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Magic Johnson - $500 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Johnson has a star on the Hollywood walk of fame. He is one of the richest NBA players around the globe. He played for the Los Angeles Lakers as a point guard before retiring.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-890 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Magic-Johnson.jpg\" alt=\"magic-johnson\" width=\"589\" height=\"456\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Michael Jordan - $1.1 Billion</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Michael Jordan is true NBA legend. The decorated NBA professional player sealed enormous endorsements through his career. These added to his skillful play that attracted huge sums pushing his worth through the roof.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-891\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Michael-Jordan.jpg\" alt=\"michael-jordan\" width=\"597\" height=\"398\" />','NBA Bank Accounts You Won’t Believe','','publish','open','open','','nba-bank-accounts-you-wont-believe','','','2016-10-27 22:13:00','2016-10-27 22:13:00','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/?p=873',0,'post','',0),(874,1,'2016-10-27 21:43:50','2016-10-27 21:43:50','','reggie-miller','','inherit','open','closed','','reggie-miller','','','2016-10-27 21:43:50','2016-10-27