omfort. He was instrumental in the Golden States’ fight to the Finals in the last NBA championship.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-903\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Steph-Curry-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"steph-curry\" width=\"603\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Grant Hill - $180 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Hill has had a great basketball career. He has played for Phoenix Suns, Detroit Pistons, Los Angeles Clippers, and Orlando Magic. He has two children, married and happily collecting African American art.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-900 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Grant-Hill.jpg\" alt=\"grant-hill\" width=\"601\" height=\"420\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kevin Garnett - $180 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Currently playing a power forward for the Minnesota Timberwolves, Garnett lives a happy family life. He has two daughters and married.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-899 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kevin-Garnett.jpg\" alt=\"kevin-garnett\" width=\"608\" height=\"405\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Hakeem Olajuwon - $200 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Olajuwon played for Houston Rockets and the Toronto Raptors as a center. The Nigerian-American won two NBA championships with the Rockets in 1994 and 1995. He is regarded as one of the best centers in the game.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-898 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Hakeem-Olajuwon.jpg\" alt=\"hakeem-olajuwon\" width=\"602\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Lebron James - $270 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>James led the CAVs to win their last NBA championship taking his tally to three championships. The overachieving player has four NBA MVP awards to his name and truly sits on a huge fortune.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-894 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Lebron-James.jpg\" alt=\"Cavaliers Mavericks Basketball\" width=\"589\" height=\"392\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kobe Bryant - $260 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The world has lived to celebrate Kobe, famously known as ‘The Black Mamba.\' He is one of the most referenced athletes. For two decades, Kobe played for Los Angeles Lakers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-893 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kobe-Bryant.jpg\" alt=\"kobe-bryant\" width=\"601\" height=\"393\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Shaquille O’Neal - $350 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The retired basketball professional player was nicknamed ‘Shaq.\' He is now an analyst in the ‘Inside the NBA’ sports show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-892 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Shaquille-ONeal.jpg\" alt=\"shaquille-oneal\" width=\"586\" height=\"396\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Magic Johnson - $500 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Johnson has a star on the Hollywood walk of fame. He is one of the richest NBA players around the globe. He played for the Los Angeles Lakers as a point guard before retiring.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-890 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Magic-Johnson.jpg\" alt=\"magic-johnson\" width=\"589\" height=\"456\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Michael Jordan - $1.1 Billion</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Michael Jordan is true NBA legend. The decorated NBA professional player sealed enormous endorsements through his career. These added to his skillful play that attracted huge sums pushing his worth through the roof.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-891\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Michael-Jordan.jpg\" alt=\"michael-jordan\" width=\"597\" height=\"398\" />','NBA Bank Accounts You Won’t Believe','','inherit','closed','closed','','873-autosave-v1','','','2016-10-27 22:04:51','2016-10-27 22:04:51','',873,'http://feelsyoung.com/873-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(916,1,'2016-10-28 09:27:21','2016-10-28 09:27:21','<h3>Wondering how much pastors make? They travel internationally and some own some of the best properties in the world, we have found a list of the richest pastors whose millionaire status will surely shock you!</h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Louis Farrakhan $3 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Known best for his Million Man March in Washington D.C, Farrakhan is a reputed religious and political leader. He heads mosques in Boston and Harlen. He has held various leadership programs for the Islam Nation and has written a number of books.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-917 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Louis-Farrakhan.jpg\" alt=\"louis-farrakhan\" width=\"594\" height=\"396\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Charles E. Blake $230,000</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The California Bishop was reported to earn close to $900,000 annually. His net worth went down with his dwindling popularity.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-918 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Charles-E.-Blake.jpg\" alt=\"charles-e-blake\" width=\"588\" height=\"433\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Robert Tilton $500,000</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At some point, the renowned televangelist earned $80 million yearly through his Success-N-Life infomercial. Tilton was accused of taking advantage of the vulnerable people.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-919 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Robert-Tilton.jpg\" alt=\"robert-tilton\" width=\"552\" height=\"436\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Paul Cain $1Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 18 years, Cain became a minister in Europe for the Voice of Healing Revival back in the 40s. He has made a fortune while struggling with homosexuality and alcoholism problems.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-920\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Paul-Cain.jpg\" alt=\"paul-cain\" width=\"536\" height=\"382\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Charles Stanley $1.5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Stanley became a minister at the age of 14 years. He owns a worldwide radio network and TV program. He has a Master of Theology, Doctor of Theology, and Master of Divinity. He founded the In Touch Ministries that makes a whopping $73 million while he pockets only $125,000 a year.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-921 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Charles-Stanley.jpg\" alt=\"charles-stanley\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jimmy Swaggart $1.5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The renowned priest has been on the airwaves since the 1980s. He was ordained in the 50s and has had an hour-long television show over the weekend. It was aired on more than 200 networks. Additionally, he had an AM radio broadcast. Swaggart has lived beyond his thick times during a sex scandal in the 90s; he has built a million dollar home through ministry a loan.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-922 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jimmy-Swaggart.jpg\" alt=\"jimmy-swaggart\" width=\"634\" height=\"408\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Leroy Jenkins $4 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>After his 12 years in prison, for arson, Jenkins married a 77-year-old woman who swept a $6 million lottery. Shortly after the wedding, his wife died, and he opened the Leroy Jenkins Ministries. He was investigated for miracle water that contained coliform bacteria. He later moved to Scottsdale, Arizona. He sells gospel albums and practices international televangelists.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-923 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Leroy-Jenkins.jpg\" alt=\"leroy-jenkins\" width=\"537\" height=\"393\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tony Campolo $4 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Campolo is a known to be close to the Democratic Party. He was Bill Clinton’s spiritual advisor. The ordained Baptist minister is open to the members of the LBGTQ. He has featured in hit shows like ‘Larry King Live’ and ‘The Colbert Night.’</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-924 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tony-Campolo.jpg\" alt=\"tony-campolo\" width=\"534\" height=\"381\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Al Sharpton $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The former James Brown’s tour manager is a renowned civil rights activist and religious leader. It is argued that he was ordained at 9 years as a Pentecostal minister. Since the 1980s, Al Sharpton has appeared on TV and radio shows as a Baptist minister.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-926 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Al-Sharpton.jpg\" alt=\"al-sharpton\" width=\"559\" height=\"374\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong> John Hagee $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Hagee opened the Cornerstone Church in San Antonio, Texas. This was after starting the John Hagee Ministries. He is widely followed with over 150 million households following him globally. Hagee is the CEO of Christian Evangelism Television, a non-profit organization.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-927 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/John-Hagee-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"john-hagee\" width=\"604\" height=\"340\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Joseph Prince $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Prince founded the New Creation Church in Asia. The widely followed minister earns just $550,000 a year while his church makes millions.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-928 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Joseph-Prince-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"joseph-prince\" width=\"603\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Bishop Eddie Long $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Under the leadership of Bishop Eddie Long, the New Missionary Baptist Church in Georgia has gained a cool 25,000 members. However, tax fraud and domestic abuse are some of the personal issues that caused her scrutiny.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-933 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Bishop-Eddie-Long.jpg\" alt=\"bishop-eddie-long\" width=\"598\" height=\"336\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Bishop Noel Jones $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Noel is a Ph.D. holder who has led his City of Refuge Sanctuary Choir to sell a chart-topping album in 2007. In 2013, he started a television show ‘Preachers of L.A.’</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-934 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Bishop-Noel-Jones.jpg\" alt=\"bishop-noel-jones\" width=\"603\" height=\"412\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Paula White $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the mid-80s, Paula White became a Christian after a tough childhood: her mother turned to alcohol upon her father’s suicide. Paula launched her own church called New Destiny Christian Center Orlando, Florida. Paula White Today is her television show. Her humanitarian service has earned her awards. Jonathan Cain is her second marriage.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-935 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Paula-White.jpg\" alt=\"paula-white\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Franklin Graham $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The son of Pastor Billy Graham was born William Graham III. He has made a name for himself for Billy Graham Evangelistic Association and Samaritan’s Purse.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-936 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Franklin-Graham.jpg\" alt=\"franklin-graham\" width=\"611\" height=\"368\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kenneth Copeland $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Best known for his ‘prosperity gospel’ way of preaching, Copeland is the charismatic movement leader. Before becoming a pastor, Kenneth used to be a pilot and a recording artist. He has several church-owned assets and property like an airstrip, jet, and lakefront mansion.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-940 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kenneth-Copeland.jpg\" alt=\"kenneth-copeland\" width=\"601\" height=\"401\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kay Arthur $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Before giving her life to Christ, Arthur saw her husband commit suicide when she left him and then she went for a married man for two years. With her new husband on a Mexican missionary, Arthur founded Precept Ministries International. She has written a number of Bible Studies and books.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-941 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kay-Arthur.jpg\" alt=\"kay-arthur\" width=\"563\" height=\"422\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Peter Popoff $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In 1946, Popoff fled Berlin to California with his family. Before starting his TV ministry in the 1970s, he studied at the University of California. He became a popular faith healer through his aggressive and energetic power. He is known for curing depression, paralysis, and heart problems on TV. He was once questioned as a fake. In 2007, he bought a $4.5 million home in California.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-943 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Peter-Popoff.jpg\" alt=\"peter-popoff\" width=\"600\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Juanita Bynum $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Juanita is a regular on TBN; she is a renowned gospel singer, writer, empowerment coach, Pentecostals televangelist, and actress. She has hosted a number of women conferences such as the ‘Woman, Thou Art Loosed’ in 1999, Atlanta. It was attended by over 52,000 people. She is the CEO of Juanita Bynum Enterprises.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-944 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Juanita-Bynum.jpg\" alt=\"juanita-bynum\" width=\"588\" height=\"426\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jesse Jackson $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>His unshaken civil rights activism has made a name for Jesse. He became a Baptist minister in 1968 and focused on the political runs of 1984 and 1988. He had ‘Both Sides of Jesse Jackson’ show on CNN.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-945 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jesse-Jackson.jpg\" alt=\"jesse-jackson\" width=\"581\" height=\"388\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ed Young, Jr. $11 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Ed Young, Jr. followed his father’s church life. He has authored the New York Times best-selling book ‘The Sexperiment.’ Over 5,000 weekly followers crown his position as the E! Channel, he joined Ed Young Television Network.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-948 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Ed-Young-Jr.jpg\" alt=\"ed-young-jr\" width=\"617\" height=\"347\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>John MacArthur $12 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Christian evangelical preacher was ordained in the ‘60s. In 1977, MacArthur started an international broadcast in Baltimore, Maryland. He went on to build his Los Angeles College in 1986.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-951 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/John-MacArthur.jpg\" alt=\"john-macarthur\" width=\"564\" height=\"329\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ernest Angley $13 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 18, Angley became a Christian. He managed to raise sufficient cash to buy Grace Cathedral in Ohio as well as the channel 55 TV station while he had only a Bible and a tent. The nationwide Ernest Angley Hour has helped him buy Boeing 747 for aid and mission transports.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-952 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Ernest-Angley.jpg\" alt=\"ernest-angley\" width=\"516\" height=\"449\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Cindy Trimm $15 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 30, Trimm was a senator. She traveled the world to rebuild towns through ministry. She has offered spiritual growth, written books and given sermons. She is now a Florida Embassy Worship Center pastor.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-953\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Cindy-Trimm-1024x620.jpg\" alt=\"cindy-trimm\" width=\"615\" height=\"373\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ernie Fletcher $16 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Flecther has been in the U.S. Air Force, medicine and House of Representatives. When he endorsed a death warrant for a criminal, he had a conflict of religious and political interests.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-954 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Ernie-Fletcher.jpg\" alt=\"ernie-fletcher\" width=\"566\" height=\"378\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Bishop T.D. Jakes $18 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At The Potters’ House, T.D. Jakes has a following of over 30,000 as a Dallas minister. He has over 50 outreach ministries, a $1.7 million mansion and a family of 5 children.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-950 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Bishop-T.D.-Jakes.jpg\" alt=\"bishop-t-d-jakes\" width=\"609\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kirk Cameron $20 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>His role on ‘Growing Pains’ is kirk’s brand. The famous actor in the ‘80s is a radical Christian pastor. Together with his wife, they operate a free camp for children who have terminal diseases. He received the National Religious Broadcasters’ Best Program Award for two consecutive years.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-949 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kirk-Cameron.jpg\" alt=\"kirk-cameron\" width=\"596\" height=\"398\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Billy Graham $25 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Billy Graham is one of the Southern Baptist leaders’ most famous of all time. He was a spiritual advisor to many presidents. For more than 55 times, he featured in the Gallup’s Most Admired Men and Women list. His civil rights activism is best known for his stand with Martin Luther King Jr. in New York. Over his 60 years of services, he has touched over 2.2 billion people.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-947 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Billy-Graham.jpg\" alt=\"billy-graham\" width=\"604\" height=\"340\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Rick Warren $25 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Warren is in charge of one of the mega churches in the U.S. When he gave President Obama’s invocation at his 2009 inauguration; Warren became famous worldwide.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-946 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Rick-Warren.jpg\" alt=\"rick-warren\" width=\"557\" height=\"372\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Joyce Meyer $25 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Meyer is one of the most influential evangelicals. She is a teacher, an author and a motivational speaker who got saved due to child abuse. She owns a private jet and various homes.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-942 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Joyce-Meyer.jpg\" alt=\"joyce-meyer\" width=\"602\" height=\"502\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Creflo Dollar $27 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The founder of the World Changers Church International, Creflo Dollar, has grown from 8 members to over 8,500 church capacity leader. He owns Arrow Records, Creflo Dollar Ministries, and Creflo Dollar Ministerial Associates.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-939 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Creflo-Dollar.jpg\" alt=\"creflo-dollar\" width=\"511\" height=\"511\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>John Danforth $35 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>First, Danforth was a senator and United Nations’ Ambassador. The ordained Episcopal priest is a part owner of the St. Louis Blues Hockey League. He gets most of his wealth from the family heir of stocks and real estate.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-938 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/John-Danforth.jpg\" alt=\"john-danforth\" width=\"601\" height=\"389\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Benny Hinn $42 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Israeli televangelist hosted healing summits in major cities and stadiums to earn his millions. He got enough to feed 100,000 children every year. During the Hurricane Katrina, he sent $100,000 to victims.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-937 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Benny-Hinn.jpg\" alt=\"benny-hinn\" width=\"462\" height=\"559\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Joel Olsteen $40 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The televangelist and author, Olsteen, is a pastor of Lakewood Church in Houston, Texas. This is the largest Protestant church in the U.S. His sermons are broadcast in over 100 countries.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-932 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Joel-Olsteen.jpg\" alt=\"joel-olsteen\" width=\"602\" height=\"331\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Chris Oyakhilome $50 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The founder of Believers’ Loveworld Incorporated, Pastor Chris is talented Nigerian minister. He claims to cure HIV among other claims.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-931 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Chris-Oyakhilome.jpg\" alt=\"chris-oyakhilome\" width=\"568\" height=\"379\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jan Crouch $100 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The daughter of a Georgia pastor, Crouch, is a co-founder of the industry’s biggest network together with her husband, Paul. TBN (Trinity Broadcasting Network) is bigger than Fox, CBS, and NBC. TBN has its own five individual networks. Her family is now caught up in several lawsuits after her death due to stroke in May 2016. She had a jet and a mobile home for her dogs.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-930 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jan-Crouch-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"jan-crouch\" width=\"613\" height=\"345\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Pat Robertston $100 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>This Southern Baptist minister created the Christian Broadcasting Network in Virginia. It is available in 180 countries. He once tried to run for the presidency. He raises money for political candidates that are conservative.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-929\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pat-Robertston.jpg\" alt=\"pat-robertston\" width=\"616\" height=\"331\" />','Richest Mega-Pastors in America','','publish','open','open','','richest-mega-pastors-in-america','','','2016-10-28 10:06:54','2016-10-28 10:06:54','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/?p=916',0,'post','',0),(917,1,'2016-10-28 08:24:44','2016-10-28 08:24:44','','louis-farrakhan','','inherit','open','closed','','louis-farrakhan','','','2016-10-28 08:24:44','2016-10-28 08:24:44','',916,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Louis-Farrakhan.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(918,1,'2016-10-28 08:25:16','2016-10-28 08:25:16','','charles-e-blake','','inherit','open','closed','','charles-e-blake','','','2016-10-28 08:25:16','2016-10-28 08:25:16','',916,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Charles-E.-Blake.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(919,1,'2016-10-28 08:25:40','2016-10-28 08:25:40','','robert-tilton','','inherit','open','closed','','robert-tilton','','','2016-10-28 08:25:40','2016-10-28 08:25:40','',916,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Robert-Tilton.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(920,1,'2016-10-28 08:26:07','2016-10-28 08:26:07','','paul-cain','','inherit','open','closed','','paul-cain','','','2016-10-28 08:26:07','2016-10-28 08:26:07','',916,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Paul-Cain.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(921,1,'2016-10-28 08:28:01','2016-10-28 08:28:01','','charles-stanley','','inherit','open','closed','','charles-stanley','','','2016-10-28 08:28:01','2016-10-28 08:28:01','',916,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Charles