ctices international televangelists.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-923 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Leroy-Jenkins.jpg\" alt=\"leroy-jenkins\" width=\"537\" height=\"393\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tony Campolo $4 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Campolo is a known to be close to the Democratic Party. He was Bill Clinton’s spiritual advisor. The ordained Baptist minister is open to the members of the LBGTQ. He has featured in hit shows like ‘Larry King Live’ and ‘The Colbert Night.’</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-924 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tony-Campolo.jpg\" alt=\"tony-campolo\" width=\"534\" height=\"381\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Al Sharpton $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The former James Brown’s tour manager is a renowned civil rights activist and religious leader. It is argued that he was ordained at 9 years as a Pentecostal minister. Since the 1980s, Al Sharpton has appeared on TV and radio shows as a Baptist minister.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-926 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Al-Sharpton.jpg\" alt=\"al-sharpton\" width=\"559\" height=\"374\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong> John Hagee $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Hagee opened the Cornerstone Church in San Antonio, Texas. This was after starting the John Hagee Ministries. He is widely followed with over 150 million households following him globally. Hagee is the CEO of Christian Evangelism Television, a non-profit organization.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-927 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/John-Hagee-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"john-hagee\" width=\"604\" height=\"340\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Joseph Prince $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Prince founded the New Creation Church in Asia. The widely followed minister earns just $550,000 a year while his church makes millions.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-928 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Joseph-Prince-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"joseph-prince\" width=\"603\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Bishop Eddie Long $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Under the leadership of Bishop Eddie Long, the New Missionary Baptist Church in Georgia has gained a cool 25,000 members. However, tax fraud and domestic abuse are some of the personal issues that caused her scrutiny.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-933 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Bishop-Eddie-Long.jpg\" alt=\"bishop-eddie-long\" width=\"598\" height=\"336\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Bishop Noel Jones $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Noel is a Ph.D. holder who has led his City of Refuge Sanctuary Choir to sell a chart-topping album in 2007. In 2013, he started a television show ‘Preachers of L.A.’</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-934 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Bishop-Noel-Jones.jpg\" alt=\"bishop-noel-jones\" width=\"603\" height=\"412\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Paula White $5 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the mid-80s, Paula White became a Christian after a tough childhood: her mother turned to alcohol upon her father’s suicide. Paula launched her own church called New Destiny Christian Center Orlando, Florida. Paula White Today is her television show. Her humanitarian service has earned her awards. Jonathan Cain is her second marriage.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-935 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Paula-White.jpg\" alt=\"paula-white\" width=\"590\" height=\"332\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Franklin Graham $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The son of Pastor Billy Graham was born William Graham III. He has made a name for himself for Billy Graham Evangelistic Association and Samaritan’s Purse.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-936 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Franklin-Graham.jpg\" alt=\"franklin-graham\" width=\"611\" height=\"368\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kenneth Copeland $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Best known for his ‘prosperity gospel’ way of preaching, Copeland is the charismatic movement leader. Before becoming a pastor, Kenneth used to be a pilot and a recording artist. He has several church-owned assets and property like an airstrip, jet, and lakefront mansion.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-940 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kenneth-Copeland.jpg\" alt=\"kenneth-copeland\" width=\"601\" height=\"401\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Kay Arthur $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Before giving her life to Christ, Arthur saw her husband commit suicide when she left him and then she went for a married man for two years. With her new husband on a Mexican missionary, Arthur founded Precept Ministries International. She has written a number of Bible Studies and books.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-941 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Kay-Arthur.jpg\" alt=\"kay-arthur\" width=\"563\" height=\"422\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Peter Popoff $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In 1946, Popoff fled Berlin to California with his family. Before starting his TV ministry in the 1970s, he studied at the University of California. He became a popular faith healer through his aggressive and energetic power. He is known for curing depression, paralysis, and heart problems on TV. He was once questioned as a fake. In 2007, he bought a $4.5 million home in California.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-943 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Peter-Popoff.jpg\" alt=\"peter-popoff\" width=\"600\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Juanita Bynum $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Juanita is a regular on TBN; she is a renowned gospel singer, writer, empowerment coach, Pentecostals televangelist, and actress. She has hosted a number of women conferences such as the ‘Woman, Thou Art Loosed’ in 1999, Atlanta. It was attended by over 52,000 people. She is the CEO of Juanita Bynum Enterprises.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-944 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Juanita-Bynum.jpg\" alt=\"juanita-bynum\" width=\"588\" height=\"426\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Jesse Jackson $10 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>His unshaken civil rights activism has made a name for Jesse. He became a Baptist minister in 1968 and focused on the political runs of 1984 and 1988. He had ‘Both Sides of Jesse Jackson’ show on CNN.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-945 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Jesse-Jackson.jpg\" alt=\"jesse-jackson\" width=\"581\" height=\"388\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ed Young, Jr. $11 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Ed Young, Jr. followed his father’s church life. He has authored the New York Times best-selling book ‘The Sexperiment.’ Over 5,000 weekly followers crown his position as the E! Channel, he joined Ed Young Television Network.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-948 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Ed-Young-Jr.jpg\" alt=\"ed-young-jr\" width=\"617\" height=\"347\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>John MacArthur $12 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Christian evangelical preacher was ordained in the ‘60s. In 1977, MacArthur started an international broadcast in Baltimore, Maryland. He went on to build his Los Angeles College in 1986.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-951 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/John-MacArthur.jpg\" alt=\"john-macarthur\" width=\"564\" height=\"329\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Ernest Angley $13 Million</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 18, Angley became a Christian. He managed to raise sufficient cash to buy Grace Cathedral in Ohio as well as the channel 55 TV station while he had only a Bible and a tent. The nationwide Ernest Angley Hour has helped him buy Boeing 747 for