16-11-15 16:58:35','2016-11-15 16:58:35','',965,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/The-Mysterious-Theme-Song.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1033,1,'2016-11-15 17:03:01','2016-11-15 17:03:01','','larry-tates-sons-tragic','','inherit','open','closed','','larry-tates-sons-tragic','','','2016-11-15 17:03:01','2016-11-15 17:03:01','',965,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Larry-Tate’s-Son’s-Tragic.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1034,1,'2016-11-15 17:07:00','2016-11-15 17:07:00','<h3>It still remains a shock how “Bewitched” has remained in the limelight since it first aired back on September 17, 1964. The show might have lasted for only 8 seasons but the twitchy nose signature by Samantha remains an indelible mark in everyone’s memory. Even better, the show story was later made into a movie starring Will Farrell and Nicole Kidman. Since the NBC pilot order in October 2014, there has been a rumor on the TV show remake.</h3>\r\n<h3>There were stringent moves and efforts to conceal a number of issues regarding the TV show. However, there are a couple of things that could never be kept a secret, not forever. Below are 20 things you probably never knew about the “Bewitched” TV show.</h3>\r\n<h2><strong>The Revelation of Sol Saks’ Inspiration</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The “Bewitched” show’s creator, Sol Saks, created the show after watched the <em>I Married A Witch </em>and <em>Bell, Book and Candle </em>films. He modeled the pilot episode after these films. In a number of interviews, Saks expressed his confidence in lack of contradiction and no litigation since the “Bewitched” show was produced by Screen Gems, a company owned by Columbia Pictures and so were both movies.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-972 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bewitched-Creator-1024x527.png\" alt=\"bewitched-creator\" width=\"632\" height=\"325\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>“The Darrin Syndrome”</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Several actors played Darrin, Samantha’s husband. For instance, the switching of Dick York with Dick Sargent was a shocking move by the directors. It was done without warning or notice whatsoever. This was presumably done with the guts that the audience would never care or notice. It was later known as “The Darrin Syndrome.” For information, Dick York hard chronic back pain and thus left the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-973 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/The-Darrin-1024x517.jpg\" alt=\"the-darrin\" width=\"640\" height=\"323\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Other characters too were swapped</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>For most people, Darrin was the most, if not the only, switched character in the show. This is without the knowledge of many on the fact that actresses too were swapped for the Gladys Kravitz’s nosey neighbor role. This part was first played by Alice Pearce and later taken by Sandra Gould.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-974 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Darrin-Wasn’t-The-1024x526.jpg\" alt=\"darrin-wasnt-the\" width=\"640\" height=\"329\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Richard Crenna was almost a Darrin</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>As the pilot was searching for Samantha, Richard Sargent was close to signing for the role of Darrin Stephens. He was a young actor in those early days of the show casting. Crenna could have not been a serious consideration but who knows what could have happened to the show if he was chosen! Probably, the Darrin Syndrome would never have occurred.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-975 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Richard-Crenna.png\" alt=\"richard-crenna\" width=\"612\" height=\"415\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Elizabeth Montgomery played multiple roles and never replaced</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>While other characters were being switched, Montgomery never got replaced and in fact, she played as Serena – Samantha’s cousin.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-976 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Elizabeth-Montgomery.jpg\" alt=\"elizabeth-montgomery\" width=\"654\" height=\"495\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Then came Dick Sargent</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>During the 5<sup>th</sup> season of “Bewitched,” York was given some B-12 by a replacement doctor. It was during a lunch break after filming. He got a seizure and was rushed to the hospital. The show continued without Darrin since he never returned. This happened for a few episodes until the new Dick Sargent came in.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-977 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Enter-Dick-Sargent.jpg\" alt=\"enter-dick-sargent\" width=\"547\" height=\"415\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Then Came York</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Later, Richard Crenna got an offer to play the next Darrin, but again he was too busy and tied up with “The Real McCoys”, and so he missed out – again! The male lead role went to Dick York. Later, the role was taken up by Sargent. It is a question of speculation on whether or not the show would have lasted 8 seasons if he took the role.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-978 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/York-It-Is.jpg\" alt=\"york-it-is\" width=\"603\" height=\"452\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Why did Dick York leave?</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>While there was no explanation on the show as to why York departed, the actor had a good reason for his departure. While he was filming <em>Cordura, </em>York tore most of his right back muscles and they never recovered fully. He got pain medication but it was never a long-term solution.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-979 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Dick-York’s-Real.png\" alt=\"dick-yorks-real\" width=\"620\" height=\"460\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Elizabeth Montgomery\'s Real Life Pregnancies\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Elizabeth was pregnant for 3 times. She had her firstborn in July 1964. Two of her pregnancies were brought into the script by the producers. This saw the introduction of Adam and Tabitha to the Stephens family. Indeed, this enriched the TV family in a very natural way.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-980 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Elizabeth-Montgomery-2.png\" alt=\"elizabeth-montgomery-2\" width=\"615\" height=\"421\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The new Darrin Stephens – Dick York</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Samantha Stephens had a mortal husband, Darrin Stephens. Dick York played his role. Throughout the 60s, he was a beloved actor thanks to this role. In addition, his <em>Inherit the Wind </em>classic film in the 60s gave him a name. He would later carry his charm and looks into his future life.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-981 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Dick-York-As-Darrin-1024x723.jpg\" alt=\"dick-york-as-darrin\" width=\"576\" height=\"407\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anti-Aging Potion</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In her 60s, Elizabeth was truly a cool babe. She maintained her beauty even in her later years. Her secret must have been some anti-aging spell on herself.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-982 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Anti-Aging-Potion.png\" alt=\"anti-aging-potion\" width=\"621\" height=\"407\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Special Brooch</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In case you never knew, Agnes Moorehead wore a starburst brooch often. It was set with old-mine diamonds of 8.5 carats. The pin was admired by many including Montgomery. When Moorehead’s TV daughter passed on in 1974, she bequeathed it to her.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-983 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/A-Special-Brooch.jpg\" alt=\"a-special-brooch\" width=\"345\" height=\"504\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Terminal Cancer for Alice Pearce</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Alice Pearce passed away in March 1966; marking has disappearance from the “Bewitched” world. Four months before Alice landed her new role in the show, she got the cancer diagnosis. Unfortunately, even after the surgery, doctors informed her that her ovarian cancer was terminal. She kept this to herself and never told her coworkers about it.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-984 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Alice-Pearce-Cursed-With.png\" alt=\"alice-pearce-cursed-with\" width=\"609\" height=\"447\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Emmy Award</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Two months after Alice died, her contribution through her Gladys’ portrayal, she received the Emmy Award for the Outstanding Supporting Actress.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-985 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Emmy-Award-1024x598.jpeg\" alt=\"emmy-award\" width=\"640\" height=\"374\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Friends behind the Camera? Moorehead and York had bloomed one!</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Unlike their uneasy relationship on the show, Darrin and Endora – played by York and Moorehead respectively – were great friends off the camera. It is even understood that Moorehead was close to York than anyone else in the cast.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-986 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/York-and-Moorehead.png\" alt=\"york-and-moorehead\" width=\"651\" height=\"473\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>How about their Costumes?</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>According to Kasey Rogers, who played as Louise Tate, supporting actors had their own wardrobes. They would bring their own clothes a week prior to filming. They would then be cleaned and pressed by the wardrobe department.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-993 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/The-Truth-Behind.jpg\" alt=\"the-truth-behind\" width=\"639\" height=\"474\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Cold Shoulder</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When Dick Sargent came in to replace Dick York as Darrin Stephens in the show, Moorehead did not like. She used to admire York’s talent on the screen. In fact, in a number of episodes, there was no Darrin at all.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-994 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Cold-Shoulder.jpg\" alt=\"cold-shoulder\" width=\"576\" height=\"432\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Aunt Clara Collected</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>It might appear as a wonder how Aunt Clara was obsessed with door knobs… but did you know that it was based on Marion Lorne’s real-life obsession? You will be shocked to know that the actress had over 1,000 antique door openers she had collected.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-995 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Aunt-Clara-Actress-1024x955.jpg\" alt=\"aunt-clara-actress\" width=\"613\" height=\"572\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Samantha’s Magic</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Stagehands had to do an extra thing to deliver Samantha’s “magic.” In the 60s, there was no CGI that existed. For instance, the director would have to yell ‘Cut!’ as Montgomery stood with her arms up whenever Samantha need to tidy the living room up quickly. This would be an opportunity for the stagehand to remove the clutter. Crutch-like devices were used to help her keep her arms up for some time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-996 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Samantha’s-Magic.jpg\" alt=\"samanthas-magic\" width=\"570\" height=\"594\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>and that Auntie…</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Aunt Clara was known for her endearing to the Stephens, even with all this strangeness. Darrin despised her, just like most of the relatives to Samantha.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1024\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Endearing-Auntie.png\" alt=\"endearing-auntie\" width=\"640\" height=\"470\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Always Together</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>As a passenger on Pan Am Flight 103, Jonathan had a tragic accident: it exploded over the Scotland back in 1988. Two years later, David died from heart attack and both were buried together at the Hollywood Forever Cemetery.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-998 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Together-Forever.jpg\" alt=\"together-forever\" width=\"614\" height=\"461\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Black High School students at it!</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Christmas Episode on the “Sisters at Heart” was created by black students. It was created by 22 African-American 10<sup>th</sup> graders during an English class in Marcella Saunders. The episode had a great story but has recently been considered to be politically wrong – this is due to a number of actors appearing in blackface at some point.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-999 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/The-“Sisters-at-Heart”-Christmas-1024x576.png\" alt=\"the-sisters-at-heart-christmas\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Anti-Racism</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When Samantha casts a spell on a Darrin’s racist client, the plot is then coined. The client saw everyone, including himself, as having a black skin.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1000\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Anti-Racism-Intentions-1024x775.jpg\" alt=\"anti-racism-intentions\" width=\"640\" height=\"484\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Fate and Tragic Naming of Larry Tate’s Son</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>During the show, Larry and Louise Tate had a baby boy. David White requested that the kid be named as Jonathan. This was inspired by the actor’s real life son, Jonathan, whom he had raised as a single father after his wife’s death. She had died due to second pregnancy complications.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1033 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Larry-Tate’s-Son’s-Tragic.png\" alt=\"larry-tates-sons-tragic\" width=\"617\" height=\"455\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>…and Action!</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She would lower the arms and continue with the scene once the director yelled, “Action!”</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1005 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Action.png\" alt=\"action\" width=\"600\" height=\"713\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The Theme Song</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Many never knew this but the theme song for Bewitched had lyrics. They were, however, never sung over opening credits.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1032 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/The-Mysterious-Theme-Song-1024x568.png\" alt=\"the-mysterious-theme-song\" width=\"640\" height=\"355\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The wrong Obituary of Elizabeth Montgomery</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Montgomery never allowed too much of her private life into the public space. She was very privy with such information. Her age was published as 57 at the time of her death. What many do not know is that Elizabeth was 62 by then.</h3>\r\n<h3>A number of obituaries too listed Montgomery as single. This was wrong information since she never revealed the information to the public about her marriage to Robert Foxworth a few years earlier.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1013 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Elizabeth-Montgomery’s-Obituary-1024x576.png\" alt=\"elizabeth-montgomerys-obituary\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The perspective of Darrin</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The lyrics to a song from YouTube that Steve Lawrence was heard sing were written in Darrin’s perspective – if he only knew that his wife too was a witch.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1014 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Darrin’s-Perspective.jpg\" alt=\"darrins-perspective\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Inconsistencies in her Birth Certificate</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>There was a major inconsistency in her middle name. According to the birth certificate, her middle name was Victoria but the death certificate listed her as “Elizabeth A. Montgomery.” This was one of the least known birth certificate inconsistencies.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1015 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Birth-Certificate-Inconsistencies-1024x841.jpg\" alt=\"birth-certificate-inconsistencies\" width=\"640\" height=\"526\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Drunk on set</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In a number of cases, cast members were drunk and some were even filmed drunk. It went beyond the players to even the producers, such as William Asher. Various fan sites were born to log the number of times any episode a given character was noted to be drunk. The habit was truly pervasive.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1017 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Drunk-On-Set.png\" alt=\"drunk-on-set\" width=\"633\" height=\"472\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>You won’t believe the Drinking Habits</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>There are various nightclubs and bars mentioned in the Bewitched show. To show that the habit was slowly getting out of hand, here is a list of those bars: Purple Popsicle night club, The Diamond Slipper, Joe’s Bar and Grill, Happy Times Bar, Dundee’s Bar (that was referred to as “the best restaurant in town” by Darrin), Golden Spoon Restaurant, Hearthstone Bar/Restaurant, and Elbow Room Cocktail Lounge.</h3>\r\n<h3>When children were on set, the rules were supposedly stricter. To imitate the alcohol looks, actors would be advised to use iced tea. For instance, Dick Wilson often played a drunk in Bewitched. He can only be assumed to know the intense acting involved! The habit was truly record-breaking in the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1018 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Record-Breaking-Drinking.jpg\" alt=\"record-breaking-drinking\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Montgomery almost missed in the Show</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Tammy Grimes was Sol Saks’ favorite actress to take the lead witch role. Initially, the character was to be called Cassandra and not Samantha. Saks liked the fact that Grimes had an elfin appearance that was natural. Bill Asher and Sol Saks settled for Elizabeth for the series. From the original plans, she was not to make the cut.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1022 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Elizabeth-Montgomery-Almost-Didn’t-1.jpg\" alt=\"elizabeth-montgomery-almost-didnt\" width=\"437\" height=\"566\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>…indeed Cassandra was never to be</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>She auditioned for the original role but her contract with Screen Gems tied her down and could never take the job. This necessitated for the character to be renamed to Samantha.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1023 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Cassandra-Wasn’t-Meant-To-Be-997x1024.jpg\" alt=\"cassandra-wasnt-meant-to-be\" width=\"576\" height=\"591\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>The magic is here</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>For the “Bewitched” set, the house that was used for the “Gidget,” 1959 movie was copied in reverse and used. The interior and patio were a replica of another Gidget movie. The home’s façade too had appeared in “I Dream of Jeannie” and “Dennis the Menace” shows among others.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1031 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Home-Is-Where-The-Magic-Is.jpg\" alt=\"home-is-where-the-magic-is\" width=\"600\" height=\"457\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>No Personal Differences</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Both the “I Dream Of Jeannie” and “Bewitched” shows were based on gorgeous blonde women who had magical powers.  From the shows, Jeannie was a 2,000-year-old genie who fell in love with a NASA astronaut and both had a shared plot line then. However, Elizabeth never felt any personal issue with “I Dream Of Jeannie’s” Larry Hagman and Barbara Eden – who were the stars.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1030 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Nothing-Personal.jpg\" alt=\"nothing-personal\" width=\"447\" height=\"464\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Two Tabithas</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Originally, the Olsen twins, who were fraternal, were named Diane and Erin Murphy. They were cast to share Tabitha, Stephens’s daughter role.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1029 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Two-Tabithas.jpg\" alt=\"two-tabithas\" width=\"624\" height=\"417\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Be Natural</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When Erin took to acting, she quickly became a star of the show. She was used for close-up shots as well as speaking scenes. On the other hand, Diane was used for long shots.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1028 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/A-Natural.png\" alt=\"a-natural\" width=\"545\" height=\"408\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Witches at War</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Rumor has it that the debut of NBC’s “I Dream Of Jeannie” show a year after “Bewitched” on ABC never pleased Elizabeth Montgomery. Seems the rivalry in the networks went down to the shows and actors!</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1027 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/War-Of-The-Witches.jpg\" alt=\"war-of-the-witches\" width=\"610\" height=\"449\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Gladys Kravitz’s Hand-Me-Down</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The lot and its neighborhood of homes has been in use for close to half a decade. It can be recognized from a number of TV films and shows. Actually, this was often at the same time! The homes were officially known as “Blondie Street” after the movie serial that was based on adventures of Blondie and Dagwood Bumstead.)</h3>\r\n<h3>During “Bewithced”, the nosy neighbor to Samantha and Darrin, Mrs Kravitz was also living in the Patridge home. The show, “The Partridge Family” debuted before the “Bewitched” series ended its run. This shows that both the Kravitz and the Partridge shared a home.</h3>\r\n<h3>Living in a modern 2-story house that had a white picket fence, the Partridge family was so modern. In 1999, the fence was brought down and the front windows were replaced by bay windows in the “Bewitched” time. The front door was different in a little way. While facing the Partridge house, the next door home to the right was used in the “I Dream of Jeannie” as Jeannie and Major Nelson’s house. This home’s front yard was removed during “The Partridge Family”. Three feet of the yard were removed to widen the driveway so as to accommodate the bus. The original width has since been restored.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1021 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Gladys-Kravitz’s-Hand-Me-Down-1024x752.jpg\" alt=\"gladys-kravitzs-hand-me-down\" width=\"640\" height=\"470\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Confession Episode</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The “I Confess” episode was interrupted, where Darrin got upset with Samantha’s excessive use of her magic. He felt that Samantha would “out” herself if she continued that way.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1025 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/I-Confess-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"i-confess\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Montgomery Never Wiggled her Nose</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>From the show, Samantha used to wiggle her nose. In reality, the role’s actress, Elizabeth Montgomery, never did it. It was a camera trick. This was according to Erin Murphy – Tabitha, who played her daughter - only her upper lip that wiggled and not the nose. Others claimed the nose moved as her mouth did.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1026 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Samantha-Actress-Elizabeth-Montgomery-Never-Actually-Wiggled.jpg\" alt=\"samantha-actress-elizabeth-montgomery-never-actually-wiggled\" width=\"896\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Hocus Smoke</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Many of the “Bewitched” stars and guest stars were actually serious smokers. Elizabeth, for instance, was a chain smoker and so was Paul Lynde. Dick York used to blow 3 packs a day! Later, in some interview, Erin Murphy, the Tabitha character recalled her parents always insisting that smoking was bad but she wondered if it is the case, then why was everyone around smoking?</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1019 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Hocus-Smokus.jpg\" alt=\"hocus-smokus\" width=\"635\" height=\"486\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Great Character Cast</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>“Bewitched” had amazing, slew and quality unusual side characters. Uncle Arthur was such a character from the show. He was played by Paul Lynde. Lynde had appeared in the “I Dream Of Jeannie” for 3 times: one as an IRS agent, one as film director, and another as a NASA commander.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1016 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Great-Cast-of-CharactersGreat-Cast-of-Characters.jpg\" alt=\"great-cast-of-charactersgreat-cast-of-characters\" width=\"475\" height=\"404\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Dr. Bombay</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Stephens’ family doctor was a natural with doctor and was named Dr. Bombay. Bernard Fox portrayed his character and he used to show up with an outlandish costume. During the spin-off series “Tabitha”, he also made two appearances.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1006 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Dr.-Bombay.png\" alt=\"dr-bombay\" width=\"646\" height=\"446\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tragedy Over the Airwaves</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The assassination of Martin Luther King, Jr. in 1968 came down as a national tragedy. The sad news about the civil rights leader saw the interruption of the “Bewitched” show. Again, the first day of rehearsal for the show for Eerily coincided with President Kennedy’s assassination date in November 22, 1963.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1007 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Tragedy-Over-The-Airwaves-1024x776.png\" alt=\"tragedy-over-the-airwaves\" width=\"640\" height=\"485\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Actual Curse</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Some fans have a speculation of a real-life curse on the show. This is related to the unthinkable number of cast members who later died from cancer issues. While the sad statistic can hardly be tied to witchcraft, over 85% of the cast dying from the same issue raises doubts. Some have wondered whether unhealthy lifestyle was to blame.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1008 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/A-Real-Life-Curse.jpg\" alt=\"a-real-life-curse\" width=\"500\" height=\"629\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Doggone It</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In order to stay in Samantha’s home, Rodney decided to turn into a dog. He was older and professed his love to Samantha. Later, Darrin fell in love with the dog and Samantha was wondering the way to eliminate the dog. Drefuss went on to become a huge Hollywood star.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1009 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Doggone-It.jpg\" alt=\"doggone-it\" width=\"625\" height=\"457\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Weary witch</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>After the 5<sup>th</sup> season, Montgomery got tired of the “Bewitched” show. She was lured to stay with huge sums of money. However, in her last 3 seasons, it was clear she was not into it.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1010 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Weary-Witch.jpg\" alt=\"weary-witch\" width=\"566\" height=\"386\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Way to show them</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Montgomery had stopped wearing bras while filming by the time she was done with her Samantha role. It was in support for the women’s lib movement.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1011 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Way-To-Show-‘Em.jpg\" alt=\"way-to-show-em\" width=\"501\" height=\"373\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Richard Dreyfuss role</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>When he appeared on the “Man’s Best Friend” episode, Richard Dreyfuss had a shot in the TV roles. This was back in 1966. He played the Rodney character in it. This was a warlock that Samantha used to babysit while e was little.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1012 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Early-Richard-Dreyfuss-Role-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"early-richard-dreyfuss-role\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Elizabeth’s Magical transformation</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>While she got anything she wanted in the show, Montgomery was never as happy off-screen. She dated Dean Martin, Elvis, and Gary Cooper. She is rumored to have been drawn to abusive lovers by her ‘father complex’. She befriended JFK but it is not known if anything went down between them.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1004 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Elizabeth-Montgomery’s-Magical-Transformation.jpg\" alt=\"elizabeth-montgomerys-magical-transformation\" width=\"620\" height=\"616\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>More Tabitha</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>A spin-off called “Tabitha” was later introduced. The concept this time was on Tabitha, the Darrin and Samantha’s daughter. Failure to use the original Tabitha actress, Erin Murphy, was a disappointment to many fans thus not doing so well.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1003 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/More-Tabitha-Please.jpg\" alt=\"more-tabitha-please\" width=\"510\" height=\"382\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Tabitha’s Life after Bewitched</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Erin Murphy appeared in shows like “Lassie” and a lot of appearances on commercials. She also did some swimwear modeling. She worked as a makeup artist, director, stunt double, acting teacher, and motivational speaker as well as fashion stylist.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1002 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Tabitha’s-Post-Bewitched-Life-506x1024.jpg\" alt=\"tabithas-post-bewitched-life\" width=\"506\" height=\"1024\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Be-Twitched</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The director of “Bewitched,” William Asher, was Montgomery’s husband. He reveals how she would wriggle naturally in case she was nervous or frustrated.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1001 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Be-Twitched.jpg\" alt=\"be-twitched\" width=\"630\" height=\"354\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Poor Ratings for switching Darrin</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In the last 3 years, fans noticed the swapped Darrin. The ratings went under and for the fans, accepting the unfamiliar face was not an option.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-992 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Switching-Darrin-was-Bad-For-Ratings-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"switching-darrin-was-bad-for-ratings\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Secretary Switcharoo</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Various actresses played the Darrin’s secretary such as Marcia Wallace, who later voiced teacher Edna Krabappel in “The Simpsons.” She also played as the secretary to Bob Newhart in “The Bob Newhart Show” in the 70s.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-991 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Secretary-Switcharoo.jpg\" alt=\"secretary-switcharoo\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Bell, Book, and Candle</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>In <em>Bell, Book, and Candle</em>, Kim Novak, a blonde beauty played a witch that lived in modern New York City. It was an inspiration to the TV series according to Sol Saks.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-990 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bell-Book-and-Candle-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"bell-book-and-candle\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Similarities between Samantha and Serena</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>Both liked hanging with mere mortals. We cannot call her a swinger of the 60s but had some hippie tendencies. She was in favor of Samantha’s marriage to mortal but later ribs them for being less cool. Samantha and Serena were never filmed together in same scenes. They tried split-screen since the camera technology had not advanced. They tried using a double from the rear to show them both, which were played by Montgomery at the same time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-989 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Samantha-Serena-Similarities.jpg\" alt=\"samantha-serena-similarities\" width=\"582\" height=\"600\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Coincidental Birthdays</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>On the birthday of the twins playing Tabitha, June 17<sup>th</sup>, Montgomery gave birth to her actual daughter Rebecca Asher.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-988 alignleft\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Coincidental-Birthdays-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"coincidental-birthdays\" width=\"565\" height=\"424\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h2><strong>Dick York is dead</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>At 63, York died from emphysema complications. He is buried in Rockford, Michigan.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-987\" src=\"http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/RIP-Dick-York-1024x778.jpg\" alt=\"rip-dick-york\" width=\"640\" height=\"486\" />','Bewitched: Astonishing Facts Revealed About The Cast and Crew','','inherit','closed','closed','','965-revision-v1','','','2016-11-15 17:07:00','2016-11-15 17:07:00','',965,'http://feelsyoung.com/965-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1035,1,'2016-11-29 16:59:02','2016-11-29 16:59:02','http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/cropped-logo-small-favicon.png','cropped-logo-small-favicon.png','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-logo-small-favicon-png','','','2016-11-29 16:59:02','2016-11-29 16:59:02','',0,'http://feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/cropped-logo-small-favicon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1036,1,'2016-12-28 15:43:31','2016-12-28 15:43:31','<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>From Music Star to Gay Hero</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The gay star sold more than 100 million albums with his group and as a solo artist, becoming known for songs like Careless Whisper, Faith, and Last Christmas.</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1038\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/gay-hero-300x186.jpg\" alt=\"gay-hero\" width=\"545\" height=\"338\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><!--nextpage--></span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Time in Prison</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In September 2010 he received an eight-week sentence following an event the previous July in which he crashed his Range Rover into a shop in London. George was also banned from driving for five years after he pleaded guilty to driving under the influence of drugs.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1039\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/time-in-prison.jpg\" alt=\"time-in-prison\" width=\"543\" height=\"364\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Drug Possession</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In 2008 Michael took a step back from the public eye but less than a month later he was once again in the glare when he was cautioned for possession of class A drugs, which included crack cocaine, and class C drugs.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1040\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/drug-possession-300x206.jpg\" alt=\"drug-possession\" width=\"524\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>George’s Time in Rehab</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He sought solace in Australia’s Byron Bay rehab clinic with his then boyfriend Fad Fawaz to deal with emotional anxiety.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1041\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/rehab-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"rehab\" width=\"514\" height=\"355\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Rise to Fame</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael, who was set to release a documentary in 2017, rose to fame as a member of Wham!, known for their hits Last Christmas and Club Tropicana.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1042\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/fame-300x205.jpg\" alt=\"fame\" width=\"536\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2> <span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Hit Star to Gay Hero</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The struggle to establish his true identity took decades for Michael to develop. Publicly, Michael only announced his sexuality after a 1998 incident in a public bathroom in L.A., where he was arrested for “engaging in a lewd act” with a police officer.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1043\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/music-star-to-gay-star-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"music-star-to-gay-star\" width=\"534\" height=\"301\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>M1 Injury Incidence</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In May 2013, he was airlifted to hospital with a head injury following a bizarre incident on the M1. He spent several days in hospital the following year, after concerned friends dialed 999.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1044\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/frtgwdert-300x197.jpg\" alt=\"frtgwdert\" width=\"515\" height=\"338\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Death of his Partner</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael was devastated when his long-term partner Anselmo Feleppa died of a brain haemorrhage in 1993. Three years later, he met Kenny Goss whom they remained together till 2009.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1045\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/partner-300x250.jpg\" alt=\"partner\" width=\"517\" height=\"431\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Life-Threatening Pneumonia</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In 2011, George Michael stayed in a Vienna hospital due to a life-threatening bout of pneumonia. He later thanked the doctors who spend three weeks to keep him alive through the media.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1046\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/pneumonia-300x158.jpg\" alt=\"pneumonia\" width=\"522\" height=\"275\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Not New to Controversy</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In October 2006, George was found slumped over the wheel of his car. And in May 2007, he pleaded guilty to driving while unfit through drugs and was banned from driving for two years.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1047\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/injury-300x198.jpg\" alt=\"injury\" width=\"530\" height=\"350\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael\'s Philanthropy</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Among the charities he quietly aided included Macmillan Cancer Support, Childline, and the London-based HIV-awareness organization Terrence Higgins Trust. According to the Associated Press, Michael donated proceeds from the song \"<em>Jesus to a Child</em>\" to Childline.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1050\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/philanthropy-300x145.jpg\" alt=\"philanthropy\" width=\"579\" height=\"280\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Religious Views</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He was exposed to Protestant Christianity as a school-age youngster in England, but as he describes it, the religion didn’t have much of an impact on him: He praised England for being secular and criticized the United States for being too religious–something he saw as a threat to the gay community.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1051\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/religous-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"religous\" width=\"533\" height=\"300\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>George’s Father</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">His father, Kryriacos Panayiotou, is of Greek origin. He moved to England in the 1950s and changed his name to Jack Panos.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1052\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/dad-300x203.jpg\" alt=\"dad\" width=\"549\" height=\"371\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Health Problems</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">On October 2011, He cancelled a performance at London’s Royal Albert Hall due to a viral infection.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1053\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/pneumonia-health-issue-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"pneumonia-health-issue\" width=\"539\" height=\"359\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>His Boyfriend, Fadi Fawaz</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">It is believed that Fadi and George started dating when the gay start split with his long-term partner Kenny Goss in 2009. They have been together for over seven years. It was Fadi who discovered George’s body on 25<sup>th</sup> Decemeber, 2016. It is believed that Fadi will get nothing out of the massive $200 million estate, which is to be divided among George’s godchildren.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1054\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/boyfriend-300x220.jpg\" alt=\"George Michael spotted in Venice\" width=\"531\" height=\"389\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Assets</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He earned close to £48.5 million from his 25 live tours between 2006 and 2008. Sunday Times Rich List 2015 of the wealthiest British musicians estimated his net worth to be £105 million.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1057\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/assets-300x144.jpg\" alt=\"assets\" width=\"548\" height=\"263\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Relationships</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He had a relationship with a Chinese-American make-up artist Kathy Jeung, who appeared in the <em>I Want Your Sex </em>video. The relationship broke later after she knew of Michael’s bisexual orientation.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1060\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kathy-jeung.jpg\" alt=\"kathy-jeung\" width=\"521\" height=\"331\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>His Real Name</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Known professionally as George Michael, his really full name is Georgios kyriacos Panayiotou. He was an English singer, songwriter and producer who rose to fame as a member of the hit group Wham!</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1064\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/name-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"name\" width=\"523\" height=\"392\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">His Early Life</span></strong></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael aka Georgios Kyriacos Panayiotou, was born in Bushey, Hertfordshire in 1963 to a Greek Cypriot father and English mother, has sold more than 100m records to date.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1063\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/early-life-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"early-life\" width=\"509\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Godchildren</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He had godchildren whom it’s believed that the massive $200+ million estate will be divided among. Many of them offspring of fellow celebrity pals. Among those expected to get a share of the pop icon’s fortune include Roman and Harley Kemp — kids of Wham! bassist Martin Kemp, bandmate Shirlie Holliman and Spandau Ballet.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1062\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/godchildren.jpg\" alt=\"godchildren\" width=\"510\" height=\"328\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Tired and Bloated in His Last Days</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Final pictures of the iconic Wham! Singer shows the singer had put on weight in the last known images to have been taken of the gay star.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1061\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tired-and-bloated-in-his-last-days-300x186.jpg\" alt=\"tired-and-bloated-in-his-last-days\" width=\"504\" height=\"313\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Twenty Five and Concert Tours</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Twenty Five</em> was Michael\'s second greatest singles hits album, celebrating his 25th anniversary of music career. Released in November 2006, it debuted at no.1 on the charts in the UK. The album contains songs chiefly from Michael\'s solo career but also from his days in Wham!</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1059\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/live-tours-300x199.jpeg\" alt=\"George Michael \'\" width=\"529\" height=\"351\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">Political Views</span></strong></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael was an outspoken liberal view. He was a strong critic of for