 Battles</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael once fell out with Sony in 1994 and at great expense to himself in legal fees over a contract he described as \'professional slavery.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1048\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/legal-battle-300x190.jpg\" alt=\"legal-battle\" width=\"535\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n&nbsp;','25 Things You Didn’t Know About George Michael and His Death','','inherit','closed','closed','','1036-autosave-v1','','','2017-01-19 14:31:21','2017-01-19 14:31:21','',1036,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1036-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1067,1,'2016-12-28 15:45:41','2016-12-28 15:45:41','<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>From Music Star to Gay Hero</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The gay star sold more than 100 million albums with his group and as a solo artist, becoming known for songs like Careless Whisper, Faith, and Last Christmas.</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1038\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/gay-hero-300x186.jpg\" alt=\"gay-hero\" width=\"545\" height=\"338\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><!--nextpage--></span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Time in Prison</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In September 2010 he received an eight-week sentence following an event the previous July in which he crashed his Range Rover into a shop in London. George was also banned from driving for five years after he pleaded guilty to driving under the influence of drugs.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1039\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/time-in-prison.jpg\" alt=\"time-in-prison\" width=\"543\" height=\"364\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Drug Possession</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In 2008 Michael took a step back from the public eye but less than a month later he was once again in the glare when he was cautioned for possession of class A drugs, which included crack cocaine, and class C drugs.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1040\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/drug-possession-300x206.jpg\" alt=\"drug-possession\" width=\"524\" height=\"360\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>George’s Time in Rehab</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He sought solace in Australia’s Byron Bay rehab clinic with his then boyfriend Fad Fawaz to deal with emotional anxiety.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1041\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/rehab-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"rehab\" width=\"514\" height=\"355\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Rise to Fame</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael, who was set to release a documentary in 2017, rose to fame as a member of Wham!, known for their hits Last Christmas and Club Tropicana.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1042\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/fame-300x205.jpg\" alt=\"fame\" width=\"536\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2> <span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Hit Star to Gay Hero</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The struggle to establish his true identity took decades for Michael to develop. Publicly, Michael only announced his sexuality after a 1998 incident in a public bathroom in L.A., where he was arrested for “engaging in a lewd act” with a police officer.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1043\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/music-star-to-gay-star-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"music-star-to-gay-star\" width=\"534\" height=\"301\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>M1 Injury Incidence</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In May 2013, he was airlifted to hospital with a head injury following a bizarre incident on the M1. He spent several days in hospital the following year, after concerned friends dialed 999.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1044\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/frtgwdert-300x197.jpg\" alt=\"frtgwdert\" width=\"515\" height=\"338\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Death of his Partner</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael was devastated when his long-term partner Anselmo Feleppa died of a brain haemorrhage in 1993. Three years later, he met Kenny Goss whom they remained together till 2009.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1045\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/partner-300x250.jpg\" alt=\"partner\" width=\"517\" height=\"431\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Life-Threatening Pneumonia</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In 2011, George Michael stayed in a Vienna hospital due to a life-threatening bout of pneumonia. He later thanked the doctors who spend three weeks to keep him alive through the media.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1046\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/pneumonia-300x158.jpg\" alt=\"pneumonia\" width=\"522\" height=\"275\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Not New to Controversy</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In October 2006, George was found slumped over the wheel of his car. And in May 2007, he pleaded guilty to driving while unfit through drugs and was banned from driving for two years.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1047\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/injury-300x198.jpg\" alt=\"injury\" width=\"530\" height=\"350\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael\'s Philanthropy</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Among the charities he quietly aided included Macmillan Cancer Support, Childline, and the London-based HIV-awareness organization Terrence Higgins Trust. According to the Associated Press, Michael donated proceeds from the song \"<em>Jesus to a Child</em>\" to Childline.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1050\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/philanthropy-300x145.jpg\" alt=\"philanthropy\" width=\"579\" height=\"280\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Religious Views</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He was exposed to Protestant Christianity as a school-age youngster in England, but as he describes it, the religion didn’t have much of an impact on him: He praised England for being secular and criticized the United States for being too religious–something he saw as a threat to the gay community.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1051\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/religous-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"religous\" width=\"533\" height=\"300\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>George’s Father</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">His father, Kryriacos Panayiotou, is of Greek origin. He moved to England in the 1950s and changed his name to Jack Panos.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1052\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/dad-300x203.jpg\" alt=\"dad\" width=\"549\" height=\"371\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Health Problems</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">On October 2011, He cancelled a performance at London’s Royal Albert Hall due to a viral infection.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1053\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/pneumonia-health-issue-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"pneumonia-health-issue\" width=\"539\" height=\"359\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>His Boyfriend, Fadi Fawaz</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">It is believed that Fadi and George started dating when the gay start split with his long-term partner Kenny Goss in 2009. They have been together for over seven years. It was Fadi who discovered George’s body on 25<sup>th</sup> Decemeber, 2016. It is believed that Fadi will get nothing out of the massive $200 million estate, which is to be divided among George’s godchildren.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1054\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/boyfriend-300x220.jpg\" alt=\"George Michael spotted in Venice\" width=\"531\" height=\"389\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Assets</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He earned close to £48.5 million from his 25 live tours between 2006 and 2008. Sunday Times Rich List 2015 of the wealthiest British musicians estimated his net worth to be £105 million.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1057\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/assets-300x144.jpg\" alt=\"assets\" width=\"548\" height=\"263\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Relationships</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He had a relationship with a Chinese-American make-up artist Kathy Jeung, who appeared in the <em>I Want Your Sex </em>video. The relationship broke later after she knew of Michael’s bisexual orientation.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1060\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/kathy-jeung.jpg\" alt=\"kathy-jeung\" width=\"521\" height=\"331\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>His Real Name</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Known professionally as George Michael, his really full name is Georgios kyriacos Panayiotou. He was an English singer, songwriter and producer who rose to fame as a member of the hit group Wham!</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1064\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/name-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"name\" width=\"523\" height=\"392\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">His Early Life</span></strong></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael aka Georgios Kyriacos Panayiotou, was born in Bushey, Hertfordshire in 1963 to a Greek Cypriot father and English mother, has sold more than 100m records to date.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1063\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/early-life-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"early-life\" width=\"509\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Godchildren</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He had godchildren whom it’s believed that the massive $200+ million estate will be divided among. Many of them offspring of fellow celebrity pals. Among those expected to get a share of the pop icon’s fortune include Roman and Harley Kemp — kids of Wham! bassist Martin Kemp, bandmate Shirlie Holliman and Spandau Ballet.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1062\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/godchildren.jpg\" alt=\"godchildren\" width=\"510\" height=\"328\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Tired and Bloated in His Last Days</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Final pictures of the iconic Wham! Singer shows the singer had put on weight in the last known images to have been taken of the gay star.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1061\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tired-and-bloated-in-his-last-days-300x186.jpg\" alt=\"tired-and-bloated-in-his-last-days\" width=\"504\" height=\"313\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Twenty Five and Concert Tours</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Twenty Five</em> was Michael\'s second greatest singles hits album, celebrating his 25th anniversary of music career. Released in November 2006, it debuted at no.1 on the charts in the UK. The album contains songs chiefly from Michael\'s solo career but also from his days in Wham!</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1059\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/live-tours-300x199.jpeg\" alt=\"George Michael \'\" width=\"529\" height=\"351\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">Political Views</span></strong></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael was an outspoken liberal view. He was a strong critic of former U.S. President George W. Bush and the Iraq War. His song “<em>Shoot The Dog</em>” is a direct attack on Bush and former UK Prime Minister Tony Blair’s comfy relationship.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1058\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/political-300x219.jpg\" alt=\"political\" width=\"514\" height=\"375\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Religion</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">He was exposed to Protestant Christianity as a school-age youngster in England, but as he describes it, the religion didn’t have much of an impact on him: He praised England for being secular and criticized the United States for being too religious.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1056\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/relion-300x168.jpg\" alt=\"relion\" width=\"521\" height=\"292\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Controversial “I<em> Want Your Sex” </em> Album</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael courted controversy with this album. Some radio stations in the US refused to play it due to its explicit content while others would only play it late at night.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1055\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/want-sex-300x198.jpg\" alt=\"want-sex\" width=\"503\" height=\"332\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Michael’s Comeback</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Trying to resurrect his career in the US, He made several appeared, and released <em>Twenty Five and</em> guest-stared on the TV series <em>Eli Stone</em> as a musical guardian angel of sorts.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1049\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/comeback-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"comeback\" width=\"495\" height=\"371\" /><!--nextpage--></span></h3>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Legal Battles</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Michael once fell out with Sony in 1994 and at great expense to himself in legal fees over a contract he described as \'professional slavery.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1048\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/legal-battle-300x190.jpg\" alt=\"legal-battle\" width=\"535\" height=\"339\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n&nbsp;','25 Things You Didn’t Know About George Michael and His Death','','inherit','closed','closed','','1036-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:45:41','2016-12-28 15:45:41','',1036,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1036-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1068,1,'2017-01-19 14:28:35','2017-01-19 14:28:35','<h1>30. 50 Cent – $155 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Discovered by Eminem and Dr. Dre, The G-Unit rapper debuted in 2003 with a 8x Platinum Album in \"Get Rich Or Die Tryin\'\". He has since released four more albums (which sold millions of copies themselves) and has appeared in numerous films. 50 Cent has also ventured into the business world and founded \"SMS Audio\", an electronics company selling headphones.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1064\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/name.jpg\" alt=\"name\" width=\"550\" height=\"413\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<ol start=\"29\">\r\n 	<li><strong> George Michael - $175 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe late British pop star has made his fortune selling more than 100 million records worldwide. Michael managed to maintain an extremely high net worth even while anonymously donating large amounts to charities for years.\r\nAfter his untimely death, Michael\'s last will caused controversy in regards to his children and his boyfriend.<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"28\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Usher - $180 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn all-round entrepreneur, Usher is credited as a singer, a songwriter, a dancer and as an actor, and is also renowned for discovering teen pop sensation Justin Bieber. He is a versatile businessman as well, and is a famous part-owner of the NBA\'s Cleveland Cavaliers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"27\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Lars Ulrich - $200 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most recognized drummers in the world, Lars Ulrich has made his fortunes playing with the infamous metal band Metallica. He has angered many music fans all around the world by leading the famous lawsuit against file-sharing website Napster. Ulrich enjoys spending large sums of his earnings on his expensive paintings collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"26\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Eminem - $210 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDr. Dre\'s incredibly successful protégé, Eminem has found success against all odds. His albums have all reached multi-platinum certifications, while in between, Eminem has managed to star in a biopic about his life, \"8 Mile\". The movie\'s title song, \"Lose Yourself\", has earned Eminem an Academy Award, making him the first Hip Hop artist to achieve the feat.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"25\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Ozzy Osbourne - $220 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\"The Godfather of Heavy Metal\" of Black Sabbath fame, Grammy Award winner Ozzy Osbourne has been an ever-present member of the industry for over 40 years.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"24\">\r\n 	<li><strong> David Bowie - $230 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPrior to his untimely death in 2016, British sensation David Bowie has been one of the music industry\'s most recognized and respected personas, with a career that spanned for almost 5 decades. Bowie has constantly changed and rewritten the rules of Rock and Roll, while also appearing in various films.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNet Worth: $230 Million.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"23\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Rod Stewart - $235 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRock icon Rod Stewart has been in the music business since the 1960\'s. He has found success being the front man in several bands before launching a solo career. His heavy touring schedule and various property investments add on to his already rich portfolio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"22\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Eric Clapton - $250 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nClapton rose to fame in the 1960\'s and never looked back since. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame after earning 18 Grammy Awards and selling millions of records worldwide, becoming one of the most influential guitarists of all time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"21\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Phil Collins - $260 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGaining fame as the drummer of British band Genesis, Phil Collins\' career has spanned almost 40 years. His earnings from Genesis only slightly surpass his earnings as a solo artist.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"20\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Roger Waters - $270 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSinger, songwriter and bassist Waters has been an integral part of legendary band Pink Floyd\'s success, writing most of the songs on the band\'s great album \"Dark Side of the Moon\", which has sold an estimated 45 million copies worldwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"19\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Dhani Harrison - $275 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe son of the late legendary Beatle George Harrison, Dhani Harrison was the sole inheritor of his father\'s estate, and therefore inherited all the wealth the late George Harrison had amassed over his prosperous career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"18\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Lady Gaga - $280 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDespite being in the scene for only roughly a decade, Lady Gaga has enjoyed incredible success, releasing critically acclaimed and commercially successful albums. Her immeasurable success and unorthodox appearance style made her a household name in the business.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"17\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jon Bon Jovi - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLead singer of successful, self-entitled rock band \"Bon Jovi\", Jon Bon Jovi is one of the best-selling artists of all time, selling over 130 million records worldwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"16\">\r\n 	<li><strong> L.A. Reid - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecord producer and executive L.A. Reid is the CEO of Epic Records, which is a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment. Reid is credited with launching the careers of several high profile artists; the list includes some very big names like Mariah Carey, Pink, Rihanna, Kanye West and Justin Bieber.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"15\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Sting - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSting started out as the singer and bassist for the band \"The Police\", but has since launched a long and incredibly successful solo career, over which he became a music icon.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"14\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Keith Richards - $340 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRock symbol Keith Richards made a career for himself being a part of legendary rock band \"The Rolling Stones\". He is widely considered to be one of the best guitarists in history, and fourteen of the songs he co-wrote with his bandmate Mick Jagger were selected by the Rolling Stone Magazine among the \"500 Greatest Songs of All Time\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"13\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Bruce Springsteen - $345 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKnown both as a rock icon and as a philanthropist and a humanitarian, Springsteen made his debut in 1973 and never looked back since. With 18 albums released and 20 Grammy Awards to his name, Springsteen is one of the industry\'s most prolific and successful artists. He is also a known supporter of and activist for LGBT rights.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"12\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Ringo Starr - $350 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBeing an integral part of the most successful band in history is highly profitable. Star has been the drummer of British band \"The Beatles\" from 1962 until the band\'s ultimate breakup. Since then has also maintained a solo career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"11\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Mick Jagger - $360 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMusician, singer, songwriter, dancer, actor, producer, legend – a lot can be said about Mick Jagger. The lead vocalist of \"The Rolling Stones\" has defined the rock scene in the 1960\'s and made his mark on rock – and on music – forever. He continues to tour with the Rolling Stones to this day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"10\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jimmy Buffet - $430 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFolk-country music singer and songwriter Jimmy Buffet has been in the business since the late 1960\'s, and his unique sound and style have helped him to enjoy incredible success. He is also a writer, writing 3 best-sellers, and a businessman, owning restaurant chains as well as a casino.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"9\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Elton John - $480 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSir Elton John is one of the most respected and celebrated artists of our time. With a career spanning over four decades, his music had become the soundtrack of many of his fans\' lives. Elton John has won it all – Grammy Awards, Brit Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award – and he has enjoyed the success and wealth that came with all of it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Emilio Estefan - $500 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSinger and producer Emilio Estefan has produced countless records that have topped the Latino charts. He has also appeared in films. Emilio and his wife Gloria own and manage a large number of high-end successful restaurants all throughout America.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jay Z - $550 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most successful rappers of all time, Jay Z has amassed a huge fortune for himself releasing multi-platinum albums as well as founding entertainment company \"Roc Nation\" and co-founding \"Roc-A-Fella Records\". He is also the co-creator of the \"Rocawear\" clothing line and the founder of sports agency \"Roc Nation Sports\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Madonna - $560 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMadonna has her hand in everything – singing, songwriting, acting, entrepreneurship – you name it. She has been in the limelight since the 1980\'s and shows no signs of slowing down even at the age of 58. She is recognized by the Guinness World Records as the best-selling female artist of all time. Her concerts have grossed over $1 billion over the course of her career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Dr. Dre - $700 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEmerging into the public eye as part of the controversial Hip Hop group NWA, Dr. Dre is now one of the most respected names in the Rap scene as well as in the music industry. His record label Aftermath Entertainment is responsible for launching the careers of mega-stars Eminem and 50 Cent. Dr. Dre is also the founder of headphone company Beats Audio, which was sold to Apple for an estimated $3 billion.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Sean Combs (P. Diddy) - $750 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecord producer, singer and businessman Sean Combs has reinvented himself countless times over the course of his career, and so he has managed to stay at the top of the music industry as a household name. Founder of successful record company \"Bad Boy Records\" and owner of his own clothing line \"Sean John\", Sean Combs\' fortune just keeps on rising.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Herb Alpert - $850 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHerb Alpert started in the 1960\'s as a part of the \"Herb Alpert and the Tijuana Grass\" jazz group, and went on to become one of the industry\'s most powerful executives.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Andrew Lloyd Webber – $1.2 Billion</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSir Andrew Lloyd Webber made his fortune composing musicals. Throughout his 50-year career Webber has composed some incredibly iconic music for operas such as \"The Phantom of the Opera\". His company, the Really Useful Group, is one of the largest and most successful theater operators in the United Kingdom.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong> Paul McCartney – $1.24 Billion</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most popular and respected musicians of the 20<sup>th</sup> century, Paul McCartney started out with The Beatles, where he helped propel them to worldwide and historical success. After the band\'s breakup, McCartney started an almost equally successful solo career, during which the Guinness World Records crowned him \"The most successful composer and recording artist of all time\".  To this day, there is no concert hall in the world that McCartney won\'t be able to fill up completely.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Possible titles for the Article:</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCan you guess these music stars\' net worth?\r\n\r\nDr. Dre\'s sale of Beats has brought him closer to $1 billion\r\n\r\nWho are the 30 richest musicians in the world?\r\n\r\nDavid Bowie\'s net worth – how much did the late singer leave behind?\r\n\r\nHow much is George Michael\'s will worth?\r\n\r\nDid illegal music downloading really hurt these artists?','Top 30 Richest Musicians','','trash','open','open','','__trashed','','','2017-01-19 18:11:41','2017-01-19 18:11:41','',0,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/?p=1068',0,'post','',0),(1069,1,'2017-01-19 14:27:11','2017-01-19 14:27:11','<h1>30. 50 Cent – $155 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Discovered by Eminem and Dr. Dre, The G-Unit rapper debuted in 2003 with a 8x Platinum Album in \"Get Rich Or Die Tryin\'\". He has since released four more albums (which sold millions of copies themselves) and has appeared in numerous films. 50 Cent has also ventured into the business world and founded \"SMS Audio\", an electronics company selling headphones.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1064\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/name.jpg\" alt=\"name\" width=\"550\" height=\"413\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"29\">\r\n 	<li><strong> George Michael - $175 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe late British pop star has made his fortune selling more than 100 million records worldwide. Michael managed to maintain an extremely high net worth even while anonymously donating large amounts to charities for years.\r\nAfter his untimely death, Michael\'s last will caused controversy in regards to his children and his boyfriend.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"28\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Usher - $180 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn all-round entrepreneur, Usher is credited as a singer, a songwriter, a dancer and as an actor, and is also renowned for discovering teen pop sensation Justin Bieber. He is a versatile businessman as well, and is a famous part-owner of the NBA\'s Cleveland Cavaliers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"27\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Lars Ulrich - $200 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most recognized drummers in the world, Lars Ulrich has made his fortunes playing with the infamous metal band Metallica. He has angered many music fans all around the world by leading the famous lawsuit against file-sharing website Napster. Ulrich enjoys spending large sums of his earnings on his expensive paintings collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"26\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Eminem - $210 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDr. Dre\'s incredibly successful protégé, Eminem has found success against all odds. His albums have all reached multi-platinum certifications, while in between, Eminem has managed to star in a biopic about his life, \"8 Mile\". The movie\'s title song, \"Lose Yourself\", has earned Eminem an Academy Award, making him the first Hip Hop artist to achieve the feat.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"25\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Ozzy Osbourne - $220 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\"The Godfather of Heavy Metal\" of Black Sabbath fame, Grammy Award winner Ozzy Osbourne has been an ever-present member of the industry for over 40 years.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"24\">\r\n 	<li><strong> David Bowie - $230 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPrior to his untimely death in 2016, British sensation David Bowie has been one of the music industry\'s most recognized and respected personas, with a career that spanned for almost 5 decades. Bowie has constantly changed and rewritten the rules of Rock and Roll, while also appearing in various films.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNet Worth: $230 Million.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"23\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Rod Stewart - $235 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRock icon Rod Stewart has been in the music business since the 1960\'s. He has found success being the front man in several bands before launching a solo career. His heavy touring schedule and various property investments add on to his already rich portfolio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"22\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Eric Clapton - $250 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nClapton rose to fame in the 1960\'s and never looked back since. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame after earning 18 Grammy Awards and selling millions of records worldwide, becoming one of the most influential guitarists of all time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"21\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Phil Collins - $260 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGaining fame as the drummer of British band Genesis, Phil Collins\' career has spanned almost 40 years. His earnings from Genesis only slightly surpass his earnings as a solo artist.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"20\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Roger Waters - $270 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSinger, songwriter and bassist Waters has been an integral part of legendary band Pink Floyd\'s success, writing most of the songs on the band\'s great album \"Dark Side of the Moon\", which has sold an estimated 45 million copies worldwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"19\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Dhani Harrison - $275 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe son of the late legendary Beatle George Harrison, Dhani Harrison was the sole inheritor of his father\'s estate, and therefore inherited all the wealth the late George Harrison had amassed over his prosperous career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"18\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Lady Gaga - $280 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDespite being in the scene for only roughly a decade, Lady Gaga has enjoyed incredible success, releasing critically acclaimed and commercially successful albums. Her immeasurable success and unorthodox appearance style made her a household name in the business.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"17\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jon Bon Jovi - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLead singer of successful, self-entitled rock band \"Bon Jovi\", Jon Bon Jovi is one of the best-selling artists of all time, selling over 130 million records worldwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"16\">\r\n 	<li><strong> L.A. Reid - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecord producer and executive L.A. Reid is the CEO of Epic Records, which is a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment. Reid is credited with launching the careers of several high profile artists; the list includes some very big names like Mariah Carey, Pink, Rihanna, Kanye West and Justin Bieber.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"15\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Sting - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSting started out as the singer and bassist for the band \"The Police\", but has since launched a long and incredibly successful solo career, over which he became a music icon.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"14\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Keith Richards - $340 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRock symbol Keith Richards made a career for himself being a part of legendary rock band \"The Rolling Stones\". He is widely considered to be one of the best guitarists in history, and fourteen of the songs he co-wrote with his bandmate Mick Jagger were selected by the Rolling Stone Magazine among the \"500 Greatest Songs of All Time\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"13\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Bruce Springsteen - $345 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKnown both as a rock icon and as a philanthropist and a humanitarian, Springsteen made his debut in 1973 and never looked back since. With 18 albums released and 20 Grammy Awards to his name, Springsteen is one of the industry\'s most prolific and successful artists. He is also a known supporter of and activist for LGBT rights.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"12\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Ringo Starr - $350 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBeing an integral part of the most successful band in history is highly profitable. Star has been the drummer of British band \"The Beatles\" from 1962 until the band\'s ultimate breakup. Since then has also maintained a solo career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"11\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Mick Jagger - $360 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMusician, singer, songwriter, dancer, actor, producer, legend – a lot can be said about Mick Jagger. The lead vocalist of \"The Rolling Stones\" has defined the rock scene in the 1960\'s and made his mark on rock – and on music – forever. He continues to tour with the Rolling Stones to this day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"10\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jimmy Buffet - $430 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFolk-country music singer and songwriter Jimmy Buffet has been in the business since the late 1960\'s, and his unique sound and style have helped him to enjoy incredible success. He is also a writer, writing 3 best-sellers, and a businessman, owning restaurant chains as well as a casino.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"9\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Elton John - $480 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSir Elton John is one of the most respected and celebrated artists of our time. With a career spanning over four decades, his music had become the soundtrack of many of his fans\' lives. Elton John has won it all – Grammy Awards, Brit Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award – and he has enjoyed the success and wealth that came with all of it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Emilio Estefan - $500 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSinger and producer Emilio Estefan has produced countless records that have topped the Latino charts. He has also appeared in films. Emilio and his wife Gloria own and manage a large number of high-end successful restaurants all throughout America.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jay Z - $550 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most successful rappers of all time, Jay Z has amassed a huge fortune for himself releasing multi-platinum albums as well as founding entertainment company \"Roc Nation\" and co-founding \"Roc-A-Fella Records\". He is also the co-creator of the \"Rocawear\" clothing line and the founder of sports agency \"Roc Nation Sports\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Madonna - $560 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMadonna has her hand in everything – singing, songwriting, acting, entrepreneurship – you name it. She has been in the limelight since the 1980\'s and shows no signs of slowing down even at the age of 58. She is recognized by the Guinness World Records as the best-selling female artist of all time. Her concerts have grossed over $1 billion over the course of her career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Dr. Dre - $700 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEmerging into the public eye as part of the controversial Hip Hop group NWA, Dr. Dre is now one of the most respected names in the Rap scene as well as in the music industry. His record label Aftermath Entertainment is responsible for launching the careers of mega-stars Eminem and 50 Cent. Dr. Dre is also the founder of headphone company Beats Audio, which was sold to Apple for an estimated $3 billion.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Sean Combs (P. Diddy) - $750 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecord producer, singer and businessman Sean Combs has reinvented himself countless times over the course of his career, and so he has managed to stay at the top of the music industry as a household name. Founder of successful record company \"Bad Boy Records\" and owner of his own clothing line \"Sean John\", Sean Combs\' fortune just keeps on rising.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Herb Alpert - $850 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHerb Alpert started in the 1960\'s as a part of the \"Herb Alpert and the Tijuana Grass\" jazz group, and went on to become one of the industry\'s most powerful executives.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Andrew Lloyd Webber – $1.2 Billion</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSir Andrew Lloyd Webber made his fortune composing musicals. Throughout his 50-year career Webber has composed some incredibly iconic music for operas such as \"The Phantom of the Opera\". His company, the Really Useful Group, is one of the largest and most successful theater operators in the United Kingdom.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong> Paul McCartney – $1.24 Billion</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most popular and respected musicians of the 20<sup>th</sup> century, Paul McCartney started out with The Beatles, where he helped propel them to worldwide and historical success. After the band\'s breakup, McCartney started an almost equally successful solo career, during which the Guinness World Records crowned him \"The most successful composer and recording artist of all time\".  To this day, there is no concert hall in the world that McCartney won\'t be able to fill up completely.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Possible titles for the Article:</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCan you guess these music stars\' net worth?\r\n\r\nDr. Dre\'s sale of Beats has brought him closer to $1 billion\r\n\r\nWho are the 30 richest musicians in the world?\r\n\r\nDavid Bowie\'s net worth – how much did the late singer leave behind?\r\n\r\nHow much is George Michael\'s will worth?\r\n\r\nDid illegal music downloading really hurt these artists?','Top 30 Richest Musicians','','inherit','closed','closed','','1068-revision-v1','','','2017-01-19 14:27:11','2017-01-19 14:27:11','',1068,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1068-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1070,1,'2017-01-19 14:28:07','2017-01-19 14:28:07','<h1>30. 50 Cent – $155 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Discovered by Eminem and Dr. Dre, The G-Unit rapper debuted in 2003 with a 8x Platinum Album in \"Get Rich Or Die Tryin\'\". He has since released four more albums (which sold millions of copies themselves) and has appeared in numerous films. 50 Cent has also ventured into the business world and founded \"SMS Audio\", an electronics company selling headphones.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1064\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/name.jpg\" alt=\"name\" width=\"550\" height=\"413\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<ol start=\"29\">\r\n 	<li><strong> George Michael - $175 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe late British pop star has made his fortune selling more than 100 million records worldwide. Michael managed to maintain an extremely high net worth even while anonymously donating large amounts to charities for years.\r\nAfter his untimely death, Michael\'s last will caused controversy in regards to his children and his boyfriend.<!--nextpage-->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"28\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Usher - $180 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn all-round entrepreneur, Usher is credited as a singer, a songwriter, a dancer and as an actor, and is also renowned for discovering teen pop sensation Justin Bieber. He is a versatile businessman as well, and is a famous part-owner of the NBA\'s Cleveland Cavaliers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"27\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Lars Ulrich - $200 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most recognized drummers in the world, Lars Ulrich has made his fortunes playing with the infamous metal band Metallica. He has angered many music fans all around the world by leading the famous lawsuit against file-sharing website Napster. Ulrich enjoys spending large sums of his earnings on his expensive paintings collection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"26\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Eminem - $210 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDr. Dre\'s incredibly successful protégé, Eminem has found success against all odds. His albums have all reached multi-platinum certifications, while in between, Eminem has managed to star in a biopic about his life, \"8 Mile\". The movie\'s title song, \"Lose Yourself\", has earned Eminem an Academy Award, making him the first Hip Hop artist to achieve the feat.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"25\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Ozzy Osbourne - $220 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\"The Godfather of Heavy Metal\" of Black Sabbath fame, Grammy Award winner Ozzy Osbourne has been an ever-present member of the industry for over 40 years.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"24\">\r\n 	<li><strong> David Bowie - $230 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPrior to his untimely death in 2016, British sensation David Bowie has been one of the music industry\'s most recognized and respected personas, with a career that spanned for almost 5 decades. Bowie has constantly changed and rewritten the rules of Rock and Roll, while also appearing in various films.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNet Worth: $230 Million.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"23\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Rod Stewart - $235 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRock icon Rod Stewart has been in the music business since the 1960\'s. He has found success being the front man in several bands before launching a solo career. His heavy touring schedule and various property investments add on to his already rich portfolio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"22\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Eric Clapton - $250 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nClapton rose to fame in the 1960\'s and never looked back since. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame after earning 18 Grammy Awards and selling millions of records worldwide, becoming one of the most influential guitarists of all time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"21\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Phil Collins - $260 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGaining fame as the drummer of British band Genesis, Phil Collins\' career has spanned almost 40 years. His earnings from Genesis only slightly surpass his earnings as a solo artist.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"20\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Roger Waters - $270 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSinger, songwriter and bassist Waters has been an integral part of legendary band Pink Floyd\'s success, writing most of the songs on the band\'s great album \"Dark Side of the Moon\", which has sold an estimated 45 million copies worldwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"19\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Dhani Harrison - $275 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe son of the late legendary Beatle George Harrison, Dhani Harrison was the sole inheritor of his father\'s estate, and therefore inherited all the wealth the late George Harrison had amassed over his prosperous career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"18\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Lady Gaga - $280 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDespite being in the scene for only roughly a decade, Lady Gaga has enjoyed incredible success, releasing critically acclaimed and commercially successful albums. Her immeasurable success and unorthodox appearance style made her a household name in the business.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"17\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jon Bon Jovi - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLead singer of successful, self-entitled rock band \"Bon Jovi\", Jon Bon Jovi is one of the best-selling artists of all time, selling over 130 million records worldwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"16\">\r\n 	<li><strong> L.A. Reid - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecord producer and executive L.A. Reid is the CEO of Epic Records, which is a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment. Reid is credited with launching the careers of several high profile artists; the list includes some very big names like Mariah Carey, Pink, Rihanna, Kanye West and Justin Bieber.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"15\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Sting - $300 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSting started out as the singer and bassist for the band \"The Police\", but has since launched a long and incredibly successful solo career, over which he became a music icon.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"14\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Keith Richards - $340 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRock symbol Keith Richards made a career for himself being a part of legendary rock band \"The Rolling Stones\". He is widely considered to be one of the best guitarists in history, and fourteen of the songs he co-wrote with his bandmate Mick Jagger were selected by the Rolling Stone Magazine among the \"500 Greatest Songs of All Time\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"13\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Bruce Springsteen - $345 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKnown both as a rock icon and as a philanthropist and a humanitarian, Springsteen made his debut in 1973 and never looked back since. With 18 albums released and 20 Grammy Awards to his name, Springsteen is one of the industry\'s most prolific and successful artists. He is also a known supporter of and activist for LGBT rights.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"12\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Ringo Starr - $350 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBeing an integral part of the most successful band in history is highly profitable. Star has been the drummer of British band \"The Beatles\" from 1962 until the band\'s ultimate breakup. Since then has also maintained a solo career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"11\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Mick Jagger - $360 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMusician, singer, songwriter, dancer, actor, producer, legend – a lot can be said about Mick Jagger. The lead vocalist of \"The Rolling Stones\" has defined the rock scene in the 1960\'s and made his mark on rock – and on music – forever. He continues to tour with the Rolling Stones to this day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"10\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jimmy Buffet - $430 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFolk-country music singer and songwriter Jimmy Buffet has been in the business since the late 1960\'s, and his unique sound and style have helped him to enjoy incredible success. He is also a writer, writing 3 best-sellers, and a businessman, owning restaurant chains as well as a casino.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"9\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Elton John - $480 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSir Elton John is one of the most respected and celebrated artists of our time. With a career spanning over four decades, his music had become the soundtrack of many of his fans\' lives. Elton John has won it all – Grammy Awards, Brit Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award – and he has enjoyed the success and wealth that came with all of it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Emilio Estefan - $500 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSinger and producer Emilio Estefan has produced countless records that have topped the Latino charts. He has also appeared in films. Emilio and his wife Gloria own and manage a large number of high-end successful restaurants all throughout America.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Jay Z - $550 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most successful rappers of all time, Jay Z has amassed a huge fortune for himself releasing multi-platinum albums as well as founding entertainment company \"Roc Nation\" and co-founding \"Roc-A-Fella Records\". He is also the co-creator of the \"Rocawear\" clothing line and the founder of sports agency \"Roc Nation Sports\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Madonna - $560 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMadonna has her hand in everything – singing, songwriting, acting, entrepreneurship – you name it. She has been in the limelight since the 1980\'s and shows no signs of slowing down even at the age of 58. She is recognized by the Guinness World Records as the best-selling female artist of all time. Her concerts have grossed over $1 billion over the course of her career.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Dr. Dre - $700 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEmerging into the public eye as part of the controversial Hip Hop group NWA, Dr. Dre is now one of the most respected names in the Rap scene as well as in the music industry. His record label Aftermath Entertainment is responsible for launching the careers of mega-stars Eminem and 50 Cent. Dr. Dre is also the founder of headphone company Beats Audio, which was sold to Apple for an estimated $3 billion.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Sean Combs (P. Diddy) - $750 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecord producer, singer and businessman Sean Combs has reinvented himself countless times over the course of his career, and so he has managed to stay at the top of the music industry as a household name. Founder of successful record company \"Bad Boy Records\" and owner of his own clothing line \"Sean John\", Sean Combs\' fortune just keeps on rising.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Herb Alpert - $850 Million</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHerb Alpert started in the 1960\'s as a part of the \"Herb Alpert and the Tijuana Grass\" jazz group, and went on to become one of the industry\'s most powerful executives.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Andrew Lloyd Webber – $1.2 Billion</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSir Andrew Lloyd Webber made his fortune composing musicals. Throughout his 50-year career Webber has composed some incredibly iconic music for operas such as \"The Phantom of the Opera\". His company, the Really Useful Group, is one of the largest and most successful theater operators in the United Kingdom.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong> Paul McCartney – $1.24 Billion</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOne of the most popular and respected musicians of the 20<sup>th</sup> century, Paul McCartney started out with The Beatles, where he helped propel them to worldwide and historical success. After the band\'s breakup, McCartney started an almost equally successful solo career, during which the Guinness World Records crowned him \"The most successful composer and recording artist of all time\".  To this day, there is no concert hall in the world that McCartney won\'t be able to fill up completely.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Possible titles for the Article:</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCan you guess these music stars\' net worth?\r\n\r\nDr. Dre\'s sale of Beats has brought him closer to $1 billion\r\n\r\nWho are the 30 richest musicians in the world?\r\n\r\nDavid Bowie\'s net worth – how much did the late singer leave behind?\r\n\r\nHow much is George Michael\'s will worth?\r\n\r\nDid illegal music downloading really hurt these artists?','Top 30 Richest Musicians','','inherit','closed','closed','','1068-revision-v1','','','2017-01-19 14:28:07','2017-01-19 14:28:07','',1068,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1068-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1071,1,'2017-01-27 09:24:42','2017-01-27 09:24:42','<h1>30. 50 Cent – $155 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Discovered by Eminem and Dr. Dre, The G-Unit rapper debuted in 2003 with a 8x Platinum Album in \"Get Rich Or Die Tryin\'\". He has since released four more albums (which sold millions of copies themselves) and has appeared in numerous films. 50 Cent has also ventured into the business world and founded \"SMS Audio\", an electronics company selling headphones.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1072\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/50-Cent.jpg\" alt=\"50-cent\" width=\"529\" height=\"352\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>29. George Michael - $175 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>The late British pop star has made his fortune selling more than 100 million records worldwide. Michael managed to maintain an extremely high net worth even while anonymously donating large amounts to charities for years.\r\nAfter his untimely death, Michael\'s last will caused controversy in regards to his children and his boyfriend.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1082\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/George-Michael.jpg\" alt=\"george-michael\" width=\"551\" height=\"433\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>28. Usher - $180 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>An all-around entrepreneur, Usher is credited as a singer, a songwriter, a dancer and as an actor, and is also renowned for discovering teen pop sensation Justin Bieber. He is a versatile businessman as well, and is a famous part-owner of the NBA\'s Cleveland Cavaliers.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1101\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Usher.jpg\" alt=\"usher\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>27. Lars Ulrich - $200 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>One of the most recognized drummers in the world, Lars Ulrich has made his fortunes playing with the infamous metal band Metallica. He has angered many music fans all around the world by leading the famous lawsuit against file-sharing website Napster. Ulrich enjoys spending large sums of his earnings on his expensive paintings collection.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1090\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Lars-Ulrich.jpg\" alt=\"lars-ulrich\" width=\"550\" height=\"364\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>26. Eminem - $210 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Dr. Dre\'s incredibly successful protégé, Eminem has found success against all odds. His albums have all reached multi-platinum certifications, while in between, Eminem has managed to star in a biopic about his life, \"8 Mile\". The movie\'s title song, \"Lose Yourself\", has earned Eminem an Academy Award, making him the first Hip Hop artist to achieve the feat.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1080\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Eminem.jpg\" alt=\"eminem\" width=\"551\" height=\"413\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>25. Ozzy Osbourne - $220 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>\"The Godfather of Heavy Metal\" of Black Sabbath fame, Grammy Award winner Ozzy Osbourne has been an ever-present member of the industry for over 40 years.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1093\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Ozzy-Osbourne.jpg\" alt=\"ozzy-osbourne\" width=\"549\" height=\"288\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>24. David Bowie - $230 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Prior to his untimely death in 2016, British sensation David Bowie has been one of the music industry\'s most recognized and respected personas, with a career that spanned for almost 5 decades. Bowie has constantly changed and rewritten the rules of Rock and Roll, while also appearing in various films.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1075\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/David-Bowie.jpg\" alt=\"david-bowie\" width=\"550\" height=\"396\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>23. Rod Stewart - $235 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Rock icon Rod Stewart has been in the music business since the 1960\'s. He has found success being the front man in several bands before launching a solo career. His heavy touring schedule and various property investments add on to his already rich portfolio.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1097\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Rod-Stewart.jpg\" alt=\"rod-stewart\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>22. Eric Clapton - $250 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Clapton rose to fame in the 1960\'s and never looked back since. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame after earning 18 Grammy Awards and selling millions of records worldwide, becoming one of the most influential guitarists of all time.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1081\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Eric-Clapton.jpg\" alt=\"None\" width=\"551\" height=\"372\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>21. Phil Collins - $260 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Gaining fame as the drummer of British band Genesis, Phil Collins\' career has spanned almost 40 years. His earnings from Genesis only slightly surpass his earnings as a solo artist.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1095\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Phil-Collins.jpg\" alt=\"phil-collins\" width=\"551\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>20. Roger Waters - $270 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Singer, songwriter and bassist Waters has been an integral part of legendary band Pink Floyd\'s success, writing most of the songs on the band\'s great album \"Dark Side of the Moon\", which has sold an estimated 45 million copies worldwide.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1098\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/rogerWaters.jpg\" alt=\"rogerwaters\" width=\"550\" height=\"306\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>19. Dhani Harrison - $275 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>The son of the late legendary Beatle George Harrison, Dhani Harrison was the sole inheritor of his father\'s estate, and therefore inherited all the wealth the late George Harrison had amassed over his prosperous career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1076\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dhani-Harrison.jpg\" alt=\"dhani-harrison\" width=\"539\" height=\"404\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>18. Lady Gaga - $280 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Despite being in the scene for only roughly a decade, Lady Gaga has enjoyed incredible success, releasing critically acclaimed and commercially successful albums. Her immeasurable success and unorthodox appearance style made her a household name in the business.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1089\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Lady-Gaga.jpg\" alt=\"lady-gaga\" width=\"416\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>17. Jon Bon Jovi - $300 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Lead singer of successful, self-entitled rock band \"Bon Jovi\", Jon Bon Jovi is one of the best-selling artists of all time, selling over 130 million records worldwide.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1086\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Jon-Bon-Jovi.jpg\" alt=\"jon-bon-jovi\" width=\"550\" height=\"344\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>16. L.A. Reid - $300 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Record producer and executive L.A. Reid is the CEO of Epic Records, which is a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment. Reid is credited with launching the careers of several high profile artists; the list includes some very big names like Mariah Carey, Pink, Rihanna, Kanye West and Justin Bieber.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1088\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/L.A.-Reid.jpg\" alt=\"THE X FACTOR: L.A. Reid. CR: Nino Munoz / FOX\" width=\"550\" height=\"432\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>15. Sting - $300 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Sting started out as the singer and bassist for the band \"The Police\", but has since launched a long and incredibly successful solo career, over which he became a music icon.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1100\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sting.jpg\" alt=\"sting\" width=\"551\" height=\"413\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>14. Keith Richards - $340 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Rock symbol Keith Richards made a career for himself being a part of legendary rock band \"The Rolling Stones\". He is widely considered to be one of the best guitarists in history, and fourteen of the songs he co-wrote with his bandmate Mick Jagger were selected by the Rolling Stone Magazine among the \"500 Greatest Songs of All Time\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1087\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Keith-Richards.jpg\" alt=\"keith-richards\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>13. Bruce Springsteen - $345 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Known both as a rock icon and as a philanthropist and a humanitarian, Springsteen made his debut in 1973 and never looked back since. With 18 albums released and 20 Grammy Awards to his name, Springsteen is one of the industry\'s most prolific and successful artists. He is also a known supporter of and activist for LGBT rights.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1074\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Bruce-Springsteen.jpg\" alt=\"bruce-springsteen\" width=\"549\" height=\"348\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>12. Ringo Starr - $350 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Being an integral part of the most successful band in history is highly profitable. Star has been the drummer of British band \"The Beatles\" from 1962 until the band\'s ultimate breakup. Since then has also maintained a solo career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1096\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ringo.jpeg\" alt=\"ringo\" width=\"549\" height=\"308\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>11. Mick Jagger - $360 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Musician, singer, songwriter, dancer, actor, producer, legend – a lot can be said about Mick Jagger. The lead vocalist of \"The Rolling Stones\" has defined the rock scene in the 1960\'s and made his mark on rock – and on music – forever. He continues to tour with the Rolling Stones to this day.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1092\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Mick-Jagger.jpg\" alt=\"mick-jagger\" width=\"549\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>10. Jimmy Buffet - $430 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Folk-country music singer and songwriter Jimmy Buffet has been in the business since the late 1960\'s, and his unique sound and style have helped him to enjoy incredible success. He is also a writer, writing 3 best-sellers, and a businessman, owning restaurant chains as well as a casino.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1085\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Jimmy-Buffett.jpg\" alt=\"performs onstage at Jimmy Buffett &amp; Friends: Live from the Gulf Coast, a concert presented by CMT at on the beach on July 11, 2010 in Gulf Shores, Alabama.\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>9. Elton John - $480 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Sir Elton John is one of the most respected and celebrated artists of our time. With a career spanning over four decades, his music had become the soundtrack of many of his fans\' lives. Elton John has won it all – Grammy Awards, Brit Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award – and he has enjoyed the success and wealth that came with all of it.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1078\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Elton-John.jpg\" alt=\"Skagerak Arena June 2009\" width=\"552\" height=\"368\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>8. Emilio Estefan - $500 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Singer and producer Emilio Estefan has produced countless records that have topped the Latino charts. He has also appeared in films. Emilio and his wife Gloria own and manage a large number of high-end successful restaurants all throughout America.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1079\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Emilio-Estefan.jpg\" alt=\"emilio-estefan\" width=\"550\" height=\"426\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>7. Jay Z - $550 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>One of the most successful rappers of all time, Jay Z has amassed a huge fortune for himself releasing multi-platinum albums as well as founding entertainment company \"Roc Nation\" and co-founding \"Roc-A-Fella Records\". He is also the co-creator of the \"Rocawear\" clothing line and the founder of sports agency \"Roc Nation Sports\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1084\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/jayz.jpg\" alt=\"NEW YORK, NY - JULY 03: Jay-Z attends the &quot;Magna Carta Holy Grail&quot; album release party at Pier 41 - Liberty Warehouse on July 3, 2013 in the Brooklyn borough of New York City. (Photo by Paul Zimmerman/WireImage)\" width=\"548\" height=\"365\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>6. Madonna - $560 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Madonna has her hand in everything – singing, songwriting, acting, entrepreneurship – you name it. She has been in the limelight since the 1980\'s and shows no signs of slowing down even at the age of 58. She is recognized by the Guinness World Records as the best-selling female artist of all time. Her concerts have grossed over $1 billion over the course of her career.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1091\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Madonna.jpg\" alt=\"madonna\" width=\"550\" height=\"397\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>5. Dr. Dre - $700 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Emerging into the public eye as a member of the controversial Hip Hop group NWA, Dr. Dre is now one of the most respected names in the Rap scene as well as in the music industry. His record label Aftermath Entertainment is responsible for launching the careers of mega-stars Eminem and 50 Cent. Dr. Dre is also the founder of headphone company Beats Audio, which was sold to Apple for an estimated $3 billion.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1077\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dr-Dre.jpg\" alt=\"1/7/2009 Las Vegas Nevada, CES -- Dr. Dre, record producer/rapper shows off his new headphones. Note- Mike Snider is writing something on this. Photo by Tim Loehrke, USAToday (Via MerlinFTP Drop)\" width=\"550\" height=\"359\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>4. Sean Combs (P. Diddy) - $750 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Record producer, singer and businessman Sean Combs has reinvented himself countless times over the course of his career, and so he has managed to stay at the top of the music industry as a household name. Founder of successful record company \"Bad Boy Records\" and owner of his own clothing line \"Sean John\", Sean Combs\' fortune just keeps on rising.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1099\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sean-Combs.jpg\" alt=\"CANNES, FRANCE - MAY 22: Sean Combs attends the \'Killing Them Softly\' Premiere during 65th Annual Cannes Film Festival at Palais des Festivals on May 22, 2012 in Cannes, France. (Photo by Gareth Cattermole/Getty Images)\" width=\"385\" height=\"501\" /><!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>3. Herb Alpert - $850 Million</h1>\r\n<h3>Herb Alpert started in the 1960\'s as a part of the \"Herb Alpert and the Tijuana Grass\" jazz group, and went on to become one of the industry\'s most powerful executives.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1083\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Herb-Alpert.jpg\" alt=\"herb-alpert\" width=\"509\" height=\"505\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>2. Andrew Lloyd Webber – $1.2 Billion</h1>\r\n<h3>Sir Andrew Lloyd Webber made his fortune composing musicals. Throughout his 50-year career Webber has composed some incredibly iconic music for operas such as \"The Phantom of the Opera\". His company, the Really Useful Group, is one of the largest and most successful theater operators in the United Kingdom.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1073\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Andrew-Lloyd-Webber.jpg\" alt=\"andrew-lloyd-webber\" width=\"502\" height=\"333\" />\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>1. Paul McCartney – $1.24 Billion</h1>\r\n<h3>One of the most popular and respected musicians of the 20<sup>th</sup> century, Paul McCartney started out with The Beatles, where he helped propel them to worldwide and historical success. After the band\'s breakup, McCartney started an almost equally successful solo career, during which the Guinness World Records crowned him \"The most successful composer and recording artist of all time\".  To this day, there is no concert hall in the world that McCartney won\'t be able to fill up completely.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1102\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Paul-McCartney-2.png\" alt=\"paul-mccartney-2\" width=\"551\" height=\"379\" />','Top Richest Musicians And Their Net Worth','','publish','open','open','','top-30-richest-musicians','','','2017-01-31 17:34:16','2017-01-31 17:34:16','',0,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/?p=1071',0,'post','',0),(1072,1,'2017-01-19 18:32:32','2017-01-19 18:32:32','','50-cent','','inherit','open','closed','','50-cent','','','2017-01-19 18:32:32','2017-01-19 18:32:32','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/50-Cent.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1073,1,'2017-01-19 18:32:37','2017-01-19 18:32:37','','andrew-lloyd-webber','','inherit','open','closed','','andrew-lloyd-webber','','','2017-01-19 18:32:37','2017-01-19 18:32:37','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Andrew-Lloyd-Webber.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1074,1,'2017-01-19 18:32:41','2017-01-19 18:32:41','','bruce-springsteen','','inherit','open','closed','','bruce-springsteen','','','2017-01-19 18:32:41','2017-01-19 18:32:41','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Bruce-Springsteen.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1075,1,'2017-01-19 18:32:48','2017-01-19 18:32:48','','david-bowie','','inherit','open','closed','',