,1,'2017-01-19 18:36:24','2017-01-19 18:36:24','','sting','','inherit','open','closed','','sting','','','2017-01-19 18:36:24','2017-01-19 18:36:24','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sting.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1101,1,'2017-01-19 18:36:33','2017-01-19 18:36:33','','usher','','inherit','open','closed','','usher','','','2017-01-19 18:36:33','2017-01-19 18:36:33','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Usher.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1102,1,'2017-01-19 19:05:11','2017-01-19 19:05:11','','paul-mccartney-2','','inherit','open','closed','','paul-mccartney-2','','','2017-01-19 19:05:11','2017-01-19 19:05:11','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Paul-McCartney-2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1103,1,'2017-01-19 19:06:01','2017-01-19 19:06:01','<h1>30. 50 Cent – $155 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1072\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/50-Cent.jpg\" alt=\"50-cent\" width=\"529\" height=\"352\" />\r\n<h3>Discovered by Eminem and Dr. Dre, The G-Unit rapper debuted in 2003 with a 8x Platinum Album in \"Get Rich Or Die Tryin\'\". He has since released four more albums (which sold millions of copies themselves) and has appeared in numerous films. 50 Cent has also ventured into the business world and founded \"SMS Audio\", an electronics company selling headphones.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>George Michael - $175 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1082\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/George-Michael.jpg\" alt=\"george-michael\" width=\"551\" height=\"433\" />\r\n<h3>The late British pop star has made his fortune selling more than 100 million records worldwide. Michael managed to maintain an extremely high net worth even while anonymously donating large amounts to charities for years.\r\nAfter his untimely death, Michael\'s last will caused controversy in regards to his children and his boyfriend.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>28. Usher - $180 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1101\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Usher.jpg\" alt=\"usher\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>An all-around entrepreneur, Usher is credited as a singer, a songwriter, a dancer and as an actor, and is also renowned for discovering teen pop sensation Justin Bieber. He is a versatile businessman as well, and is a famous part-owner of the NBA\'s Cleveland Cavaliers.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>27. Lars Ulrich - $200 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1090\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Lars-Ulrich.jpg\" alt=\"lars-ulrich\" width=\"550\" height=\"364\" />\r\n<h3>One of the most recognized drummers in the world, Lars Ulrich has made his fortunes playing with the infamous metal band Metallica. He has angered many music fans all around the world by leading the famous lawsuit against file-sharing website Napster. Ulrich enjoys spending large sums of his earnings on his expensive paintings collection.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Eminem - $210 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1080\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Eminem.jpg\" alt=\"eminem\" width=\"551\" height=\"413\" />\r\n<h3>Dr. Dre\'s incredibly successful protégé, Eminem has found success against all odds. His albums have all reached multi-platinum certifications, while in between, Eminem has managed to star in a biopic about his life, \"8 Mile\". The movie\'s title song, \"Lose Yourself\", has earned Eminem an Academy Award, making him the first Hip Hop artist to achieve the feat.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>25. Ozzy Osbourne - $220 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1093\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Ozzy-Osbourne.jpg\" alt=\"ozzy-osbourne\" width=\"549\" height=\"288\" />\r\n<h3>\"The Godfather of Heavy Metal\" of Black Sabbath fame, Grammy Award winner Ozzy Osbourne has been an ever-present member of the industry for over 40 years.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>24. David Bowie - $230 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1075\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/David-Bowie.jpg\" alt=\"david-bowie\" width=\"550\" height=\"396\" />\r\n<h3>Prior to his untimely death in 2016, British sensation David Bowie has been one of the music industry\'s most recognized and respected personas, with a career that spanned for almost 5 decades. Bowie has constantly changed and rewritten the rules of Rock and Roll, while also appearing in various films.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>23. Rod Stewart - $235 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1097\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Rod-Stewart.jpg\" alt=\"rod-stewart\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>Rock icon Rod Stewart has been in the music business since the 1960\'s. He has found success being the front man in several bands before launching a solo career. His heavy touring schedule and various property investments add on to his already rich portfolio.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>22. Eric Clapton - $250 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1081\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Eric-Clapton.jpg\" alt=\"None\" width=\"551\" height=\"372\" />\r\n<h3>Clapton rose to fame in the 1960\'s and never looked back since. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame after earning 18 Grammy Awards and selling millions of records worldwide, becoming one of the most influential guitarists of all time.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>21. Phil Collins - $260 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1095\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Phil-Collins.jpg\" alt=\"phil-collins\" width=\"551\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<h3>Gaining fame as the drummer of British band Genesis, Phil Collins\' career has spanned almost 40 years. His earnings from Genesis only slightly surpass his earnings as a solo artist.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>20. Roger Waters - $270 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1098\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/rogerWaters.jpg\" alt=\"rogerwaters\" width=\"510\" height=\"284\" />\r\n<h3>Singer, songwriter and bassist Waters has been an integral part of legendary band Pink Floyd\'s success, writing most of the songs on the band\'s great album \"Dark Side of the Moon\", which has sold an estimated 45 million copies worldwide.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>19. Dhani Harrison - $275 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1076\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dhani-Harrison.jpg\" alt=\"dhani-harrison\" width=\"548\" height=\"411\" />\r\n<h3>The son of the late legendary Beatle George Harrison, Dhani Harrison was the sole inheritor of his father\'s estate, and therefore inherited all the wealth the late George Harrison had amassed over his prosperous career.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>18. Lady Gaga - $280 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1089\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Lady-Gaga.jpg\" alt=\"lady-gaga\" width=\"550\" height=\"660\" />\r\n<h3>Despite being in the scene for only roughly a decade, Lady Gaga has enjoyed incredible success, releasing critically acclaimed and commercially successful albums. Her immeasurable success and unorthodox appearance style made her a household name in the business.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>17. Jon Bon Jovi - $300 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1086\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Jon-Bon-Jovi.jpg\" alt=\"jon-bon-jovi\" width=\"550\" height=\"344\" />\r\n<h3>Lead singer of successful, self-entitled rock band \"Bon Jovi\", Jon Bon Jovi is one of the best-selling artists of all time, selling over 130 million records worldwide.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>16. L.A. Reid - $300 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1088\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/L.A.-Reid.jpg\" alt=\"THE X FACTOR: L.A. Reid. CR: Nino Munoz / FOX\" width=\"550\" height=\"432\" />\r\n<h3>Record producer and executive L.A. Reid is the CEO of Epic Records, which is a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment. Reid is credited with launching the careers of several high profile artists; the list includes some very big names like Mariah Carey, Pink, Rihanna, Kanye West and Justin Bieber.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>15. Sting - $300 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1100\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sting.jpg\" alt=\"sting\" width=\"551\" height=\"413\" />\r\n<h3>Sting started out as the singer and bassist for the band \"The Police\", but has since launched a long and incredibly successful solo career, over which he became a music icon.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>14. Keith Richards - $340 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1087\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Keith-Richards.jpg\" alt=\"keith-richards\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>Rock symbol Keith Richards made a career for himself being a part of legendary rock band \"The Rolling Stones\". He is widely considered to be one of the best guitarists in history, and fourteen of the songs he co-wrote with his bandmate Mick Jagger were selected by the Rolling Stone Magazine among the \"500 Greatest Songs of All Time\".<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>13. Bruce Springsteen - $345 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1074\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Bruce-Springsteen.jpg\" alt=\"bruce-springsteen\" width=\"549\" height=\"348\" />\r\n<h3>Known both as a rock icon and as a philanthropist and a humanitarian, Springsteen made his debut in 1973 and never looked back since. With 18 albums released and 20 Grammy Awards to his name, Springsteen is one of the industry\'s most prolific and successful artists. He is also a known supporter of and activist for LGBT rights.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>12. Ringo Starr - $350 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1096\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ringo.jpeg\" alt=\"ringo\" width=\"551\" height=\"309\" />\r\n\r\nBeing an integral part of the most successful band in history is highly profitable. Star has been the drummer of British band \"The Beatles\" from 1962 until the band\'s ultimate breakup. Since then has also maintained a solo career.<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>11. Mick Jagger - $360 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1092\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Mick-Jagger.jpg\" alt=\"mick-jagger\" width=\"549\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<h3>Musician, singer, songwriter, dancer, actor, producer, legend – a lot can be said about Mick Jagger. The lead vocalist of \"The Rolling Stones\" has defined the rock scene in the 1960\'s and made his mark on rock – and on music – forever. He continues to tour with the Rolling Stones to this day.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>10. Jimmy Buffet - $430 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1085\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Jimmy-Buffett.jpg\" alt=\"performs onstage at Jimmy Buffett &amp; Friends: Live from the Gulf Coast, a concert presented by CMT at on the beach on July 11, 2010 in Gulf Shores, Alabama.\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>Folk-country music singer and songwriter Jimmy Buffet has been in the business since the late 1960\'s, and his unique sound and style have helped him to enjoy incredible success. He is also a writer, writing 3 best-sellers, and a businessman, owning restaurant chains as well as a casino.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>9. Elton John - $480 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1078\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Elton-John.jpg\" alt=\"Skagerak Arena June 2009\" width=\"552\" height=\"368\" />\r\n<h3>Sir Elton John is one of the most respected and celebrated artists of our time. With a career spanning over four decades, his music had become the soundtrack of many of his fans\' lives. Elton John has won it all – Grammy Awards, Brit Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award – and he has enjoyed the success and wealth that came with all of it.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>8. Emilio Estefan - $500 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1079\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Emilio-Estefan.jpg\" alt=\"emilio-estefan\" width=\"550\" height=\"426\" />\r\n<h3>Singer and producer Emilio Estefan has produced countless records that have topped the Latino charts. He has also appeared in films. Emilio and his wife Gloria own and manage a large number of high-end successful restaurants all throughout America.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>7. Jay Z - $550 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1084\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/jayz.jpg\" alt=\"NEW YORK, NY - JULY 03:  Jay-Z attends the &quot;Magna Carta Holy Grail&quot; album release party at Pier 41 - Liberty Warehouse on July 3, 2013 in the Brooklyn borough of New York City.  (Photo by Paul Zimmerman/WireImage)\" width=\"548\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<h3>One of the most successful rappers of all time, Jay Z has amassed a huge fortune for himself releasing multi-platinum albums as well as founding entertainment company \"Roc Nation\" and co-founding \"Roc-A-Fella Records\". He is also the co-creator of the \"Rocawear\" clothing line and the founder of sports agency \"Roc Nation Sports\".<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>6. Madonna - $560 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1091\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Madonna.jpg\" alt=\"madonna\" width=\"550\" height=\"397\" />\r\n<h3>Madonna has her hand in everything – singing, songwriting, acting, entrepreneurship – you name it. She has been in the limelight since the 1980\'s and shows no signs of slowing down even at the age of 58. She is recognized by the Guinness World Records as the best-selling female artist of all time. Her concerts have grossed over $1 billion over the course of her career.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>5. Dr. Dre - $700 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1077\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dr-Dre.jpg\" alt=\"1/7/2009 Las Vegas Nevada, CES -- Dr. Dre, record producer/rapper shows off his new headphones. Note- Mike Snider is writing something on this.  Photo by Tim Loehrke, USAToday (Via MerlinFTP Drop)\" width=\"550\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h3>Emerging into the public eye as a member of the controversial Hip Hop group NWA, Dr. Dre is now one of the most respected names in the Rap scene as well as in the music industry. His record label Aftermath Entertainment is responsible for launching the careers of mega-stars Eminem and 50 Cent. Dr. Dre is also the founder of headphone company Beats Audio, which was sold to Apple for an estimated $3 billion.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>4. Sean Combs (P. Diddy) - $750 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1099\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sean-Combs.jpg\" alt=\"CANNES, FRANCE - MAY 22:  Sean Combs attends the \'Killing Them Softly\' Premiere during 65th Annual Cannes Film Festival at Palais des Festivals on May 22, 2012 in Cannes, France.  (Photo by Gareth Cattermole/Getty Images)\" width=\"385\" height=\"501\" />\r\n<h3>Record producer, singer and businessman Sean Combs has reinvented himself countless times over the course of his career, and so he has managed to stay at the top of the music industry as a household name. Founder of successful record company \"Bad Boy Records\" and owner of his own clothing line \"Sean John\", Sean Combs\' fortune just keeps on rising.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>3. Herb Alpert - $850 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1083\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Herb-Alpert.jpg\" alt=\"herb-alpert\" width=\"509\" height=\"505\" />\r\n<h3>Herb Alpert started in the 1960\'s as a part of the \"Herb Alpert and the Tijuana Grass\" jazz group, and went on to become one of the industry\'s most powerful executives.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>2. Andrew Lloyd Webber – $1.2 Billion</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1073\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Andrew-Lloyd-Webber.jpg\" alt=\"andrew-lloyd-webber\" width=\"502\" height=\"333\" />\r\n<h3>Sir Andrew Lloyd Webber made his fortune composing musicals. Throughout his 50-year career Webber has composed some incredibly iconic music for operas such as \"The Phantom of the Opera\". His company, the Really Useful Group, is one of the largest and most successful theater operators in the United Kingdom.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>1. Paul McCartney – $1.24 Billion</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1102\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Paul-McCartney-2.png\" alt=\"paul-mccartney-2\" width=\"551\" height=\"379\" />\r\n<h3>One of the most popular and respected musicians of the 20<sup>th</sup> century, Paul McCartney started out with The Beatles, where he helped propel them to worldwide and historical success. After the band\'s breakup, McCartney started an almost equally successful solo career, during which the Guinness World Records crowned him \"The most successful composer and recording artist of all time\".  To this day, there is no concert hall in the world that McCartney won\'t be able to fill up completely.</h3>','Top 30 Richest Musicians','','inherit','closed','closed','','1071-revision-v1','','','2017-01-19 19:06:01','2017-01-19 19:06:01','',1071,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1071-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1104,1,'2017-01-19 19:06:54','2017-01-19 19:06:54','<h1>30. 50 Cent – $155 Million</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1072\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/50-Cent.jp