n','closed','','shaq','','','2017-01-22 07:27:47','2017-01-22 07:27:47','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Shaq.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1134,1,'2017-01-22 07:27:55','2017-01-22 07:27:55','','2013 American Ballet Theatre Opening Night Spring Gala - Arrivals','NEW YORK, NY - MAY 13:  Actress Sigourney Weaver attends the American Ballet Theatre opening night Spring Gala at Lincoln Center on May 13, 2013 in New York City.  (Photo by Stephen Lovekin/Getty Images)','inherit','open','closed','','2013-american-ballet-theatre-opening-night-spring-gala-arrivals','','','2017-01-22 07:27:55','2017-01-22 07:27:55','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sigourney.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1135,1,'2017-01-22 07:28:04','2017-01-22 07:28:04','','spike-lee','','inherit','open','closed','','spike-lee','','','2017-01-22 07:28:04','2017-01-22 07:28:04','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/spike-lee.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1136,1,'2017-01-22 07:28:10','2017-01-22 07:28:10','','steve-carell','','inherit','open','closed','','steve-carell','','','2017-01-22 07:28:10','2017-01-22 07:28:10','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/steve-carell.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1137,1,'2017-01-22 07:28:14','2017-01-22 07:28:14','','weird-al','','inherit','open','closed','','weird-al','','','2017-01-22 07:28:14','2017-01-22 07:28:14','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/weird-al.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1138,1,'2017-01-22 07:28:24','2017-01-22 07:28:24','','will','','inherit','open','closed','','will','','','2017-01-22 07:28:24','2017-01-22 07:28:24','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/will.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1139,1,'2017-01-22 07:28:33','2017-01-22 07:28:33','','adam','','inherit','open','closed','','adam','','','2017-01-22 07:28:33','2017-01-22 07:28:33','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/adam.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1140,1,'2017-01-22 07:34:44','2017-01-22 07:34:44','','ashley-judd','','inherit','open','closed','','ashley-judd-2','','','2017-01-22 07:34:44','2017-01-22 07:34:44','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ashley-judd1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1141,1,'2017-01-22 07:38:24','2017-01-22 07:38:24','','chris-martin-singing','','inherit','open','closed','','chris-martin-singing','','','2017-01-22 07:38:24','2017-01-22 07:38:24','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Chris-Martin-singing.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1142,1,'2017-01-22 07:44:52','2017-01-22 07:44:52','','ONeal Degree','Towering over his classmates, former NBA star Shaquille O\'Neal, gestures before the graduation ceremony, Saturday, May 5, 2012 at the James L. Knight Center in Miami. Former NBA star Shaquille O\'Neal is a doctor now. O\'Neal received his doctoral degree in education from Barry University alongside 1,100 other students during commencement ceremonies Saturday. (AP Photo/The Miami Herald, Peter Andrew Bosch)  MAGS OUT','inherit','open','closed','','oneal-degree','','','2017-01-22 07:44:52','2017-01-22 07:44:52','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/shaqdegree.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1143,1,'2017-01-22 07:45:48','2017-01-22 07:45:48','<h2>Some celebs have a little more than just a high school diploma under their belts. They chose to pursue a career in acting or in music eventually, but what were their other career options?</h2>\r\n<h1>30. Shaquille O\'Neal</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1133\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Shaq.jpg\" alt=\"shaq\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>The former NBA superstar promised his mother that he will complete his Bachelor\'s degree after he left LSU for the NBA. He fulfilled that promise in 2000, earning a B.A. in general studies. O\'Neal continued to follow his passion for education in the following years, earning an MBA from the University of Phoenix through online courses, and finally received his Doctorate in Education in 2012.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>29. Ken Jeong</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1126\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Ken-Jeong.jpg\" alt=\"ken-jeong\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\nKen Jeong is known to most people from his iconic roles in films (such as The Hangover trilogy) and in TV series, such as Community. Although stand-up comedy and comedy work in general were his life-long passions, Jeong obtained an M.D. from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 1995. He is a licensed physician for internal medicine in California.<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>28. Sigourney Weaver</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1134\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sigourney.jpg\" alt=\"NEW YORK, NY - MAY 13:  Actress Sigourney Weaver attends the American Ballet Theatre opening night Spring Gala at Lincoln Center on May 13, 2013 in New York City.  (Photo by Stephen Lovekin/Getty Images)\" width=\"328\" height=\"493\" />\r\n<h3>The \"Alien\", \"Ghostbusters\", \"Avatar\" and \"The Ice Storm\" successful actress has a wealth of awards at her disposal, winning seven Golden Globe Awards. Nicknamed \"The Sci-Fi Queen\", Weaver has obtained a Bachelor\'s Degree from Stanford University as well as a Master of Fine Arts degree from Yale University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>27. David Duchovny</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1117\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/David.jpg\" alt=\"david\" width=\"550\" height=\"330\" />\r\n<h3>Before making his breakout role in The X-Files, David Duchovny attended Yale University, where he earned an M.A. in English Literature. He was aiming to obtain a doctorate but gave it up to pursue his acting career.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>26. Dolph Lundgren</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1118\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dolph.jpg\" alt=\"dolph\" width=\"376\" height=\"501\" />\r\n<h3>The Swedish bodybuilder, recognizable to audiences all over the world from films such as Rocky VI and The Expendables, earned his Master\'s in Engineering at the University of Sydney.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>25. Jodie Foster</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1124\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Jodie.jpg\" alt=\"jodie\" width=\"550\" height=\"336\" />\r\n<h3>One of the most prominent actresses of our time, Jodie Foster has appeared in countless memorable films and roles. And despite beginning her acting career in her teens, she made sure to obtain a higher education degree, receiving a B.A. in English Literature from Yale University. She later received an honorary Ph.D. from her alma mater.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>24. Lisa Kudrow</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1127\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/lisa.jpg\" alt=\"TORONTO, ON - SEPTEMBER 16:  Actress Lisa Kudrow from the film \'Love and Other Impossible Pursuits\' poses for a portrait during the 2009 Toronto International Film Festival at The Sutton Place Hotel on September 16, 2009 in Toronto, Canada.\" width=\"344\" height=\"496\" />\r\n<h3>Lisa Kudrow can be considered to be the complete opposite of her dim-witted representation of Phoebe Buffay on TV\'s Friends. Kudrow has a B.Sc. degree in Biology from Vassar College.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>23. Conan O\'Brien</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1115\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/conan.jpg\" alt=\"conan\" width=\"548\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<h3>Popular talk-show host Conan O\'Brien is not only funny, but he is also very smart and sharp. O\'Brian graduated valedictorian from his high school and went on to study at Harvard, where he obtained a B.A. in History and Literature.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>22. Art Garfunkel</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1109\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/art-gar.jpg\" alt=\"art-gar\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>Before he rose to fame as the second half of the legendary musical duo Simon and Garfunkel, Art Garfunkel was serious about his studies. So serious, that he obtained his B.A. in art history in 1962 and his M.A. in mathematics in 1967. He was on his way to earning a doctorate in mathematics education when his musical partnership with Paul Simon reached its height.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>21. Spike Lee</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1135\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/spike-lee.jpg\" alt=\"spike-lee\" width=\"549\" height=\"343\" />\r\n<h3>Widely considered to be one of the most successful African-American directors in Hollywood, Spike Lee has a B.A. in mass communications. After receiving his B.A., Lee attended New York\'s Tisch School of the Arts, where he has earned an M.A. in film and television.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>20. Jerry Springer</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1123\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/jerry-springer.jpg\" alt=\"jerry-springer\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" />\r\n<h3>The controversial host of \"The Jerry Springer Show\" has earned a B.A. in Political Science from Tulane University. He has also earned a Juris Doctor degree from Northwestern University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>19. Ashley Judd</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1140\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ashley-judd1.jpg\" alt=\"ashley-judd\" width=\"550\" height=\"344\" />\r\n<h3>The \"Ruby in Paradise\", \"Norma Jean &amp; Marilyn\" and \"Divergent\" actress has earned a Master\'s Degree in public administration from Harvard. She is also currently working on obtaining a Ph.D. from the University of Berkeley.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>18. Bill Cosby</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1116\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/cosby-bu.jpg\" alt=\"cosby-bu\" width=\"549\" height=\"386\" />\r\n<h3>Comedian, actor and author Bill Cosby has had his fair share of controversy in the past few years. He holds many honorary degrees from various universities, some of which have rescinded those degrees due to the controversy he was involved in. But Cosby can reassure himself that his own, hard earned Ed.D. Degree from the University of Massachusetts will remain at his disposal.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>17. Peter Weller</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1131\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/peter-weller.jpeg\" alt=\"peter-weller\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>Known mainly for his role as the original RoboCop, Peter Weller not only has an M.A. in Renaissance Art, but he also has a Ph.D. in Italian Renaissance Art History.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>16. \"Weird\" Al Yankovic</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1137\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/weird-al.jpg\" alt=\"weird-al\" width=\"549\" height=\"385\" />\r\n<h3>Actor, singer, songwriter, parodist, comedian, satirist, author, and, apparently, also an architect, \"Weird\" Al Yankovic has obtained a B.A. in architecture from the California Polytechnic State University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>15. Graham Chapman</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1121\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/graham-chapman.jpg\" alt=\"graham-chapman\" width=\"519\" height=\"518\" />\r\n<h3>The late Graham Chapman, known for his parts as a member of the legendary comical group Monty Python, was initially torn between pursuing an acting career or continuing on his path for a medical career. He has had an M.D. from St. Bartholomew\'s Hospital Medical School.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>14. Brian May</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1111\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/brian-may.jpg\" alt=\"SONY DSC\" width=\"551\" height=\"414\" />\r\n<h3>Brian May is best known as the lead guitarist of the rock band Queen. While still touring with the remaining living members of the group, May has obtained a Ph.D. in astrophysics and is an active astrophysicist, publishing scientific research papers.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>13. Adam Driver</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1139\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/adam.jpg\" alt=\"adam\" width=\"389\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>Adam Driver broke through in Hollywood with his role as Adam Sackler in the TV show Girls. He was later cast as Kylo Ren, the main antagonist of the new Star Wars trilogy. Before his breakthrough, though, Adam Driver was in the Marines; After he was released from service, he went on to obtain a B.A. in drama from Julliard.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>12. Ludacris</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1128\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/luda.jpg\" alt=\"luda\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>Mostly known for his successful music career during the 2000\'s and for his various roles in films – mainly in the Fast and Furious franchise – Ludacris has a Bachelor\'s degree in Music Management from Georgia State University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>11. Chris Martin</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1141\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Chris-Martin-singing.jpg\" alt=\"chris-martin-singing\" width=\"549\" height=\"424\" />\r\n<h3>Leading singer of the popular British band Coldplay, Chris Martin has attended the University College London, where he\'s earned his Bachelor\'s degree in Greek and Latin.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>10. John Legend</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1125\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/John-Legend.jpg\" alt=\"john-legend\" width=\"357\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>John Legend is an American musician, singer, and songwriter. He is the winner of ten Grammy Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award. He attended the University of Pennsylvania, where he has earned a Bachelor\'s degree in English with an emphasis on African-American literature in 1999.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>9. Brooke Shields</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1112\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Brooke-Shields-ppcorn.jpg\" alt=\"brooke-shields-ppcorn\" width=\"550\" height=\"275\" />\r\n<h3>The American actress and model started acting at the very young age of 12. Shields put her modeling career on hold so she could attend Princeton University, where she obtained a B.A. in Romance Languages.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>8. Edward Norton</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1119\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ed.jpg\" alt=\"ed\" width=\"406\" height=\"499\" />\r\n<h3>Edward Norton has gained fame for acting in some critically approved roles in films such as \"Primal Fears\", \"American History X\", \"Fight Club\" and \"Red Dragon\". He is one of Hollywood\'s most recognizable faces. Norton began acting while attending Yale University, where he studied towards – and eventually gained – a B.A. in History.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>7. Hugh Hefner</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1122\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/heff.jpg\" alt=\"heff\" width=\"550\" height=\"275\" />\r\n<h3>It\'s hard to imagine anyone in the world who is not familiar with the name Hugh Hefner. The founder of Playboy Enterprises, Hefner made a fortune for himself over the years and became one of the most recognizable celebrities in the world. In 1949, Hefner graduated from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign with a B.A. in psychology.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>6. Steve Carell</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1136\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/steve-carell.jpg\" alt=\"steve-carell\" width=\"549\" height=\"331\" />\r\n<h3>Widely regarded as one of the funniest actors in Hollywood, Steve Carell has appeared in dozens of films. He was also the leading actor on the critically acclaimed TV Series \"The Office\". Prior to his career in acting, Carell attended Denison University, where he earned his Bachelor\'s degree in History.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>5. Will Ferrell</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1138\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/will.jpg\" alt=\"will\" width=\"551\" height=\"367\" />\r\n<h3>Another one of Hollywood\'s funniest, Will Ferrell\'s career didn’t always seem to head towards comedy: in 1990 he graduated from the University of Southern California with a B.A. in Sports Information.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>4. James Franco</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1120\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/franco.jpg\" alt=\"NEW YORK, NY - AUGUST 22:  Actor James Franco attends the &quot;Kink&quot; New York Premiere at IFC Center on August 22, 2014 in New York City.  (Photo by Andrew H. Walker/Getty Images)\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>Often playing laid back, careless stoner characters, James Franco does not display the same attitude when it comes to his education. Franco has an M.F.A. degree in writing from Columbia University and is working towards obtaining a Ph.D. in English from Yale University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>3. Mayim Bialik</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1129\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/mayim.jpg\" alt=\"BEVERLY HILLS, CA - AUGUST 24:  Actress Mayim Bialik attends the Television Academy\'s Performers Peer Group Hold Cocktail Reception to Celebrate the 67th Emmy Awards at the Montage Beverly Hills Hotel on August 24, 2015 in Beverly Hills, California.  (Photo by Frederick M. Brown/Getty Images)\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>Although she appears on Television week-in, week-out as part of the cast of the highly popular series \"The Big Bang Theory\", Bialik\'s main focus prior to joining the show was actual science, and she has a Ph.D. in neuroscience to prove it.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>2. Natalie Portman</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1130\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/natalie.jpg\" alt=\"natalie\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>The Academy Award winning talented actress has made her mark on Hollywood over the past two decades. Before that, though, she has attended Harvard University, where she obtained a B.A. degree in psychology.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>1. Rowan Atkinson</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1132\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/rowan.jpg\" alt=\"rowan\" width=\"549\" height=\"288\" />\r\n<h3>The character of Mr. Bean is far from a truthful representation of the multitalented and brilliant Rowan Atkinson. The British actor actually has a Master\'s degree in Electrical Engineering from The Queen\'s College in Oxford. It appears he is as smart as he is funny.</h3>','Celebs With Higher Education Degrees That You Didn\'t Know About','','inherit','closed','closed','','1108-revision-v1','','','2017-01-22 07:45:48','2017-01-22 07:45:48','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1108-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1144,1,'2017-01-22 07:46:36','2017-01-22 07:46:36','<h2>Some celebs have a little more than just a high school diploma under their belts. They chose to pursue a career in acting or in music eventually, but what were their other career options?</h2>\r\n<h1>30. Shaquille O\'Neal</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1133\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Shaq.jpg\" alt=\"shaq\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>The former NBA superstar promised his mother that he will complete his Bachelor\'s degree after he left LSU for the NBA. He fulfilled that promise in 2000, earning a B.A. in general studies. O\'Neal continued to follow his passion for education in the following years, earning an MBA from the University of Phoenix through online courses, and finally received his Doctorate in Education in 2012.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>29. Ken Jeong</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1126\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Ken-Jeong.jpg\" alt=\"ken-jeong\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>Ken Jeong is known to most people from his iconic roles in films (such as The Hangover trilogy) and in TV series, such as Community. Although stand-up comedy and comedy work in general were his life-long passions, Jeong obtained an M.D. from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 1995. He is a licensed physician for internal medicine in California.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>28. Sigourney Weaver</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1134\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Sigourney.jpg\" alt=\"NEW YORK, NY - MAY 13: Actress Sigourney Weaver attends the American Ballet Theatre opening night Spring Gala at Lincoln Center on May 13, 2013 in New York City. (Photo by Stephen Lovekin/Getty Images)\" width=\"328\" height=\"493\" />\r\n<h3>The \"Alien\", \"Ghostbusters\", \"Avatar\" and \"The Ice Storm\" successful actress has a wealth of awards at her disposal, winning seven Golden Globe Awards. Nicknamed \"The Sci-Fi Queen\", Weaver has obtained a Bachelor\'s Degree from Stanford University as well as a Master of Fine Arts degree from Yale University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>27. David Duchovny</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1117\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/David.jpg\" alt=\"david\" width=\"550\" height=\"330\" />\r\n<h3>Before making his breakout role in The X-Files, David Duchovny attended Yale University, where he earned an M.A. in English Literature. He was aiming to obtain a doctorate but gave it up to pursue his acting career.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>26. Dolph Lundgren</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1118\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dolph.jpg\" alt=\"dolph\" width=\"376\" height=\"501\" />\r\n<h3>The Swedish bodybuilder, recognizable to audiences all over the world from films such as Rocky VI and The Expendables, earned his Master\'s in Engineering at the University of Sydney.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>25. Jodie Foster</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1124\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Jodie.jpg\" alt=\"jodie\" width=\"550\" height=\"336\" />\r\n<h3>One of the most prominent actresses of our time, Jodie Foster has appeared in countless memorable films and roles. And despite beginning her acting career in her teens, she made sure to obtain a higher education degree, receiving a B.A. in English Literature from Yale University. She later received an honorary Ph.D. from her alma mater.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>24. Lisa Kudrow</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1127\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/lisa.jpg\" alt=\"TORONTO, ON - SEPTEMBER 16: Actress Lisa Kudrow from the film \'Love and Other Impossible Pursuits\' poses for a portrait during the 2009 Toronto International Film Festival at The Sutton Place Hotel on September 16, 2009 in Toronto, Canada.\" width=\"344\" height=\"496\" />\r\n<h3>Lisa Kudrow can be considered to be the complete opposite of her dim-witted representation of Phoebe Buffay on TV\'s Friends. Kudrow has a B.Sc. degree in Biology from Vassar College.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>23. Conan O\'Brien</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1115\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/conan.jpg\" alt=\"conan\" width=\"548\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<h3>Popular talk-show host Conan O\'Brien is not only funny, but he is also very smart and sharp. O\'Brian graduated valedictorian from his high school and went on to study at Harvard, where he obtained a B.A. in History and Literature.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>22. Art Garfunkel</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1109\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/art-gar.jpg\" alt=\"art-gar\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>Before he rose to fame as the second half of the legendary musical duo Simon and Garfunkel, Art Garfunkel was serious about his studies. So serious, that he obtained his B.A. in art history in 1962 and his M.A. in mathematics in 1967. He was on his way to earning a doctorate in mathematics education when his musical partnership with Paul Simon reached its height.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>21. Spike Lee</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1135\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/spike-lee.jpg\" alt=\"spike-lee\" width=\"549\" height=\"343\" />\r\n<h3>Widely considered to be one of the most successful African-American directors in Hollywood, Spike Lee has a B.A. in mass communications. After receiving his B.A., Lee attended New York\'s Tisch School of the Arts, where he has earned an M.A. in film and television.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>20. Jerry Springer</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1123\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/jerry-springer.jpg\" alt=\"jerry-springer\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" />\r\n<h3>The controversial host of \"The Jerry Springer Show\" has earned a B.A. in Political Science from Tulane University. He has also earned a Juris Doctor degree from Northwestern University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>19. Ashley Judd</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1140\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ashley-judd1.jpg\" alt=\"ashley-judd\" width=\"550\" height=\"344\" />\r\n<h3>The \"Ruby in Paradise\", \"Norma Jean &amp; Marilyn\" and \"Divergent\" actress has earned a Master\'s Degree in public administration from Harvard. She is also currently working on obtaining a Ph.D. from the University of Berkeley.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>18. Bill Cosby</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1116\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/cosby-bu.jpg\" alt=\"cosby-bu\" width=\"549\" height=\"386\" />\r\n<h3>Comedian, actor and author Bill Cosby has had his fair share of controversy in the past few years. He holds many honorary degrees from various universities, some of which have rescinded those degrees due to the controversy he was involved in. But Cosby can reassure himself that his own, hard earned Ed.D. Degree from the University of Massachusetts will remain at his disposal.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>17. Peter Weller</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1131\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/peter-weller.jpeg\" alt=\"peter-weller\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>Known mainly for his role as the original RoboCop, Peter Weller not only has an M.A. in Renaissance Art, but he also has a Ph.D. in Italian Renaissance Art History.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>16. \"Weird\" Al Yankovic</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1137\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/weird-al.jpg\" alt=\"weird-al\" width=\"549\" height=\"385\" />\r\n<h3>Actor, singer, songwriter, parodist, comedian, satirist, author, and, apparently, also an architect, \"Weird\" Al Yankovic has obtained a B.A. in architecture from the California Polytechnic State University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>15. Graham Chapman</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1121\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/graham-chapman.jpg\" alt=\"graham-chapman\" width=\"519\" height=\"518\" />\r\n<h3>The late Graham Chapman, known for his parts as a member of the legendary comical group Monty Python, was initially torn between pursuing an acting career or continuing on his path for a medical career. He has had an M.D. from St. Bartholomew\'s Hospital Medical School.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>14. Brian May</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1111\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/brian-may.jpg\" alt=\"SONY DSC\" width=\"551\" height=\"414\" />\r\n<h3>Brian May is best known as the lead guitarist of the rock band Queen. While still touring with the remaining living members of the group, May has obtained a Ph.D. in astrophysics and is an active astrophysicist, publishing scientific research papers.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>13. Adam Driver</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1139\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/adam.jpg\" alt=\"adam\" width=\"389\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>Adam Driver broke through in Hollywood with his role as Adam Sackler in the TV show Girls. He was later cast as Kylo Ren, the main antagonist of the new Star Wars trilogy. Before his breakthrough, though, Adam Driver was in the Marines; After he was released from service, he went on to obtain a B.A. in drama from Julliard.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>12. Ludacris</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1128\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/luda.jpg\" alt=\"luda\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>Mostly known for his successful music career during the 2000\'s and for his various roles in films – mainly in the Fast and Furious franchise – Ludacris has a Bachelor\'s degree in Music Management from Georgia State University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>11. Chris Martin</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1141\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Chris-Martin-singing.jpg\" alt=\"chris-martin-singing\" width=\"549\" height=\"424\" />\r\n<h3>Leading singer of the popular British band Coldplay, Chris Martin has attended the University College London, where he\'s earned his Bachelor\'s degree in Greek and Latin.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>10. John Legend</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1125\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/John-Legend.jpg\" alt=\"john-legend\" width=\"357\" height=\"500\" />\r\n<h3>John Legend is an American musician, singer, and songwriter. He is the winner of ten Grammy Awards, as well as a Golden Globe Award and an Academy Award. He attended the University of Pennsylvania, where he has earned a Bachelor\'s degree in English with an emphasis on African-American literature in 1999.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>9. Brooke Shields</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1112\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Brooke-Shields-ppcorn.jpg\" alt=\"brooke-shields-ppcorn\" width=\"550\" height=\"275\" />\r\n<h3>The American actress and model started acting at the very young age of 12. Shields put her modeling career on hold so she could attend Princeton University, where she obtained a B.A. in Romance Languages.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>8. Edward Norton</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1119\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/ed.jpg\" alt=\"ed\" width=\"406\" height=\"499\" />\r\n<h3>Edward Norton has gained fame for acting in some critically approved roles in films such as \"Primal Fears\", \"American History X\", \"Fight Club\" and \"Red Dragon\". He is one of Hollywood\'s most recognizable faces. Norton began acting while attending Yale University, where he studied towards – and eventually gained – a B.A. in History.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>7. Hugh Hefner</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1122\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/heff.jpg\" alt=\"heff\" width=\"550\" height=\"275\" />\r\n<h3>It\'s hard to imagine anyone in the world who is not familiar with the name Hugh Hefner. The founder of Playboy Enterprises, Hefner made a fortune for himself over the years and became one of the most recognizable celebrities in the world. In 1949, Hefner graduated from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign with a B.A. in psychology.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>6. Steve Carell</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1136\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/steve-carell.jpg\" alt=\"steve-carell\" width=\"549\" height=\"331\" />\r\n<h3>Widely regarded as one of the funniest actors in Hollywood, Steve Carell has appeared in dozens of films. He was also the leading actor on the critically acclaimed TV Series \"The Office\". Prior to his career in acting, Carell attended Denison University, where he earned his Bachelor\'s degree in History.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>5. Will Ferrell</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1138\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/will.jpg\" alt=\"will\" width=\"551\" height=\"367\" />\r\n<h3>Another one of Hollywood\'s funniest, Will Ferrell\'s career didn’t always seem to head towards comedy: in 1990 he graduated from the University of Southern California with a B.A. in Sports Information.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>4. James Franco</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1120\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/franco.jpg\" alt=\"NEW YORK, NY - AUGUST 22: Actor James Franco attends the &quot;Kink&quot; New York Premiere at IFC Center on August 22, 2014 in New York City. (Photo by Andrew H. Walker/Getty Images)\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" />\r\n<h3>Often playing laid back, careless stoner characters, James Franco does not display the same attitude when it comes to his education. Franco has an M.F.A. degree in writing from Columbia University and is working towards obtaining a Ph.D. in English from Yale University.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>3. Mayim Bialik</h1>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1129\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/mayim.jpg\" alt=\"BEVERLY HILLS, CA - AUGUST 24: Actress Mayim Bialik attends the Television Academy\'s Performers Peer Group Hold Cocktail Reception to Celebrate the 67th Emmy Awards at the Montage Beverly Hills Hotel on August 24, 2015 in Beverly Hills, California. (Photo by Frederick M. Brown/Getty Images)\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>Although she appears on Television week-in, week-out as part of the cast of the highly popular series \"The Big Bang Theory\", Bialik\'s main focus prior to joining the show was actual science, and she has a Ph.D. in neuroscience to prove it.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>2. Natalie Portman</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1130\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/natalie.jpg\" alt=\"natalie\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" />\r\n<h3>The Academy Award winning talented actress has made her mark on Hollywood over the past two decades. Before that, though, she has attended Harvard University, where she obtained a B.A. degree in psychology.<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>1. Rowan Atkinson</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1132\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/rowan.jpg\" alt=\"rowan\" width=\"549\" height=\"288\" />\r\n<h3>The character of Mr. Bean is far from a truthful representation of the multitalented and brilliant Rowan Atkinson. The British actor actually has a Master\'s degree in Electrical Engineering from The Queen\'s College in Oxford. It appears he is as smart as he is funny.</h3>','Celebs With Higher Education Degrees That You Didn\'t Know About','','inherit','closed','closed','','1108-revision-v1','','','2017-01-22 07:46:36','2017-01-22 07:46:36','',1108,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1108-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1145,1,'2017-01-22 08:08:17','2017-01-22 08:08:17','','anna-kendrick','','inherit','open','closed','','anna-kendrick','','','2017-01-22 08:08:17','2017-01-22 08:08:17','',1113,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/anna-kendrick.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1146,1,'2017-01-22 08:08:25','2017-01-22 08:08:25','','billie','','inherit','open','closed','','billie','','','2017-01-22 08:08:25','2017-01-22 08:08:25','',1113,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/billie.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1147,1,'2017-01-22 08:08:37','2017-01-22 08:08:37','','bradley','','inherit','open','closed','','bradley','','','2017-01-22 08:08:37','2017-01-22 08: