283,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/171.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1327,2,'2017-01-26 11:37:54','2017-01-26 11:37:54','','28','','inherit','open','closed','','28-2','','','2017-01-26 11:37:54','2017-01-26 11:37:54','',1283,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/281.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1328,2,'2017-01-26 11:42:09','2017-01-26 11:42:09','<h2>\"Neighbours\" is one of Australian TV\'s longest-running and most successful daytime soaps. The show has been running from 1985 and has aired over 7,000 episodes to this day. With such a long time in the running, it\'s intriguing to stop and look where some of the show\'s cast are today.</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Guy Pearce – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Guy Pearce was one of the original members of the cast, and the show jumpstarted his acting career. He remained on the show for four years and portrayed the character of Mike Young.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1284\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/110.jpg\" alt=\"1\" width=\"290\" height=\"440\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Guy Pearce – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>After leaving \"Neighbours\", Pearce moved to Hollywood, where he managed to get into the movie business and landed roles in some big-budgeted motion pictures. He appeared in some memorable roles in films such as \"Memento\", \"L.A. Confidential\", and \"The Hurt Locker\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1285\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/27.jpg\" alt=\"2\" width=\"302\" height=\"434\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Liam Hemsworth - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Liam Hemsworth also got his career started as a member of the \"Neighbours\" cast. He was on the show for one season, during which he portrayed Bridget Parker\'s love interest, Josh Taylor.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1286\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/310.jpg\" alt=\"3\" width=\"306\" height=\"352\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Liam Hemsworth - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Liam has also moved to bigger and brighter pastures in Hollywood soon after leaving the show. He has found success in Hollywood as well, playing in the blockbuster saga of \"The Hunger Games\" films as well as in \"The Last Song\" and \"The Elephant Princess\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1287\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/48.jpg\" alt=\"4\" width=\"302\" height=\"334\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Madeleine West - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Madeleine\'s story regarding \"Neighbours\" is a truly spectacular one, as she got her role as Dee Bliss on the show just three days after getting an agent for the first time.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1288\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/510.jpg\" alt=\"5\" width=\"550\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Madeleine West - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Madeleine has been away from \"Neighbours\" for a few years as she wanted to raise a family – in which she found great success, giving birth to 6 children. She recently got back to the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1289\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/67.jpg\" alt=\"6\" width=\"549\" height=\"330\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Jesse Spencer - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Famous actor Jesse Spencer also got his career started starring in \"Neighbours\". He spent six years on the show, portraying the character of Billy Kennedy, Libby, and Malcolm Kennedy\'s younger brother.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1290\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/71.jpg\" alt=\"7\" width=\"550\" height=\"343\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Jesse Spencer - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Jesse moved to Hollywood like many of his fellow \"Neighbours\" alumni. He enjoyed tremendous success on the critically acclaimed series \"House M.D.\" where he portrayed the character of Robert Chase, and can currently be seen acting in the series \"Chicago Fire\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1322\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/82.jpg\" alt=\"8\" width=\"550\" height=\"412\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Imbruglia - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>A young Natalie Imbruglia starred on the show as café/construction worker Beth, who had a complicated love life and went through some difficult relationships on the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1292\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/91.jpg\" alt=\"9\" width=\"304\" height=\"371\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Imbruglia - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Natalie continued with her acting career after leaving the show but found the most success in music. She developed a career as a singer and has released five albums to date.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1293\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/101.jpg\" alt=\"10\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Delta Goodrem – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Delta Goodrem portrayed the shy Nina Tucker on the show. As the show went on, her character evolved and became more and more confident in herself.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1294\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/111.jpg\" alt=\"11\" width=\"302\" height=\"401\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Delta Goodrem - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Delta followed the example of her character Nina Tucker and became a singer. She has released several well-received songs while continuing to act in between. She was also appointed as a judge on \"The Voice Australia\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1295\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/121.jpg\" alt=\"12\" width=\"302\" height=\"399\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Alan Dale - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Alan Dale was one of the show\'s most devoted actors, as he appeared in over 800 episodes. He starred as Jim Robinson, who eventually died of a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1296\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/131.jpg\" alt=\"13\" width=\"301\" height=\"408\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Alan Dale - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Alan Dale found great success after being written off of the show, and has appeared in several TV series - such as \"Once Upon a Time\" and \"NCIS\" - and films, such as \"Captain America: The Winter Soldier\" and \"The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1297\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/141.jpg\" alt=\"14\" width=\"550\" height=\"396\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dichen Lachman - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>The talented actress Dichen Lachman portrayed Rachel and Zeke Kinski\'s older sister, the rebellious Katya, for a whopping 103 episodes.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1298\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/151.jpg\" alt=\"15\" width=\"399\" height=\"327\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dichen Lachman - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Dichen\'s career has only gone upwards as time went by, as she has appeared in several successful TV series, such as \"Dollhouse\", \"The 100\", \"Shameless\" and \"Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1299\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/161.jpg\" alt=\"16\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Stefan Dennis – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>One of \"Neighbours\" original cast members and longest-serving cast members, Stefan Dennis portrays the much-loved character of Paul Robinson to this day.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1326\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/171.jpg\" alt=\"17\" width=\"549\" height=\"309\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Stefan Dennis – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Stefan has appeared in over 3,100 episodes of the show to this day, and has been its devoted cast member for over 30 years. He makes appearances on other shows from time to time, but his main commitment is and always has been to \"Neighbours\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1325\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/181.jpg\" alt=\"18\" width=\"472\" height=\"323\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Craig McLachlan - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Craig McLachlan is a Gold Logie award-winning actor, musician, singer and composer. He portrayed the curly haired Henry Ramsay on the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1300\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/191.jpg\" alt=\"19\" width=\"303\" height=\"374\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Craig McLachlan – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Nowadays Craig McLachlan is acting again after taking a hiatus to try his luck in music. He has continued to star in soap shows, and can be seen today on the show \"The Doctor Blake Mysteries\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1301\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/201.jpg\" alt=\"20\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Leah de Niese - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Leah de Niese joined the show\'s cast when she was only eleven years old. She appeared on the show as Miranda Starvaggi from 1994 all the way to 2001.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1302\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/211.jpg\" alt=\"21\" width=\"319\" height=\"479\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Leah de Niese - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Nowadays Leah has already passed the age of 30. She mostly keeps to herself, and tries to stay away from the limelight. She was last seen in a supporting role on the show \"Twentysomething\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1303\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/221.jpg\" alt=\"22\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Tom Oliver – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Tom Oliver is one of \"Neighbours\" longest-serving cast members, joining in 1985 and appearing in over 2,800 episodes to this day.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1304\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/231.jpg\" alt=\"23\" width=\"396\" height=\"471\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Tom Oliver – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Tom Oliver quit the show at the age of 78, after almost 20 years of playing the role of lovable rogue Lou Carpenter. His final appearance on \"Neighbours\" came in December 2016.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1305\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/241.jpg\" alt=\"24\" width=\"345\" height=\"481\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dean Geyer – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Dean Geyer was a contestant of \"Australian Idol\" before joining the show. He portrayed the character of Ty Harper while in \"Neighbours\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1306\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/251.jpg\" alt=\"25\" width=\"472\" height=\"324\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Dean Geyer – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>After his story arc on the show was completed, Geyer left for the US and joined the highly successful TV show \"Glee\", where he portrayed the character of Brody Weston.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1307\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/26.jpeg\" alt=\"26\" width=\"303\" height=\"407\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>David Hoflin – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Swedish-born David Hoflin joined the cast of \"Neighbours\" for one year in 2007. He played the character of Oliver Barns on the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1308\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/27.png\" alt=\"27\" width=\"331\" height=\"416\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>David Hoflin – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>David went on to appear in some very successful TV series, such as \"Supernatural\", \"Hawaii Five-O\", \"Crossbones\" and \"American Crime\". He can now be spotted portraying the main character of F. Scott Fitzgerald on Amazon\'s period drama series \"Z: The Beginning of Everything\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1327\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/281.jpg\" alt=\"28\" width=\"316\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Ben Mendelson – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Ben Mendelson appeared on the show for one year between 1986 and 1987. He portrayed the character of Warren Murphy, but left the show after just 19 episodes to star in the film that turned out to give him his big breakthrough – \"The Year My Voice Broke\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1309\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/291.jpg\" alt=\"29\" width=\"295\" height=\"437\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Ben Mendelson – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Mendelson went on to have a very successful career both in Australia and in Hollywood. He has appeared in some major blockbusters these past few years in particular – with \"The Dark Knight Rises\" and the \"Star Wars\" anthology film \"Rogue One\" as examples.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1310\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/301.jpg\" alt=\"Premiere of the new Netflix original series \'Bloodline\' at the SVA Theatre - Red Carpet Arrivals Featuring: Ben Mendelsohn Where: New York City, New York, United States When: 03 Mar 2015 Credit: Ivan Nikolov/WENN.com\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>James Sorensen – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>A more recent member of the show\'s cast, James Sorensen has appeared on the show as the teenage single father Declan Napier.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1311\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/311.jpg\" alt=\"31\" width=\"334\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>James Sorensen – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>James has pretty much moved on from acting, choosing to become a doctor instead. He currently attends university in order to obtain his medical degree.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1312\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/321.jpg\" alt=\"32\" width=\"421\" height=\"470\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Bassingthwaighte - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Natalie\'s character on the show was the crazy Isabelle \"Izzy\" Hoyland. Her character provided some controversial and crazy storylines to the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1313\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/331.jpg\" alt=\"Editorial Use Only / No Merchandising  Mandatory Credit: Photo by FremantleMedia Ltd/REX (853826kg)  \'Neighbours\'    Stefan Dennis and Natalie Bassingthwaighte  Grundy TV Archives\" width=\"550\" height=\"344\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Bassingthwaighte - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>After leaving the show, Natalie decided to branch out into music alongside her acting career. She enjoyed some success in music, and was chosen to be one of the judges on the Australian version of \"The X-Factor\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1314\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/341.jpg\" alt=\"34\" width=\"314\" height=\"471\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Radha Mitchell - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Radha Mitchell started her (now long and prosperous) career on \"Neighbours\" in 1994 at the mere age of 21. She stayed on the show for 3 years, during which she portrayed the character of Catherine O\'Brien.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1315\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/35.png\" alt=\"35\" width=\"549\" height=\"472\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Radha Mitchell - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Radha went on to have a very successful career which is still in full swing even today. She has appeared in \"Man on Fire\", \"Finding Neverland\", \"Pitch Black\", \"Silent Hill\" and \"Surrogates\", and has won several awards.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1316\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/361.jpg\" alt=\"36\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Margot Robbie - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Hollywood hotshot Margot Robbie has also started her career with a role on \"Neighbours\". She portrayed Donna Freedman, a groupie who was overly-obsessed with Ty Harper, on the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1317\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/371.jpg\" alt=\"37\" width=\"331\" height=\"472\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Margot Robbie - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Margot has really made it in Hollywood these past few years and is considered one of the hottest names around in the industry. She had roles in \"The Wolf of Wall Street\", \"The Legend of Tarzan\", \"Focus\" and \"Suicide Squad\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1318\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/381.jpg\" alt=\"Mandatory Credit: Photo by Jim Smeal/BEI/BEI/Shutterstock (3511922jh) Margot Robbie 19th Annual Critics\' Choice Movie Awards, Arrivals, Los Angeles, America - 16 Jan 2014\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Kylie Minogue - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Kylie Minogue appeared on the show in the early stages of her career. She portrayed the character of Charlene \"Lenny\" Robinson.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1319\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/391.jpg\" alt=\"39\" width=\"328\" height=\"410\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Kylie Minogue - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Kylie Minogue enjoyed tremendous success in her career and became a pop icon. She has continued to act from time to time, but her main focus was her musical career, during which she had released 13 albums and countless hit songs.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1320\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/401.jpg\" alt=\"40\" width=\"379\" height=\"474\" />','The \"Neighbours\" Cast – Then & Now','','inherit','closed','closed','','1283-revision-v1','','','2017-01-26 11:42:09','2017-01-26 11:42:09','',1283,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1283-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1329,2,'2017-01-26 11:43:11','2017-01-26 11:43:11','<h2>\"Neighbours\" is one of Australian TV\'s longest-running and most successful daytime soaps. The show has been running from 1985 and has aired over 7,000 episodes to this day. With such a long time in the running, it\'s intriguing to stop and look where some of the show\'s cast are today.</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Guy Pearce – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Guy Pearce was one of the original members of the cast, and the show jumpstarted his acting career. He remained on the show for four years and portrayed the character of Mike Young.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1284\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/110.jpg\" alt=\"1\" width=\"290\" height=\"440\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Guy Pearce – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>After leaving \"Neighbours\", Pearce moved to Hollywood, where he managed to get into the movie business and landed roles in some big-budgeted motion pictures. He appeared in some memorable roles in films such as \"Memento\", \"L.A. Confidential\", and \"The Hurt Locker\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1285\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/27.jpg\" alt=\"2\" width=\"302\" height=\"434\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Liam Hemsworth - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Liam Hemsworth also got his career started as a member of the \"Neighbours\" cast. He was on the show for one season, during which he portrayed Bridget Parker\'s love interest, Josh Taylor.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1286\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/310.jpg\" alt=\"3\" width=\"306\" height=\"352\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Liam Hemsworth - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Liam has also moved to bigger and brighter pastures in Hollywood soon after leaving