uploads/2017/01/82.jpg\" alt=\"8\" width=\"550\" height=\"412\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Imbruglia - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>A young Natalie Imbruglia starred on the show as café/construction worker Beth, who had a complicated love life and went through some difficult relationships on the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1292\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/91.jpg\" alt=\"9\" width=\"304\" height=\"371\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Imbruglia - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Natalie continued with her acting career after leaving the show but found the most success in music. She developed a career as a singer and has released five albums to date.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1293\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/101.jpg\" alt=\"10\" width=\"549\" height=\"366\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Delta Goodrem – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Delta Goodrem portrayed the shy Nina Tucker on the show. As the show went on, her character evolved and became more and more confident in herself.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1294\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/111.jpg\" alt=\"11\" width=\"302\" height=\"401\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Delta Goodrem - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Delta followed the example of her character Nina Tucker and became a singer. She has released several well-received songs while continuing to act in between. She was also appointed as a judge on \"The Voice Australia\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1295\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/121.jpg\" alt=\"12\" width=\"302\" height=\"399\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Alan Dale - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Alan Dale was one of the show\'s most devoted actors, as he appeared in over 800 episodes. He starred as Jim Robinson, who eventually died of a heart attack.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1296\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/131.jpg\" alt=\"13\" width=\"301\" height=\"408\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Alan Dale - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Alan Dale found great success after being written off of the show, and has appeared in several TV series - such as \"Once Upon a Time\" and \"NCIS\" - and films, such as \"Captain America: The Winter Soldier\" and \"The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1297\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/141.jpg\" alt=\"14\" width=\"550\" height=\"396\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dichen Lachman - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>The talented actress Dichen Lachman portrayed Rachel and Zeke Kinski\'s older sister, the rebellious Katya, for a whopping 103 episodes.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1298\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/151.jpg\" alt=\"15\" width=\"399\" height=\"327\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dichen Lachman - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Dichen\'s career has only gone upwards as time went by, as she has appeared in several successful TV series, such as \"Dollhouse\", \"The 100\", \"Shameless\" and \"Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1299\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/161.jpg\" alt=\"16\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Stefan Dennis – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>One of \"Neighbours\" original cast members and longest-serving cast members, Stefan Dennis portrays the much-loved character of Paul Robinson to this day.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1326\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/171.jpg\" alt=\"17\" width=\"549\" height=\"309\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Stefan Dennis – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Stefan has appeared in over 3,100 episodes of the show to this day, and has been its devoted cast member for over 30 years. He makes appearances on other shows from time to time, but his main commitment is and always has been to \"Neighbours\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1325\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/181.jpg\" alt=\"18\" width=\"472\" height=\"323\" />\r\n<!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Craig McLachlan - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Craig McLachlan is a Gold Logie award-winning actor, musician, singer and composer. He portrayed the curly haired Henry Ramsay on the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1300\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/191.jpg\" alt=\"19\" width=\"303\" height=\"374\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Craig McLachlan – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Nowadays Craig McLachlan is acting again after taking a hiatus to try his luck in music. He has continued to star in soap shows, and can be seen today on the show \"The Doctor Blake Mysteries\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1301\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/201.jpg\" alt=\"20\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Leah de Niese - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Leah de Niese joined the show\'s cast when she was only eleven years old. She appeared on the show as Miranda Starvaggi from 1994 all the way to 2001.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1302\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/211.jpg\" alt=\"21\" width=\"319\" height=\"479\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Leah de Niese - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Nowadays Leah has already passed the age of 30. She mostly keeps to herself, and tries to stay away from the limelight. She was last seen in a supporting role on the show \"Twentysomething\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1303\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/221.jpg\" alt=\"22\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Tom Oliver – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Tom Oliver is one of \"Neighbours\" longest-serving cast members, joining in 1985 and appearing in over 2,800 episodes to this day.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1304\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/231.jpg\" alt=\"23\" width=\"396\" height=\"471\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Tom Oliver – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Tom Oliver quit the show at the age of 78, after almost 20 years of playing the role of lovable rogue Lou Carpenter. His final appearance on \"Neighbours\" came in December 2016.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1305\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/241.jpg\" alt=\"24\" width=\"345\" height=\"481\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dean Geyer – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Dean Geyer was a contestant of \"Australian Idol\" before joining the show. He portrayed the character of Ty Harper while in \"Neighbours\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1306\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/251.jpg\" alt=\"25\" width=\"472\" height=\"324\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Dean Geyer – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>After his story arc on the show was completed, Geyer left for the US and joined the highly successful TV show \"Glee\", where he portrayed the character of Brody Weston.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1307\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/26.jpeg\" alt=\"26\" width=\"303\" height=\"407\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>David Hoflin – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Swedish-born David Hoflin joined the cast of \"Neighbours\" for one year in 2007. He played the character of Oliver Barns on the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1308\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/27.png\" alt=\"27\" width=\"331\" height=\"416\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>David Hoflin – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>David went on to appear in some very successful TV series, such as \"Supernatural\", \"Hawaii Five-O\", \"Crossbones\" and \"American Crime\". He can now be spotted portraying the main character of F. Scott Fitzgerald on Amazon\'s period drama series \"Z: The Beginning of Everything\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1327\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/281.jpg\" alt=\"28\" width=\"316\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Ben Mendelson – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Ben Mendelson appeared on the show for one year between 1986 and 1987. He portrayed the character of Warren Murphy, but left the show after just 19 episodes to star in the film that turned out to give him his big breakthrough – \"The Year My Voice Broke\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1309\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/291.jpg\" alt=\"29\" width=\"295\" height=\"437\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Ben Mendelson – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Mendelson went on to have a very successful career both in Australia and in Hollywood. He has appeared in some major blockbusters these past few years in particular – with \"The Dark Knight Rises\" and the \"Star Wars\" anthology film \"Rogue One\" as examples.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1310\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/301.jpg\" alt=\"Premiere of the new Netflix original series \'Bloodline\' at the SVA Theatre - Red Carpet Arrivals Featuring: Ben Mendelsohn Where: New York City, New York, United States When: 03 Mar 2015 Credit: Ivan Nikolov/WENN.com\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>James Sorensen – Then</h1>\r\n<h3>A more recent member of the show\'s cast, James Sorensen has appeared on the show as the teenage single father Declan Napier.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1311\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/311.jpg\" alt=\"31\" width=\"334\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>James Sorensen – Now</h1>\r\n<h3>James has pretty much moved on from acting, choosing to become a doctor instead. He currently attends university in order to obtain his medical degree.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1312\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/321.jpg\" alt=\"32\" width=\"421\" height=\"470\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Bassingthwaighte - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Natalie\'s character on the show was the crazy Isabelle \"Izzy\" Hoyland. Her character provided some controversial and crazy storylines to the show.</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1313\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/331.jpg\" alt=\"Editorial Use Only / No Merchandising Mandatory Credit: Photo by FremantleMedia Ltd/REX (853826kg) \'Neighbours\' Stefan Dennis and Natalie Bassingthwaighte Grundy TV Archives\" width=\"550\" height=\"344\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Natalie Bassingthwaighte - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>After leaving the show, Natalie decided to branch out into music alongside her acting career. She enjoyed some success in music, and was chosen to be one of the judges on the Australian version of \"The X-Factor\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1314\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/341.jpg\" alt=\"34\" width=\"314\" height=\"471\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Radha Mitchell - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Radha Mitchell started her (now long and prosperous) career on \"Neighbours\" in 1994 at the mere age of 21. She stayed on the show for 3 years, during which she portrayed the character of Catherine O\'Brien.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1315\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/35.png\" alt=\"35\" width=\"549\" height=\"472\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Radha Mitchell - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Radha went on to have a very successful career which is still in full swing even today. She has appeared in \"Man on Fire\", \"Finding Neverland\", \"Pitch Black\", \"Silent Hill\" and \"Surrogates\", and has won several awards.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1316\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/361.jpg\" alt=\"36\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Margot Robbie - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Hollywood hotshot Margot Robbie has also started her career with a role on \"Neighbours\". She portrayed Donna Freedman, a groupie who was overly-obsessed with Ty Harper, on the show.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1317\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/371.jpg\" alt=\"37\" width=\"331\" height=\"472\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Margot Robbie - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Margot has really made it in Hollywood these past few years and is considered one of the hottest names around in the industry. She had roles in \"The Wolf of Wall Street\", \"The Legend of Tarzan\", \"Focus\" and \"Suicide Squad\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-1318\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/381.jpg\" alt=\"Mandatory Credit: Photo by Jim Smeal/BEI/BEI/Shutterstock (3511922jh) Margot Robbie 19th Annual Critics\' Choice Movie Awards, Arrivals, Los Angeles, America - 16 Jan 2014\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<h3><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Kylie Minogue - Then</h1>\r\n<h3>Kylie Minogue appeared on the show in the early stages of her career. She portrayed the character of Charlene \"Lenny\" Robinson.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1319\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/391.jpg\" alt=\"39\" width=\"328\" height=\"410\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Kylie Minogue - Now</h1>\r\n<h3>Kylie Minogue enjoyed tremendous success in her career and became a pop icon. She has continued to act from time to time, but her main focus was her musical career, during which she had released 13 albums and countless hit songs.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1320\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/401.jpg\" alt=\"40\" width=\"379\" height=\"474\" />','The \"Neighbours\" Cast – Then & Now','','inherit','closed','closed','','1283-revision-v1','','','2017-01-26 11:43:11','2017-01-26 11:43:11','',1283,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/1283-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1330,2,'2017-01-27 09:17:08','2017-01-27 09:17:08','<h2>Law &amp; Order is undoubtedly one of the television\'s most beloved shows ever. It had it all – action, suspense, drama, romance, tragedy and more. The love for the show is undeniable, as although it ended some years ago, you can still catch reruns of it on a variety of TV channels. Many actors and actresses appeared on the show; some stayed, some left. Check out our list of where all of the show\'s cast members are now.</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Richard Belzer</h1>\r\n<h3>Richard Belzer has been a truly faithful member of the cast, as he played the character of Detective John Munch for almost 23 years on the show. Nowadays the veteran actor can still be seen on TV, this time on Netflix\'s \"The Unbreakable Kimmie Schmidt\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1331\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/112.jpg\" alt=\"1\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" />  <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Vincent D\'Onofrio</h1>\r\n<h3>Vincent D\'Onofrio was on the show \"Law and Order: Criminal Intent\" for a long nine years, during which he played the part of detective Robert Green. He has led a successful acting career before the show and continues on that same path after leaving it. He played the antagonist on Netflix\'s \"Daredevil\", and appeared in the film \"The Magnificent Seven\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1332\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/210.jpg\" alt=\"2\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Ice-T</h1>\r\n<h3>Rap star turned actor Ice-T is one of the show\'s most recognizable faces. He has been portraying detective Odafin \"Fin\" Tutuola on the \"Special Victims Unit\" spinoff ever since its second season, back in 2000. Although his career still revolves around \"Law and Order\" to this day, you can still see him having the occasional guest role both on television and in film.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1333\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/312.jpg\" alt=\"3\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Carolyn McCormick</h1>\r\n<h3>Carolyn McCormick portrayed the character of Dr. Elizabeth Oliver on the original \"Law and Order\" as well as on some of the show\'s spin-offs. Today she sticks to playing a doctor, this time on the CBS series \"Madam Secretary\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1334\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/410.jpg\" alt=\"4\" width=\"551\" height=\"311\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Jill Hennessy</h1>\r\n<h3>Jill Hennessy was truly stunning on the show. She assumed the role of prosecutor Claire Kincaid from the first season of the show up to its third season. Today, although she is nearing 50, she still makes regular appearances on TV shows such as \"Madame Secretary\" and \"The Good Wife\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1335\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/511.jpg\" alt=\"5\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Paul Sorvino</h1>\r\n<h3>Known to Law and Order fans as NYPD Sergeant Phil Cerreta, Paul Sorvino has been on the show for many years. He once had a thriving career acting in films but nowadays mostly appears on the small screen, most prominently in a supporting role on \"The Goldbergs\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1336\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/68.jpg\" alt=\"6\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Anthony Anderson</h1>\r\n<h3>Anthony Anderson had a very short and unmemorable stint on the show from 2008 until the show\'s ending in 2010. He played the character of detective Kevin Bernard, which didn\'t get as much appreciation from the fans as the show\'s producers must have hoped it would. Nowadays Anderson has the leading role in the successful comedy show \"Blackish\", a role for which he continues to receive critical acclaim.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1337\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/72.jpg\" alt=\"7\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Mariska Hargitay</h1>\r\n<h3>Mariska has appeared on \"Law and Order: Special Victims Unit\" for many years, during which she had faithfully portrayed the critically acclaimed character of Detective Olivia Benson; she has won several Primetime Emmy awards for her portrayal of the character. She will always remain Olivia Benson in the hearts of \"Law and Order\" fans worldwide, but you can catch her playing an entirely different character on the shows \"Chicago Fire\" and \"Chicago PD\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1338\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/83.jpg\" alt=\"8\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Katheryn Erbe</h1>\r\n<h3>Katheryn Erbe portrayed detective Alexandra James on \"Law and Order: Criminal Intent\", the show\'s famous spin-off series, from 2001 all the way to 2010. She has mainly appeared in some small roles in films since then. She made a heartwarming return to the role of detective James as a guest star on \"Law and Order: Special Victims Unit\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1339\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/92.jpg\" alt=\"9\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Leslie Hendrix</h1>\r\n<h3>Leslie Hendrix\'s character, the medical examiner Elizabeth Rodgers, is one of the show\'s greatest cross-over characters and has appeared on four (!) different versions of the show. She enjoys continuous success in her career and has appeared on several successful TV shows, such as \"The Good Wife\", \"The Blacklist\" and \"Gotham\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1340\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/102.jpg\" alt=\"10\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>John Cariani</h1>\r\n<h3>John Cariani has appeared as the forensics expert Julian Beck on the original \"Law and Order\" for five years. Before that, he appeared in two episodes of \"Law and Order: Criminal Intent\" in 2001 and in 2003. Today John mostly does stage work, though he does appear in minor roles on TV now and then, on shows such as \"Homeland\", \"The Good Wife\" and \"The Blacklist\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1341\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/113.jpg\" alt=\"11\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Benjamin Bratt</h1>\r\n<h3>The charismatic, powerful presence of Benjamin Bratt served the show well for four years, during which he appeared on the show as detective Rey Curtis. Benjamin left the show to pursue a career in film. He has found some success in pursuing this goal, appearing in films such as \"Ride Along 2\" and \"Dr. Strange\". He also guest-starred on the popular TV series \"Modern Family\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1342\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/122.jpg\" alt=\"12\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>William H. Burns</h1>\r\n<h3>William Burns portrayed officer Robbins on a recurring role on \"Special Victims Unit\" for ten years. Besides his work on the show, he mainly appeared in small, supporting roles in films such as \"Café Society\" and \"The Bourne Ultimatum\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1343\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/132.jpg\" alt=\"13\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Jerry Orbach</h1>\r\n<h3>Jerry Orbach faithfully served the show for 12 years as detective Lennie Briscoe. Sadly, his career and consequently his role on the show were cut short because of his untimely death in 2004. He was only 69 years old when he passed away.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1344\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/142.jpg\" alt=\"14\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Richard Brooks</h1>\r\n<h3>Richard Brooks was also part of the show\'s original cast. He portrayed the character of District Attorney Paul Robinette from 1990 to 1993. Nowadays he plays the character of Patrick on BET\'s \"Being Mary Jane\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1345\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/152.jpg\" alt=\"15\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Christopher Meloni</h1>\r\n<h3>Christopher Meloni portrayed one of SVU\'s most beloved characters in Detective Elliot Stabler. He has a thriving career in film, appearing in films such as \"The Diary of a Teenage Girl\", \"Sin City: A Dame To Kill For\" and \"Man of Steel\". He can also be spotted in a supporting role on the TV series \"Veep\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1346\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/162.jpg\" alt=\"16\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Elisabeth Rohm</h1>\r\n<h3>The gorgeous Elisabeth Rohm was on the show from 2001 to 2005 as Assistant District Attorney Serena Southerlyn. Since leaving the show she has been focusing mainly on her career in film. She has a close working relationship with famous director David O. Russell and had supporting roles in two of his films, \"Joy\" and \"American Hustle\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1347\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/172.jpg\" alt=\"17\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Sam Waterson</h1>\r\n<h3>Sam Waterson spent 16 years on the show as Jack McCoy, the tough New York City District Attorney. He\'s a wonderful, charismatic actor and one of the main reasons for the show\'s success and ability to stay on the air for such a long time.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1348\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/182.jpg\" alt=\"18\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Carey Lowell</h1>\r\n<h3>Carey Lowell portrayed Assistant District Attorney Jamie Ross on the show. Her stunning beauty did not only show on the TV screen but in real life as well, which surely was one of the reasons why she was married to famous actor Richard Gere for 11 years. Nowadays Lowell doesn\'t really act anymore.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1349\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/192.jpg\" alt=\"19\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Allison Siko</h1>\r\n<h3>Alison Siko is still young, and so most of her career lies in front of her and not the other way around. She appeared on \"Law and Order: Special Victims Unit\" for four seasons as Detective Elliot Stabler\'s daughter Kathleen Stabler. Sadly, she hasn\'t appeared in pretty much anything since leaving the show but is said to be pursuing roles in movies rather than on television.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1350\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/202.jpg\" alt=\"20\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Fred Dalton Thompson</h1>\r\n<h3>Fred Dalton Thompson was cast in the show in his final months of serving as a senator back in 2003. He played the character of Arthur Branch, Manhattan\'s D.A., on the show. After trying to run for president in the 2008 elections, Fred Dalton Thompson sadly passed away aged 73 in 2015.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1351\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/212.jpg\" alt=\"21\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Stephanie March</h1>\r\n<h3>Stephanie March portrayed the character of Assistant District Attorney Alexandra Cabot for three seasons on \"Law and Order: Special Victims Unit\". Sadly, she makes more headlines in her private life than in her professional life, with her 2015 divorce from her husband making some very unpleasant headlines in the media.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1352\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/222.jpg\" alt=\"22\" width=\"551\" height=\"311\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Tamara Tunie</h1>\r\n<h3>Tamara Tunie has been appearing on and off the \"Special Victims Unit\" cast list for ten years. In the show, she portrayed the character of Dr. Melinda Warner. It\'s not the only role she\'s had on TV, though, and the experienced actress has most recently appeared on some successful television shows such as \"Chicago Fire\", \"Zoo\", and \"Elementary\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1353\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/232.jpg\" alt=\"23\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>George Dzundza</h1>\r\n<h3>George Dzundza played detective Max Greevey albeit for the very short period of just one season. At just over 70 years old, George is still making appearances on various TV shows. He most recently appeared on \"Stargate SG-1\" and on \"Grey\'s Anatomy\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1354\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/242.jpg\" alt=\"24\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Diane Neal</h1>\r\n<h3>Diane Neal\'s character Assistant District Attorney Casey Novak joined the \"Law and Order: Special Victims Unit\" to replace Stephanie March\'s character, Alexandra Cabot. She can be seen today appearing on the TV series \"NCIS\" and its own spin-off series \"NCIS: New Orleans\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1355\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/252.jpg\" alt=\"25\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Alana De La Garza</h1>\r\n<h3>The beautiful Alana has appeared not only on the original \"Law and Order\", but on \"Special Victims Unit\" and \"LA\" as well. She portrayed Consuela \"Connie\" Rubirosa on the show, who started as an Assistant District Attorney but became an Assistant U.S. Attorney for the Southern District of New York as the shows progressed. Today she can be seen playing in \"Criminal Minds: Beyond Borders\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1356\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/261.jpg\" alt=\"26\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Jeremy Sisto</h1>\r\n<h3>Jeremy Sisto was another addition to the cast back in 2008, which means he was on the show for only two years until it ended in 2010. He played the character of Detective Cyrus Lupo during those two seasons. Nowadays he can be seen on the TV series \"Suburbia\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1357\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/271.jpg\" alt=\"27\" width=\"551\" height=\"311\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Andy Karl</h1>\r\n<h3>Andy Karl has done most of his work on the stage on Broadway, but he also appeared on \"Special Victims Unit\" as Sergeant Mike Dodds. He has returned to the stage since then, where you can see him acting in various plays on the stage in New York.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1358\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/282.jpg\" alt=\"28\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Andrea Navedo</h1>\r\n<h3>Detective Ana Cordova has appeared in four seasons of \"Law and Order\". Andrea Navedo, the talented actress who portrayed her, can be seen today on CW\'s successful series \"Jane The Virgin\", where she is a part of the show\'s main cast.</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1359\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/292.jpg\" alt=\"29\" width=\"551\" height=\"311\" />\r\n\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<h1>Michael Moriarty</h1>\r\n<h3>Michael Moriarty was a part of the show\'s initial cast, appearing on four on the first seasons of the show as Executive Assistant District Attorney Ben Stone. He has been in the business for a very long time, and at the age of 75 has a long list of film appearances to his name. One of the most recent additions to this list is the 2012 film \"The Yellow Paper\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1360\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/302.jpg\" alt=\"30\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>B.D. Wong</h1>\r\n<h3>Bradley Darryl Wong is a Tony award-winning American actor who played Dr. George Huang on the show\'s spin-off series \"Special Victims Unit\". He currently appears on the TV shows \"Mr. Robot\" and \"Gotham\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1361\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/313.jpg\" alt=\"31\" width=\"551\" height=\"311\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Milena Govich</h1>\r\n<h3>Milena Govich played NYPD detective Nina Cassidy on the show, albeit for just one lone season. She recently had small parts on \"The Mentalist\" and on \"Finding Carter\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1362\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/322.jpg\" alt=\"32\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Linus Roache</h1>\r\n<h3>Linus Roache is a highly respected, talented actor. He has made numerous appearances both in film and on television and joined the cast of the show for its last two seasons as D.A. Michael Cutter. He most recently had parts on the hit television shows \"The Blacklist\" and \"Vikings\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1363\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/332.jpg\" alt=\"33\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dann Florek</h1>\r\n<h3>Dann Florek appeared in the original \"Law and Order\" as Captain Donald Cragen and has reprised his role in the spin-off \"Special Victims Unit\". He has retired from acting in 2015 after some very long and prosperous years in the business. He most recently appeared on the TV series \"Under The Dome\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1364\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/342.jpg\" alt=\"34\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Dennis Farina</h1>\r\n<h3>Dennis Farina was a well-known and highly respected actor by the time he joined the cast of the show as Detective Joe Fontana. His character was written into the show in order to replace Lennie Briscoe, but never really clicked with the audiences. Farina, sadly, passed away in 2013, at the age of 69.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1365\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/351.jpg\" alt=\"35\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>S. Epatha Merkerson</h1>\r\n<h3>Sharon Epatha Merkerson was on the show for a long time – 17 years to be exact. She portrayed the NYPD lieutenant Anita Van Buren. Since the show ended, Merkerson appeared as Sharon Goodwin on all the \"Chicago\" series\' shows.</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1366\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/362.jpg\" alt=\"36\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Chris North</h1>\r\n<h3>Chris North became known for his role as detective Mike Logan on the show; at roughly the same time, he played the character of Mr. Big on \"Sex and the City\". Noth, who is now 61 years old, just recently finished his part on the successful long-running TV series \"The Good Wife\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1367\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/372.jpg\" alt=\"37\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /><!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Jesse L. Martin</h1>\r\n<h3>Jesse L. Martin played detective Ed Green on the show and partnered fellow co-star Jerry Orbach on screen. He was famously one of the first black characters on the show. Jesse found success in his past Law &amp; Order life as he is now a member of the main cast of Netflix\'s successful show \"The Arrow\".</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1368\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/382.jpg\" alt=\"38\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" /> <!--nextpage--></h3>\r\n<h1>Angie Harmon</h1>\r\n<h3>The beautiful Angie Harmon started her acting career with her role on the show as District Attorney Abbie Carmichael. She is 44 years old today, and you can catch her on TNT\'s TV series \"Rizzoli and Isles\".</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1369\" src=\"http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/392.jpg\" alt=\"39\" width=\"549\" height=\"310\" />','The Cast Of Law & Order: Then & Now','','publish','open','open','','the-cast-of-law-order-then-now','','','2017-01-27 09:17:08','2017-01-27 09:17:08','',0,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/?p=1330',0,'post','',0),(1331,2,'2017-01-26 13:10:11','2017-01-26 13:10:11','','1','','inherit','open','closed','','1-7','','','2017-01-26 13:10:11','2017-01-26 13:10:11','',1330,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/112.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1332,2,'2017-01-26 13:10:18','2017-01-26 13:10:18','','2','','inherit','open','closed','','2-7','','','2017-01-26 13:10:18','2017-01-26 13:10:18','',1330,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/210.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1333,2,'2017-01-26 13:10:23','2017-01-26 13:10:23','','3','','inherit','open','closed','','3-7','','','2017-01-26 13:10:23','2017-01-26 13:10:23','',1330,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/312.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1334,2,'2017-01-26 13:10:27','2017-01-26 13:10:27','','4','','inherit','open','closed','','4-6','','','2017-01-26 13:10:27','2017-01-26 13:10:27','',1330,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/410.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1335,2,'2017-01-26 13:10:31','2017-01-26 13:10:31','','5','','inherit','open','closed','','5-7','','','2017-01-26 13:10:31','2017-01-26 13:10:31','',1330,'http://www.feelsyoung.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/511.jpg'